<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
<eesti>Tegutsemise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right to Operate </inglise>
<eesti>1. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 1 </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusluba </eesti>
<inglise>Activity Licences </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 48. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 48. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusluba </eesti>
<inglise>Activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hinguna tegutsemiseks peab isikul olema vastav tegevusluba (edaspidi k&auml;esolevas osas tegevusluba). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to operate as an investment firm, a person shall hold a relevant activity licence (hereinafter in this Part activity licence). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusluba on t&auml;htajatu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Activity licences are issued for an unspecified term. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegevusluba ei ole &uuml;leantav ning selle omandamine ja kasutamine teiste isikute poolt on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Activity licences are not transferable, and the acquisition or use thereof by other persons is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa ulatus </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusluba antakse kas eraldi m&otilde;ne investeerimisteenuse v&otilde;i k&otilde;ikide investeerimisteenuste osutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An activity licence is issued for the provision of individual investment services separately or for the provision of all investment services. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hing v&otilde;ib osutada &uuml;ksnes neid investeerimisteenuseid, mille kohta talle on antud tegevusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An investment firm may only provide investment services for the provision of which it has been granted an activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>Teiste investeerimisteenuste osutamiseks peab investeerimis&uuml;hing taotlema t&auml;iendava tegevusloa. </eesti>
<inglise>In order to provide other investment services, an investment firm shall apply for an additional activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui seadusest ei tulene teisiti, v&otilde;ib iga investeerimis&uuml;hing osutada k&otilde;iki investeerimisk&otilde;rvalteenuseid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Unless otherwise provided by law, an investment firm may provide all non-core services. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 50. </inglise>
<eesti>Krediidiasutuse ja fondivalitseja tegevusload </eesti>
<inglise>Activity licences of credit institution and management company </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Krediidiasutuse tegevusluba omav &auml;ri&uuml;hing ei pea investeerimisteenuste osutamiseks eraldi tegevusluba taotlema. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A company which holds an activity licence of a credit institution need not apply for a separate activity licence for the provision of investment services. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Fondivalitseja tegevusluba omav &auml;ri&uuml;hing ei pea v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiportfelli valitsemiseks eraldi tegevusluba taotlema. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A company which holds an activity licence of a management company need not apply for a separate activity licence for the management of securities portfolios. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 51. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 51. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus </eesti>
<inglise>Decision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa annab ja selle tunnistab kehtetuks inspektsioon oma otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An activity licence shall be issued or revoked by a decision of the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusloa kohta tehtavas otsuses m&auml;rgitakse v&auml;hemalt: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A decision regarding an activity licence shall at least set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) isiku, kelle kohta otsus tehakse, nimi ja registrikood; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name and registry code of the person with regard to whom the decision is made; </inglise>
<eesti>2) investeerimisteenuse liik v&otilde;i liigid, mille kohta otsus tehakse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the type or types of investment services with regard to which the decision is made; </inglise>
<eesti>3) otsuse tegemise ja j&otilde;ustumise kuup&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the date on which the decision is made and the date on which it enters into force. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegevusloa andmisest keeldumise ja tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamise korral peab otsus sisaldama sellekohast p&otilde;hjendust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A decision refusing to grant or revoking an activity licence shall contain the justification therefor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 52. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 52. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsusest teavitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Notification regarding decision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa kohta tehtud otsuse edastab inspektsioon viivitamata p&auml;rast otsuse tegemist isikule, kelle tegevusloa kohta otsus tehti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Supervision Authority shall forward a decision regarding an activity licence to the person with regard to whom the decision is made immediately after making the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusloa andmise v&otilde;i kehtetuks tunnistamise otsus avalikustatakse hiljemalt otsuse tegemisele j&auml;rgneval t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 237 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A decision regarding the issue or revocation of an activity licence shall be disclosed at the latest on the working day following the making of the decision pursuant to the procedure prescribed in &sect; 237 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamisest teatab inspektsioon ringh&auml;&auml;lingus ning v&auml;hemalt &uuml;hes &uuml;leriigilise levikuga p&auml;evalehes hiljemalt kolmandal p&auml;eval, arvates kehtetuks tunnistamise otsuse tegemisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Supervision Authority shall disclose information regarding the revocation of an activity licence through the broadcast media and in at least one national daily newspaper not later than on the third day after the decision to revoke the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 53. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 53. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa taotlus </eesti>
<inglise>Application for activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa taotlemiseks tuleb esitada inspektsioonile vastav taotlus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to apply for an activity licence, a relevant application shall be submitted to the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Taotlus koosneb kirjalikust avaldusest ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 54 nimetatud lisadest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An application shall consist of a written application and the annexes specified in &sect; 54 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotluse vormi kehtestab rahandusminister oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The format of applications shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Taotlusele ja sellega seonduvalt hiljem esitatud andmetele lisatakse taotleja k&otilde;igi juhatuse liikmete poolt allkirjastatud kinnitus taotlemisel esitatud andmete ja dokumentide &otilde;igsuse kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Confirmation regarding the accuracy of the information and documents submitted upon application, signed by all members of the management board of the applicant, shall be appended to the application and to any information submitted later in connection with the application. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 54 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 5 ja 6 nimetatud f&uuml;&uuml;siliste isikute kohta esitatud andmete ja dokumentide &otilde;igsust kinnitavad nimetatud isikud oma allkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>The accuracy of information and documents submitted with regard to natural persons specified in clauses 54 (1) 5) and 6) of this Act shall be confirmed by the above-mentioned persons by their signatures. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 54. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 54. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotlemisel esitatavad andmed </eesti>
<inglise>Information submitted upon application </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa taotlemiseks tuleb investeerimis&uuml;hingu asutajatel v&otilde;i registreeritud aktsiaseltsi juhatusel inspektsioonile esitada j&auml;rgmised dokumendid ja andmed: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to apply for an activity licence, the founders of an investment firm or the management board of a registered public limited company shall submit the following documents and information to the Supervision Authority: </inglise>
<eesti>1) taotleja asutamisel - notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud asutamisleping v&otilde;i -otsus ning krediidiasutuse teatis aktsiakapitali sissemaksmise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) upon foundation of the applicant - a notarised memorandum of association or foundation resolution and a notice issued by a credit institution regarding the payment of share capital; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tegutseva &auml;ri&uuml;hingu puhul - &auml;riregistri registrikartoteegi B osa registrikaardi &auml;rakiri; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in the case of an operating company - a copy of the registry card from part B of the card register of the commercial register; </inglise>
<eesti>3) p&otilde;hikirja &auml;rakiri, tegutseva &auml;ri&uuml;hingu puhul ka &uuml;ldkoosoleku otsus p&otilde;hikirja muutmise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a copy of the articles of association and, in the case of an operating company, also the resolution of the general meeting on amendment of the articles of association; </inglise>
<eesti>4) taotleja aktsion&auml;ride nimekiri, milles on andmed iga aktsion&auml;ri sissemakse suuruse, aktsiate ja h&auml;&auml;lte arvu kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a list of shareholders of the applicant, which sets out information on the size of the contribution and the number of shares and votes of each shareholder; </inglise>
<eesti>5) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 73 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud andmed taotlejas olulist osalust omavate aktsion&auml;ride kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>5) information specified in subsection 73 (2) of this Act relating to shareholders with a qualifying holding in the applicant; </inglise>
<eesti>6) andmed &auml;ri&uuml;hingu n&otilde;ukogu ja juhatuse liikmete ning teiste tegevjuhtkonda kuuluvate isikute (edaspidi juht) ja siseaudiitori kohta, mis sisaldavad v&auml;hemalt isiku ees- ja perekonnanime, isikukoodi v&otilde;i selle puudumisel s&uuml;nniaega, elukoha aadressi, hariduse kirjeldust, t&auml;ielikku &uuml;levaadet t&ouml;&ouml;- ja ametikohtadest ning osalemisest ettev&otilde;tluses viimase 10 aasta jooksul, samuti tema kohta karistusregistrisse kantud karistustest; </eesti>
<inglise>6) information on the members of the supervisory board and management board of the company and other persons belonging to the management (hereinafter managers), and on the internal auditor of the company, which sets out at least the person's given name and surname, personal identification code or, in the absence thereof, date of birth, residential address, educational background, a complete list of places of employment and positions held as well as participation in business during the last ten years, and punishments entered in the punishment register with regard to him or her; </inglise>
<eesti>7) andmed &auml;ri&uuml;hingute kohta, milles taotleja v&otilde;i selle n&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;i juhatuse liikme osalus on suurem kui 20 protsenti, kusjuures nimetatud andmed peavad sisaldama aktsia- v&otilde;i osakapitali suurust, tegevusalade loetelu ning eelmainitud isikute osaluse suurust; </eesti>
<inglise>7) information on companies in which the holding of the applicant or any member of its management board or supervisory board exceeds 20 per cent, which also sets out the amount of share capital, a list of the areas of activity and the size of the holding of the above-mentioned persons; </inglise>
<eesti>8) taotleja audiitori ees- ja perekonnanimi, isikukood, elukoha aadress ja audiitori tunnistuse number; </eesti>
<inglise>8) the given name, surname, personal identification code and residential address of the auditor of the applicant and the number of the auditor's professional licence; </inglise>
<eesti>9) taotleja viimasena kinnitatud majandusaasta aruanne; </eesti>
<inglise>9) the last approved annual report of the applicant; </inglise>
<eesti>10) taotleja bilanss ja kasumiaruanne taotluse esitamisele eelnenud kuu l&otilde;pu seisuga juhul, kui taotluse esitamisel on majandusaasta l&otilde;pust m&ouml;&ouml;dunud rohkem kui seitse kuud; </eesti>
<inglise>10) the balance sheet and income statement of the applicant as at the end of the month prior to submission of the application if, upon submission of the application, more than seven months have passed since the end of the financial year; </inglise>
<eesti>11) Maksuameti kohaliku asutuse t&otilde;end taotleja ja k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktides 5 ja 7 nimetatud isikute maksuv&otilde;lgnevuste puudumise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>11) a statement from the local Tax Board Office certifying the absence of tax arrears with respect to the applicant and the persons specified in clauses 5) and 7) of this subsection; </inglise>
<eesti>12) taotleja kolme aasta &auml;riplaan, mis sisaldab v&auml;hemalt kavandatavate tegevuste, taotleja organisatsioonilise &uuml;lesehituse, tegevuskohtade, rakendatavate infotehnoloogiliste s&uuml;steemide ja muude tehniliste vahendite ning majandusn&auml;itajate kirjeldust; </eesti>
<inglise>12) the applicant's three-year business plan which sets out at least a description of the applicant's planned activities, organisational structure, places of business, information systems and other technical facilities, and a description of its economic indicators; </inglise>
<eesti>13) taotleja raamatupidamise sise-eeskirja ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 82 nimetatud sise-eeskirja projekt; </eesti>
<inglise>13) the draft accounting policies and procedures of the applicant and the draft policies and procedures specified in &sect; 82 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>14) rahapesu t&otilde;kestamise seaduse (RT I 1998, 110, 1811; 2000, 84, 533) &sect; 13 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud tegevusjuhend ja selle t&auml;itmise kontrollimise sisekontrollieeskiri; </eesti>
<inglise>14) the code of conduct and internal audit rules to monitor compliance with the code of conduct as prescribed in subsection 13 (2) of the Money Laundering Prevention Act (RT I 1998, 110, 1811; 2000, 84, 533); </inglise>
<eesti>15) t&otilde;end riigil&otilde;ivu tasumise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>15) proof of payment of the state fee. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&auml;iendava tegevusloa taotlemisel esitab investeerimis&uuml;hing k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 2, 3, 9, 10, 12, 13 ja 15 nimetatud andmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon application for an additional activity licence, an investment firm shall submit the information specified in clauses (1) 2), 3), 9), 10), 12), 13) and 15) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 55. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 55. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotluse l&auml;bivaatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Review of application </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui taotleja ei ole tegevusloa taotlemisel esitanud k&otilde;iki k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 54 nimetatud andmeid ja dokumente v&otilde;i need ei ole t&auml;ielikud v&otilde;i n&otilde;uetekohaselt vormistatud, n&otilde;uab inspektsioon taotlejalt puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an applicant has failed to submit all the information and documents specified in &sect; 54 of this Act or if such information or documents are incomplete or have not been prepared in accordance with the requirements, the Supervision Authority shall demand elimination of the deficiencies by the applicant. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 54 nimetatud andmete ja dokumentide p&otilde;hjal ei ole v&otilde;imalik veenduda, kas tegevusloa taotlejal on investeerimisteenuste osutamiseks piisavad v&otilde;imalused ja ta vastab seadusega v&otilde;i selle alusel investeerimis&uuml;hingule s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele, v&otilde;ib inspektsioon n&otilde;uda t&auml;iendavate andmete ja dokumentide esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority may demand the submission of additional information and documents if it is not convinced on the basis of the information and documents specified in &sect; 54 of this Act as to whether the applicant has adequate facilities for the provision of investment services or whether it meets the requirements for investment firms prescribed by law or on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Taotleja esitatud andmete kontrollimiseks v&otilde;ib inspektsioon n&otilde;uda t&auml;psustavate andmete ja dokumentide esitamist ning teostada kohapealset kontrolli. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In order to verify the information submitted by the applicant, the Supervision Authority may demand the submission of additional information and documents and may carry out an on-site inspection. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1-3 nimetatud andmed esitatakse inspektsiooni poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud m&otilde;istlikul t&auml;htajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The data referred to in subsections (1) -(3) of this section shall be submitted during a reasonable term determined by the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Otsuse tegevusloa andmise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise kohta teeb inspektsioon kuue kuu jooksul p&auml;rast inspektsioonile vastava avalduse laekumist, kuid mitte hiljem kui kahe kuu jooksul p&auml;rast k&otilde;igi vajalike dokumentide ja andmete laekumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Supervision Authority shall make a decision regarding the issue of or refusal to issue an activity licence within six months after the Supervision Authority receives a corresponding application, but not later than within two months after receipt of all the necessary documents and information. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Otsuse t&auml;iendava tegevusloa andmise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise kohta teeb inspektsioon &uuml;he kuu jooksul p&auml;rast inspektsioonile vastava avalduse ja k&otilde;igi n&otilde;utavate andmete ning dokumentide laekumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Supervision Authority shall make a decision regarding the issue of or refusal to issue an additional activity licence within one month after the Supervision Authority receives a corresponding application and all the necessary information and documents. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 56. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 56. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa andmisest keeldumine </eesti>
<inglise>Refusal to issue activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>Inspektsioon keeldub tegevusloa andmisest, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>The Supervision Authority shall refuse to issue an activity licence if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tegevusloa taotlemisel esitatud andmed v&otilde;i dokumendid ei vasta k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i need on eba&otilde;iged, eksitavad v&otilde;i mittet&auml;ielikud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the information or documents submitted upon application for the activity licence do not meet the requirements provided for in this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof or are inaccurate, misleading or incomplete; </inglise>
<eesti>2) taotleja ei esitanud t&auml;htaegselt v&otilde;i on keeldunud esitamast inspektsioonile loa taotlemisel esitamisele kuuluvaid v&otilde;i muid inspektsiooni poolt n&otilde;utud andmeid, dokumente v&otilde;i teavet; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the applicant fails, within the prescribed term, or refuses to submit the information and documents subject to submission upon application for a permit or as are requested by the Supervision Authority to the Supervision Authority; </inglise>
<eesti>3) taotleja ei vasta k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the applicant does not meet the requirements provided for in this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>4) inspektsiooni hinnangul ei vasta taotleja juht, siseaudiitor v&otilde;i taotlejas olulist osalust omav isik k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) in the opinion of the Supervision Authority, the manager or internal auditor of the applicant or a person having a qualifying holding in the applicant does not meet the requirements provided for in this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>5) taotleja on olulisel m&auml;&auml;ral v&otilde;i korduvalt rikkunud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;udeid v&otilde;i taotleja tegevus v&otilde;i tegevusetus ei vasta headele &auml;ritavadele. </eesti>
<inglise>5) the applicant has materially or repeatedly violated requirements provided for in legislation or if the activities or omissions of the applicant are in contradiction with good business practices. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 57. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 57. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa l&otilde;ppemine </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusluba l&otilde;peb: </eesti>
<inglise>An activity licence terminates: </inglise>
<eesti>1) investeerimis&uuml;hingu l&otilde;petamise otsuse tegemisel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) if a decision is taken to dissolve the investment firm; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) if the activity licence is revoked; </inglise>
<eesti>3) investeerimis&uuml;hingute &uuml;hendamisel - &uuml;hendataval isikul; </eesti>
<inglise>3) in the event of a merger of investment firms, if it is held by the firm being acquired; </inglise>
<eesti>4) investeerimis&uuml;hingu pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>4) if the investment firm is declared bankrupt. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 58. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 58. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamine on tegevusloa andmise otsusega omandatud &otilde;iguse t&auml;ielik v&otilde;i osaline &auml;rav&otilde;tmine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Revocation of an activity licence is the total or partial deprivation of a right acquired by a decision to issue an activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa v&otilde;ib tunnistada kehtetuks t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i &uuml;ksikute investeerimisteenuste kaupa, piiritledes &otilde;igused, mis tegevusloa omanik tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamisega kaotab. </eesti>
<inglise>An activity licence may be revoked completely or by individual investment services, whereupon the rights of which the holder of the activity licence is deprived upon revocation of the activity licence shall be specified. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistada, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority may revoke an activity licence if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) investeerimis&uuml;hing ei ole alustanud tegevusloas n&auml;idatud tegevust 12 kuu jooksul tegevusloa andmisest arvates v&otilde;i investeerimis&uuml;hingu tegevus on peatunud kauemaks kui 12 kuuks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the investment firm does not commence the activities specified in the licence within twelve months as of the issue of the activity licence or if the activities of the investment firm are suspended for more than twelve months; </inglise>
<eesti>2) on ilmnenud, et tegevusloa taotlemisel on esitatud eksitavaid, tegelikkusele mittevastavaid andmeid v&otilde;i v&otilde;ltsitud dokumente v&otilde;i investeerimis&uuml;hing on hiljem esitanud selliseid andmeid v&otilde;i dokumente; </eesti>
<inglise>2) it has been established that misleading or inaccurate information or falsified documents were submitted upon application for the activity licence or if the investment firm has later submitted such information or documents; </inglise>
<eesti>3) investeerimis&uuml;hing on rikkunud k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatut; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the investment firm violates the provisions of this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>4) inspektsiooni hinnangul investeerimis&uuml;hingu juht, siseaudiitor v&otilde;i investeerimis&uuml;hingus olulist osalust omav isik ei vasta k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) in the opinion of the Supervision Authority, the manager or internal auditor of the investment firm or a person having a qualifying holding in the investment firm does not meet the requirements provided for in this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>5) investeerimis&uuml;hing on olulisel m&auml;&auml;ral v&otilde;i korduvalt rikkunud muid &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;udeid v&otilde;i investeerimis&uuml;hingu tegevus v&otilde;i tegevusetus ei vasta headele &auml;ritavadele; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the investment firm has materially or repeatedly violated other requirements provided for in legislation or if its activities or omissions are in contradiction with good business practices; </inglise>
<eesti>6) investeerimis&uuml;hing ei ole t&auml;ies ulatuses v&otilde;i t&auml;htaegselt t&auml;itnud inspektsiooni poolt tehtud ettekirjutust; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the investment firm fails to comply with a precept issued by the Supervision Authority in full or within the specified term; </inglise>
<eesti>7) investeerimis&uuml;hing ei ole v&otilde;imeline t&auml;itma endale v&otilde;etud kohustusi v&otilde;i tema tegevus kahjustab muul p&otilde;hjusel oluliselt investorite v&otilde;i teiste klientide huve v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru korrap&auml;rast toimimist; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the investment firm is unable to perform the obligations it has assumed or if, for any other reason, its activities significantly damage the interests of investors or other clients or adversely affect the regular functioning of the securities market; </inglise>
<eesti>8) investeerimis&uuml;hing ei ole t&auml;htaegselt v&otilde;i t&auml;ies ulatuses tasunud Tagatisfondi seaduses (RT I 2002, 23, 131) etten&auml;htud investorikaitse osafondi osamakseid. </eesti>
<inglise>8) the investment firm fails to pay the contributions to the Investor Protection Sectoral Fund prescribed in the Guarantee Fund Act (RT I 2002, 23, 131) within the specified term or in full. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.02.2002 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2002 - RT I 2002, 23, 131) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.02.02 entered into force 01.07.02 - RT I 2002, 23, 131) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegevusluba tunnistatakse kehtetuks investeerimis&uuml;hingu taotlusel, kui ta ei osuta enam investeerimisteenuseid ning kui tema klientide &otilde;igustatud huvid on seejuures k&uuml;llaldaselt kaitstud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An activity licence shall be revoked on the application of the investment firm if it no longer provides investment services and if the legitimate interests of its clients are thereby adequately protected. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Enne tegevusloa k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 alusel kehtetuks tunnistamise otsustamist v&otilde;ib inspektsioon teha investeerimis&uuml;hingule t&auml;htajalise ettekirjutuse tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamise aluseks olevate puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Prior to making a decision to revoke an activity licence on the basis of subsection (2) of this section, the Supervision Authority may issue a precept to the investment firm establishing a term for elimination of the deficiencies which are the basis for revocation of the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>2. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevus v&auml;lisriigis </eesti>
<inglise>Activities Abroad </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 59. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 59. </inglise>
<eesti>T&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja ja filiaal v&auml;lisriigis </eesti>
<inglise>Subsidiary and branch abroad </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui Eestis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hing soovib asutada investeerimisteenuseid osutavat t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjat v&otilde;i filiaali v&auml;lisriigis v&otilde;i omandada osalust m&otilde;nes v&auml;lisriigi investeerimis&uuml;hingus, mille tulemusena viimane muutub tema t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjaks, tuleb tal selleks taotleda inspektsioonilt vastav luba (edaspidi k&auml;esolevas jaos luba). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an investment firm registered in Estonia wishes to found a subsidiary or branch providing investment services abroad or acquire a holding in a foreign investment firm, as a result of which the latter becomes a subsidiary of the Estonian firm, relevant permission (hereinafter in this Division permission) shall be sought from the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Loa taotlemiseks tuleb esitada inspektsioonile kirjalik avaldus ja j&auml;rgmised andmed: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to apply for permission, a written application and the following information shall be submitted to the Supervision Authority: </inglise>
<eesti>1) riigi nimetus, kus t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjat v&otilde;i filiaali soovitakse asutada v&otilde;i kus registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hingus soovitakse osalust omandada; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name of the state in which the subsidiary or branch is to be founded or in which the investment firm in which a holding is to be acquired is registered; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja &auml;rinimi ja aadress v&otilde;i filiaali nimetus ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the business name and address of the subsidiary or the name and address of the branch; </inglise>
<eesti>3) v&auml;lisriigi investeerimis&uuml;hingu, milles soovitakse omandada osalust, kahe viimase majandusaasta aruanded koos esitaja poolt allkirjastatud eestikeelse t&otilde;lkega; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the annual reports for the past two financial years of the foreign investment firm in which a holding is to be acquired, accompanied by a translation into Estonian signed by the person submitting the reports; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i filiaali k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 54 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 12 nimetatud &auml;riplaan, millele lisatakse suhete kirjeldus asutava investeerimis&uuml;hinguga; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the business plan of the subsidiary or branch specified in clause 54 (1) 12) of this Act, accompanied by a description of the relationship with the founding investment firm; </inglise>
<eesti>5) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 54 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 6 nimetatud andmed t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja juhtimisorganite liikmete v&otilde;i filiaali juhataja kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the information specified in clause 54 (1) 6) of this Act on the members of the directing bodies of the subsidiary or the director of the branch; </inglise>
<eesti>6) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 73 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud andmed t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjas olulist osalust omavate isikute kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the information specified in subsection 73 (2) of this Act on persons having a qualifying holding in the subsidiary. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 60. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 60. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa taotluse menetlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Processing of application for permission </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Loa taotlemisele ja taotluse l&auml;bivaatamisele kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 51-53 ja 55 tegevusloa ja taotluse kohta s&auml;testatut, kui k&auml;esolevast jaost ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Unless otherwise provided in this Division, applications for permission and the processing thereof shall be subject to the provisions of &sect;&sect; 51-53 and 55 of this Act regulating activity licences and applications therefor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioon teavitab vastava v&auml;lisriigi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutust esitatud loa taotlusest kahe kuu jooksul, arvates taotluse esitamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority shall inform the securities market supervisory agency of the relevant foreign state of the submission of an application for permission within two months as of the receipt of the application. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui inspektsiooni ja vastava v&auml;lisriigi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutuse vahel ei ole s&otilde;lmitud koost&ouml;&ouml;lepingut, s&otilde;lmib inspektsioon nimetatud asutusega kokkuleppe investeerimis&uuml;hingu t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i filiaali &uuml;le j&auml;relevalve teostamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>If no co-operation agreement exists between the Supervision Authority and the securities market supervisory agency of the relevant foreign state, the Supervision Authority shall enter into an agreement with the agency regarding the exercise of supervision over the subsidiary or branch of the investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Loa andmise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise kohta teeb inspektsioon otsuse kahe kuu jooksul p&auml;rast k&otilde;igi n&otilde;utud andmete ja dokumentide esitamist, kuid mitte hiljem kui kuus kuud p&auml;rast loa taotluse esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Supervision Authority shall make a decision regarding the grant of or refusal to grant permission within two months as of submission of all the necessary information and documents, but not later than within six months as of submission of the application. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa andmisest keeldumise korral peab otsus sisaldama p&otilde;hjendust. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon refusal to grant permission, the decision shall contain the justification for refusal. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Loa andmise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise kohta tehtud otsuse edastab inspektsioon viivitamata taotlejale. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Supervision Authority shall immediately forward the decision regarding the grant of or refusal to grant permission to the applicant. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa andmisest teavitatakse ka vastava v&auml;lisriigi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutust. </eesti>
<inglise>The securities market supervisory agency of the relevant foreign state shall also be notified of the grant of permission. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) V&auml;lisriigis t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjat v&otilde;i filiaali omav Eestis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hing on kohustatud inspektsioonile ja vastava riigi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutusele teatama k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 59 l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 2, 4 ja 5 loetletud andmete muutmise kavatsusest v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kuu ette. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An investment firm registered in Estonia which has a subsidiary or branch in a foreign state is required to notify the Supervision Authority and the securities market supervisory agency of the relevant state at least one month in advance if it intends to amend the information specified in clauses 59 (2) 2), 4) and 5) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 61. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 61. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa andmisest keeldumine </eesti>
<inglise>Refusal to grant permission </inglise>
<eesti>Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib keelduda loa andmisest, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>The Supervision Authority may refuse to grant permission if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) loa taotlemisel esitatud andmed v&otilde;i dokumendid ei vasta k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i need on eba&otilde;iged, eksitavad v&otilde;i mittet&auml;ielikud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the information or documents submitted upon application for permission do not meet the requirements provided for in this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof or are inaccurate, misleading or incomplete; </inglise>
<eesti>2) taotleja ei esitanud t&auml;htaegselt v&otilde;i on keeldunud esitamast inspektsioonile loa taotlemisel esitamisele kuuluvaid v&otilde;i muid inspektsiooni poolt n&otilde;utud andmeid, dokumente v&otilde;i teavet; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the applicant fails, within the prescribed term, or refuses to submit the information and documents subject to submission upon application for permission or as are requested by the Supervision Authority to the Supervision Authority; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja juhtimisorganite liikmed v&otilde;i filiaali juhataja ei vasta k&auml;esolevas seaduses investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhatuse liikmetele kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the members of the directing bodies of the subsidiary or the director of the branch do not meet the requirements for members of the management board of an investment firm as established by this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjas, kelles osalust omandatakse, olulist osalust omavad isikud ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 72 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) persons having a qualifying holding in the subsidiary in which a holding is being acquired do not meet the requirements provided for in &sect; 72 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>5) t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i taotleja finantsseisund ei ole piisavalt kindel; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the financial situation of the subsidiary or applicant is not sufficiently sound; </inglise>
<eesti>6) t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i filiaali asutamine v&otilde;i osaluse omandamine v&otilde;i taotleja poolt esitatud &auml;riplaani rakendamine v&otilde;ib kahjustada investorite huve v&otilde;i investeerimis&uuml;hingu finantsseisundit v&otilde;i usaldusv&auml;&auml;rset tegevust Eestis v&otilde;i vastavas v&auml;lisriigis; </eesti>
<inglise>6) foundation of the subsidiary or branch or acquisition of the holding or implementation of the business plan submitted by the applicant may damage the interests of investors the financial situation of the investment firm or its reliable activities in Estonia or in the relevant foreign state; </inglise>
<eesti>7) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 60 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud lepingut v&otilde;i kokkulepet ei ole s&otilde;lmitud v&otilde;i vastava v&auml;lisriigi &otilde;igusaktid ei v&otilde;imalda t&otilde;husa j&auml;relevalve teostamist ning selleks vajaliku teabe saamist. </eesti>
<inglise>7) no agreement specified in subsection 60 (2) of this Act has been entered into or the legislation of the relevant foreign state does not enable adequate supervision to be exercised and the data necessary therefor to be acquired. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 62. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 62. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of permission </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib tunnistada loa kehtetuks, kui ilmnevad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 58 l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 2, 3 v&otilde;i 6 v&otilde;i &sect; 61 punktides 3-7 s&auml;testatud asjaolud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Supervision Authority may revoke permission if circumstances prescribed in clauses 58 (2) 2), 3) or 6) or clauses 61 3) -7) of this Act emerge. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Loa kehtetuks tunnistamisest teavitab inspektsioon viivitamata investeerimis&uuml;hingut ning vastava v&auml;lisriigi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority shall immediately notify the investment firm which applied for permission and the securities market supervisory agency of the relevant foreign state of the revocation of permission. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 63. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 63. </inglise>
<eesti>Esinduse avamine v&auml;lisriigis </eesti>
<inglise>Opening of representative office abroad </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu esinduse avamisest v&auml;lisriigis peab investeerimis&uuml;hing inspektsiooni teavitama v&auml;hemalt 10 p&auml;eva enne esinduse avamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An investment firm shall notify the Supervision Authority of the opening of a representative office abroad at least ten days prior to the opening of the representative office. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Esinduse avamise korral esitatavate andmete loetelu ja selle esitamise kord kehtestatakse rahandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The list of information to be submitted in the event of the opening of a representative office and the procedure for the submission thereof shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 64. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 64. </inglise>
<eesti>Erisused filiaali asutamisel lepinguriigis </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications for opening of branch in Contracting State </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Filiaali asutamisele lepinguriigis kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 59-61 v&auml;lisriigis filiaali asutamise kohta s&auml;testatut, kui k&auml;esolevast paragrahvist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Unless otherwise prescribed in this section, the provisions of &sect;&sect; 59-61 of this Act regulating the foundation of a branch in a foreign state shall apply with regard to the foundation of a branch in a Contracting State. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Loa saamiseks filiaali asutamiseks lepinguriigis peab Eestis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hing inspektsioonile esitama kirjaliku avalduse ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 59 l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 1, 2, 4 ja 5 nimetatud andmed ning lepinguriigi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutuse aadressi koos dokumentide ning andmetega, mida vastavalt selle riigi &otilde;igusaktidele v&otilde;idakse filiaali asutamisel selle asutuse poolt n&otilde;uda. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to obtain permission to found a branch in a Contracting State, an investment firm registered in Estonia shall submit a written application to the Supervision Authority together with the information specified in clauses 59 (2) 1), 2), 4) and 5) of this Act, the address of the securities market supervisory agency of the Contracting State and any information and documents which, pursuant to the legislation of that state, may be demanded by the agency upon the foundation of a branch. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Loa andmise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise kohta teeb inspektsioon otsuse kahe kuu jooksul p&auml;rast k&otilde;igi k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 n&otilde;utud andmete ja dokumentide esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Supervision Authority shall make a decision regarding the grant of or refusal to grant permission within two months after submission of all the necessary information and documents referred to in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus edastatakse viivitamata taotlejale. </eesti>
<inglise>The decision shall be immediately forwarded to the applicant. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib keelduda loa andmisest, kui ilmnevad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 61 punktides 1, 3, 5 v&otilde;i 6 nimetatud asjaolud. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Supervision Authority may refuse to grant permission if circumstances specified in clauses 61 1), 3), 5) or 6) of this Act become evident. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Loa andmise otsusest teavitab inspektsioon viivitamata vastava lepinguriigi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Supervision Authority shall notify the securities market supervisory agency of the relevant Contracting State immediately of a decision to grant permission. </inglise>
<eesti>Teabele lisatakse investeerimis&uuml;hingut, asutatavat filiaali ja nende finantsseisundit iseloomustavad andmed, samuti andmed investeerimis&uuml;hingu filiaali klientide suhtes rakendatava investori kaitse skeemi kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>Such notice shall be accompanied by information characterising the investment firm, the branch to be founded and their financial situation, as well as information on the investor protection scheme applied with respect to clients of the branch of the investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Eestis rakendatava investori kaitse skeemi muudatustest teavitab inspektsioon viivitamata k&otilde;ikide lepinguriikide v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutusi, kus Eestis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hingud on asutanud filiaali. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Supervision Authority shall immediately notify the securities market supervisory agencies of all Contracting States in which investment firms registered in Estonia have opened a branch of any changes to the investor protection scheme applicable in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Investeerimis&uuml;hing v&otilde;ib asutada filiaali ja alustada tegevust p&auml;rast lepinguriigi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutuselt vastava teabe saamist v&otilde;i p&auml;rast kahe kuu m&ouml;&ouml;dumist k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 5 nimetatud teabe laekumisest lepinguriigi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) An investment firm may open a branch and commence operations after receipt of the relevant information from the securities market supervisory agency of the Contracting State or after two months have passed since receipt of the information specified in subsection (5) of this section by the securities market supervisory agency of the Contracting State. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 65. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 65. </inglise>
<eesti>Piiri&uuml;leste investeerimisteenuste osutamine lepinguriigis </eesti>
<inglise>Provision of cross-border investment services in Contracting State </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eestis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hing peab teavitama inspektsiooni piiri&uuml;leste investeerimisteenuste osutamise kavatsusest lepinguriigis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An investment firm registered in Estonia shall notify the Supervision Authority of its intention to start providing cross-border investment services in a Contracting State. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud teabes n&auml;idatakse v&auml;hemalt lepinguriigi nimi, kus kavatsetakse investeerimisteenuseid osutada, ning &auml;riplaan koos kavandatava tegevuse kirjeldusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The notice referred to in subsection (1) of this section shall set out at least the name of the Contracting State where cross-border investment services are intended to be provided and the business plan with a description of the planned activities. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Inspektsioon teavitab investeerimis&uuml;hingu piiri&uuml;leste investeerimisteenuste osutamise kavatsusest vastava lepinguriigi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutust &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates vastava teabe k&auml;ttesaamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Supervision Authority shall notify the securities market supervisory agency of the relevant Contracting State of the intention of an investment firm to provide cross-border investment services within one month as of receipt of the relevant notice. </inglise>
<eesti>Selle t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel v&otilde;ib investeerimis&uuml;hing alustada piiri&uuml;leste investeerimisteenuste osutamist, arvestades seejuures vastavas lepinguriigis kehtestatud ja investeerimis&uuml;hingule teatavaks tehtud n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>After the expiry of this term, the investment firm may start providing cross-border investment services, taking into account the requirements established in the relevant Contracting State and made known to the investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Piiri&uuml;leseid investeerimisteenuseid osutav investeerimis&uuml;hing peab k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud &auml;riplaanis kavandatavatest muudatustest aegsasti kirjalikult teavitama inspektsiooni ja vastava liikmesriigi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An investment firm providing cross-border investment services shall notify the Supervision Authority and the securities market supervisory agency of the relevant Contracting State in writing and well in advance of any changes intended to be made in the business plan specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>3. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 3 </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lisriigi investeerimis&uuml;hingu tegevus Eestis </eesti>
<inglise>Activities of Foreign Investment Firms in Estonia </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 66. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 66. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa taotlemine v&auml;lisriigi investeerimis&uuml;hingu filiaali asutamiseks Eestis </eesti>
<inglise>Application for permission to found branch of foreign investment firm in Estonia </inglise>
<eesti>(1) V&auml;lisriigis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hing peab Eestis filiaali asutamiseks taotlema inspektsioonilt sellekohase loa (edaspidi k&auml;esolevas jaos luba). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to found a branch in Estonia, an investment firm registered in a foreign state shall apply for the relevant permission (hereinafter in this Division permission) from the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolevas jaos s&auml;testatut ei kohaldata investeerimisteenuseid osutava v&auml;lisriigi krediidiasutuse filiaali asutamisele Eestis. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The provisions of this Division shall not apply to the founding of a branch of a foreign credit institution in Estonia which is providing investment services. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Loa taotlemisel esitatakse inspektsioonile kirjalik avaldus ning j&auml;rgmised andmed ja dokumendid: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon application for permission, a written application and the following information and documents shall be submitted to the Supervision Authority: </inglise>
<eesti>1) filiaali nimetus ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name and address of the branch: </inglise>
<eesti>2) filiaali juhataja andmed vastavalt &auml;riseadustiku (RT I 1995, 26-28, 355; 1998, 91-93, 1500; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 24, 360; 57, 596; 102, 907; 2000, 29, 172; 49, 303; 55, 365; 57, 373; 2001, 34, 185; 56, 332 ja 336) &sect; 387 punktides 10 ja 11 s&auml;testatule; </eesti>
<inglise>2) information on the director of the branch in accordance with the provisions of clauses 387 10) and 11) of the Commercial Code (RT I 1995, 26-28, 355; 1998, 91-93, 1500; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 24, 360; 57, 596; 102, 907; 2000, 29, 172; 49, 303; 55, 365; 57, 373; 2001, 34, 185; 56, 332 and 336); </inglise>
<eesti>3) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 73 l&otilde;ikes 2 n&otilde;utud andmed investeerimis&uuml;hingus olulist osalust omavate isikute kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the information required in subsection 73 (2) of this Act on persons having a qualifying holding in the investment firm; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &auml;riseadustiku &sect; 386 l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 1, 3, 4 ja 5 s&auml;testatud andmed ja dokumendid; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the information and documents provided for in clauses 386 (2) 1), 3), 4) and 5) of the Commercial Code; </inglise>
<eesti>5) taotleja kahe viimase majandusaasta aruanded; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the annual reports of the applicant for the past two financial years; </inglise>
<eesti>6) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 54 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 12 nimetatud filiaali &auml;riplaan, millele lisatakse suhete kirjeldus asutava investeerimis&uuml;hinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the business plan of the branch as referred to in clause 54 (1) 12) of this Act, together with a description of its relationship with the founding investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Lisaks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud andmetele tuleb v&auml;lisriigi investeerimis&uuml;hingul inspektsioonile esitada oma asukohamaa v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutuse: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In addition to the information specified in subsection (3) of this section, a foreign investment firm shall submit the following to the Supervision Authority from the securities market supervisory agency of its home country: </inglise>
<eesti>1) n&otilde;usolek filiaali asutamiseks Eestis; </eesti>
<inglise>1) permission to open a branch in Estonia; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kinnitus selle kohta, et tal on asukohamaal kehtiv tegevusluba ning tema tegevus on korrektne ja koosk&otilde;las heade tavadega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) confirmation to the effect that the investment holds a valid activity licence in its home country and that it pursues its activities in a correct manner and in accordance with good business practices; </inglise>
<eesti>3) andmed taotleja finantsseisundi, sealhulgas omavahendite suuruse, kapitali adekvaatsuse, maksej&otilde;ulisuse ning asukohamaa investori kaitse skeemi kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>3) information on the financial situation of the applicant, including the size of its own funds, capital adequacy and solvency, and on the investor protection scheme in its home country. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis nimetatud v&otilde;&otilde;rkeelsed andmed ja dokumendid tuleb v&auml;lisriigi investeerimis&uuml;hingul legaliseerida konsulaarseaduses (RT I 1998, 113/114, 1874; 2001, 23, 126) s&auml;testatud korras ning esitada koos allkirjastatud eestikeelse t&otilde;lkega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The foreign language information and documents specified in this section shall be legalised by a foreign investment firm pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Consular Act (RT I 1998, 113/114, 1874; 2001, 23, 126) and submitted together with a signed translation into Estonian. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 67. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 67. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa taotluse menetlemine ja loa kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Processing of application for permission and revocation of permission </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Loa taotlemisele, taotluse l&auml;bivaatamisele, loa andmisele ning kehtetuks tunnistamisele kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 51-53, &sect; 55 l&otilde;igetes 1-5, &sect;-des 56 ja 58 tegevusloa ning taotluse kohta s&auml;testatut, kui k&auml;esolevast jaost ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Unless otherwise provided in this Division, applications for permission and the review, grant and revocation thereof shall be subject to the provisions of &sect;&sect; 51-53, subsections 55 (1) -(5), &sect; 56 and &sect; 58 of this Act regulating the activity licences and applications therefor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Lisaks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 56 s&auml;testatud alustele v&otilde;ib inspektsioon keelduda loa andmisest, kui taotleja asukohamaa &otilde;igusaktid v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutus ei taga piisavat j&auml;relevalvet taotleja &uuml;le v&otilde;i kui ei ole s&otilde;lmitud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 60 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud lepingut v&otilde;i kokkulepet ja inspektsiooni koost&ouml;&ouml; asukohamaa v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutusega ei ole piisav. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In addition to the reasons provided for in &sect; 56 of this Act, the Supervision Authority may refuse to grant permission if the legislation or the securities market supervisory agency of the home country of the applicant do not guarantee adequate supervision of the applicant or if no agreement specified in subsection 60 (2) of this Act has been entered into and co-operation between the Supervision Authority and the securities market supervisory agency of such country is insufficient. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Eestis filiaali omav v&auml;lisriigis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hing on kohustatud inspektsiooni ja vastava riigi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutust teavitama k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 66 l&otilde;ike 3 punktides 1, 2 ja 6 loetletud andmete muutmise kavatsusest v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kuu ette. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An investment firm which is registered in a foreign state and which has a branch in Estonia is required to notify the Supervision Authority and the securities market supervisory agency of the relevant state of its intention to change the information listed in clauses 66 (3) 1), 2), and 6) of this Act at least one month in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib tunnistada loa kehtetuks, kui ilmnevad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 58 v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud asjaolud. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Supervision Authority may revoke permission if circumstances provided for in &sect; 58 of this Act or in subsection (2) of this section become evident. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 68. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 68. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lisriigi investeerimis&uuml;hingu esindus </eesti>
<inglise>Representative office of foreign investment firm </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui v&auml;lisriigis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hing kavatseb avada Eestis oma esinduse, peab ta esitama inspektsioonile sellekohase teabe koos j&auml;rgmiste andmete ja dokumentidega: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the event that an investment firm registered in a foreign state intends to open a representative office in Estonia, it shall submit a relevant notice to the Supervision Authority together with the following information and documents: </inglise>
<eesti>1) asukohamaa v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutuse kinnitus selle kohta, et investeerimis&uuml;hingul on kehtiv tegevusluba; </eesti>
<inglise>1) confirmation from the securities market supervisory agency of its home country to the effect that the investment firm holds a valid activity licence; </inglise>
<eesti>2) esinduse tegevuskava; </eesti>
<inglise>2) an action plan for the representative office; </inglise>
<eesti>3) esindaja volitusi t&otilde;endav volikiri; </eesti>
<inglise>3) an authorisation document certifying the authorisation of the representative; </inglise>
<eesti>4) dokument investeerimis&uuml;hingu registreerimise kohta tema asukohamaal (&auml;riregistri v&auml;ljav&otilde;te v&otilde;i registreerimistunnistuse &auml;rakiri); </eesti>
<inglise>4) a document concerning the registration of the investment firm in its home country (an extract from the commercial register or a copy of the certificate of registration); </inglise>
<eesti>5) investeerimis&uuml;hingu p&otilde;hikiri; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the articles of association of the investment firm; </inglise>
<eesti>6) esinduse asukoht, aadress ja sidevahendite numbrid. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the seat, address and telecommunications numbers of the representative office. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud dokumendid tuleb inspektsioonile esitada koos t&otilde;estatud eestikeelse t&otilde;lkega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The documents specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be submitted to the Supervision Authority together with a notarised translation into Estonian. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 69. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 69. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepinguriigi filiaal Eestis </eesti>
<inglise>Branch of Contracting State in Estonia </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Lepinguriigis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hingu filiaali asutamisele Eestis ei kohaldata k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 66 l&otilde;igetes 1, 3, 4 ja 5 ning &sect; 67 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 v&auml;lisriigi investeerimis&uuml;hingu filiaali asutamise kohta s&auml;testatut, kui k&auml;esolevast paragrahvist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Unless otherwise prescribed in this section, the provisions of subsections 66 (1), (3), (4) and (5) and subsections 67 (1) and (2) of this Act regulating the foundation of a branch of a foreign investment firm shall not apply with regard to the founding in Estonia of a branch of an investment firm registered in a Contracting State. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Lepinguriigis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hing peab Eestis filiaali asutamise kavatsusest oma asukohariigi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutuse kaudu inspektsiooni teavitama. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An investment firm registered in a Contracting State shall notify the Supervision Authority of its intention to open a branch in Estonia through the securities market supervisory agency of its home country. </inglise>
<eesti>Teabele peavad olema lisatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 66 l&otilde;ike 3 punktides 1, 2 ja 6 ning l&otilde;ikes 4 nimetatud andmed. </eesti>
<inglise>The information specified in clauses 66 (3) 1), 2) and 6) and subsection 65 (4) of this Act shall be annexed to the notice. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kahe kuu jooksul p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud teabe saamist teavitab inspektsioon lepinguriigis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hingut Eestis investeerimisteenuste osutamisel rakendatavatest tegevusn&otilde;uetest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Within two months after receipt of the information specified in subsection (2) of this section, the Supervision Authority shall notify the investment firm registered in a Contracting State of the operating requirements applicable in Estonia to the provision of investment services. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Investeerimis&uuml;hing v&otilde;ib asutada filiaali ja alustada tegevust p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud teabe saamist inspektsioonilt v&otilde;i p&auml;rast kahe kuu m&ouml;&ouml;dumist k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud teabe laekumisest inspektsioonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An investment firm may open a branch and commence operations after receipt of the information specified in subsection (3) of this section from the Supervision Authority or after two months have passed since receipt of the information specified in subsection (2) of this section by the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Filiaali &auml;riregistrisse kandmisel esitatakse inspektsiooni kinnitus k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud andmete saamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Confirmation from the Supervision Authority concerning receipt of the information specified in subsection (2) of this section shall be submitted upon the entry of a branch in the commercial register. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 70. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 70. </inglise>
<eesti>Piiri&uuml;leste investeerimisteenuste osutamine Eestis </eesti>
<inglise>Provision of cross-border investment services in Estonia </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Piiri&uuml;lene investeerimisteenus k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi t&auml;henduses on investeerimisteenus, mida osutab isik, kes ise v&otilde;i kelle filiaal ei ole registreeritud Eestis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this section, cross-border investment services are investment services provided by a person who is not or whose branch is not registered in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Lepinguriigis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hing v&otilde;ib alustada piiri&uuml;leste investeerimisteenuste osutamist Eestis p&auml;rast inspektsioonile k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 65 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud andmeid sisaldava teabe edastamist vastava lepinguriigi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutuse poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An investment firm registered in a Contracting State may start providing cross-border investment services in Estonia after the securities market supervisory agency of the relevant Contracting State has forwarded the information specified in subsection 65 (2) of this Act to the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lepinguriigis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hing peab Eestis piiri&uuml;leste investeerimisteenuste osutamisel j&auml;rgima k&auml;esoleva seadusega ja selle alusel investeerimisteenuste osutamisele kehtestatud n&otilde;udeid, millest inspektsioon teavitab vastavat investeerimis&uuml;hingut p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud teabe saamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An investment firm registered in a Contracting State and providing cross-border investment services in Estonia shall observe the requirements for the provision of investment services prescribed in and on the basis of this Act, of which it shall be informed by the Supervision Authority after receipt of the information specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Piiri&uuml;leseid investeerimisteenuseid osutav investeerimis&uuml;hing peab k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud teabes sisalduvas &auml;riplaanis kavandatavatest muudatustest aegsasti kirjalikult teavitama inspektsiooni ja vastava lepinguriigi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An investment firm providing cross-border investment services shall notify the Supervision Authority and the securities market supervisory agency of the relevant Contracting State in writing and well in advance of any changes intended to be made to the business plan specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) V&auml;lisriigis tegutseva v&auml;&auml;rtpaberib&ouml;rsi liige v&otilde;ib inspektsiooni loal (edaspidi k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis piiri&uuml;leste teenuste osutamise luba) osutada piiri&uuml;leseid investeerimisteenuseid Eestis elavatele v&otilde;i asuvatele isikutele Eestis asuva v&auml;&auml;rtpaberib&ouml;rsi vahendusel ilma, et tema suhtes kohaldataks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2-4 s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) With the permission of the Supervision Authority (hereinafter in this section permission to provide cross-border services), a member of a stock exchange operating in a foreign state may provide cross-border investment services to persons residing or located in Estonia through the intermediation of a stock exchange located in Estonia without coming within the scope of the provisions subsections (2) -(4) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Piiri&uuml;leste teenuste osutamise loa taotlemiseks tuleb esitada inspektsioonile vastav taotlus. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A relevant application shall be submitted to the Supervision Authority for permission to provide cross-border services. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotluse vormi koos taotluses n&auml;idatavate andmete loeteluga kehtestab rahandusminister oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The format for applications and the list of information to be set out therein shall be established by a regulation the of the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>Piiri&uuml;leste teenuste osutamise loa taotlemisele ja taotluse l&auml;bivaatamisele kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 51 ja 52 s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>The provisions of &sect;&sect; 51 and 52 of this Act shall apply to applications for permission to provide cross-border services and to the review thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda otsuse tegemiseks vajalike andmete ja dokumentide esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>The Supervision Authority has the right to demand that information and documents necessary for making the decision be submitted. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Piiri&uuml;leste teenuste osutamise loa andmise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise kohta teeb inspektsioon otsuse &uuml;he kuu jooksul k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 6 nimetatud taotluse, andmete ja dokumentide esitamisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The Supervision Authority shall make a decision regarding the grant of or refusal to grant permission to provide cross-border services within one month as of submission of the application, information and documents specified in subsection (6) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>Inspektsioon keeldub piiri&uuml;leste teenuste osutamise loa andmisest v&otilde;i tunnistab antud loa kehtetuks, kui j&auml;relevalve teostamine taotleja &uuml;le vajalikul tasemel on takistatud v&otilde;i kliendi huvid piiri&uuml;lese teenuse osutamisel ei ole piisavalt kaitstud. </eesti>
<inglise>The Supervision Authority shall refuse to grant permission to provide cross-border services or revoke permission already granted if adequate supervision of the applicant is not possible or if the interests of the client are not sufficiently protected upon the provision of cross-border services. </inglise>
<eesti>9. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 9 </inglise>
<eesti>Aktsiad, aktsion&auml;rid, juhtimine </eesti>
<inglise>Shares, Shareholders, Management </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 71. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 71. </inglise>
<eesti>Aktsiad </eesti>
<inglise>Shares </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu aktsiad on vabalt v&otilde;&otilde;randatavad. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The shares of an investment firm are freely transferable. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu aktsiate v&otilde;&otilde;randamisel ei kohaldata &auml;riseadustiku &sect; 229 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud aktsion&auml;ri ostuees&otilde;igust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The pre-emptive right of a shareholder provided for in subsection 229 (2) of the Commercial Code does not apply upon the transfer of the shares of an investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 72. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 72. </inglise>
<eesti>Olulist osalust omavatele isikutele esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for persons having qualifying holding </inglise>
<eesti>Investeerimis&uuml;hingus v&otilde;ivad olulist osalust omada isikud, kes on v&otilde;imelised tagama investeerimis&uuml;hingu kindla ja usaldusv&auml;&auml;rse juhtimise ning kelle omanike struktuur ja &auml;risidemed on l&auml;bipaistvad ega takista t&otilde;husa j&auml;relevalve teostamist. </eesti>
<inglise>Qualifying holdings in an investment firm may be held by persons who are able to ensure the sound and prudent management of the investment firm and whose business connections and structure of owners are transparent and do not prevent supervision from being exercised efficiently. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 73. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 73. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa taotlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Application for permission </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui isik kavatseb omandada olulist osalust investeerimis&uuml;hingus v&otilde;i suurendada seda &uuml;le 20, 33 v&otilde;i 50 protsendi investeerimis&uuml;hingu aktsiakapitalist v&otilde;i aktsiatega esindatud h&auml;&auml;lte arvust v&otilde;i kui investeerimis&uuml;hing muutuks tehingu tulemusena tema t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjaks, on ta kohustatud eelnevalt taotlema inspektsioonilt vastava loa (edaspidi k&auml;esolevas peat&uuml;kis luba). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a person intends to acquire a qualifying holding in an investment firm or to increase a qualifying holding so that the proportion of the share capital or votes represented by shares in the investment firm held by the person would exceed 20, 33 or 50 per cent or so that the investment firm would become a subsidiary of the person as a result of the transaction, the person is required to apply to the Supervision Authority beforehand for permission (hereinafter in this Chapter permission). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Loa saamiseks tuleb inspektsioonile esitada taotlus, milles n&auml;idatakse omatava ja omandatava osaluse suurus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to obtain permission, an application shall be submitted to the Supervision Authority which sets out the size of the current holding and of that to be acquired. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotlusele lisatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>The following shall be appended to the application: </inglise>
<eesti>1) juriidilisest isikust omandaja nimi, registrikood ja asukoht, &auml;ri&uuml;hingu puhul samuti k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 54 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 2 ja 3 nimetatud dokumendid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name, registry code and location of the applicant if the applicant is a legal person, and also the documents specified in clauses 54 (1) 2) and 3) of this Act if the applicant is a company; </inglise>
<eesti>2) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 54 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 6 nimetatud andmed omandajaks oleva &auml;ri&uuml;hingu n&otilde;ukogu ja juhatuse liikmete kohta ning loa taotleja kinnitus nimetatud isikute usaldusv&auml;&auml;rsuse ja laitmatu reputatsiooni kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>2) information specified in clause 54 (1) 6) of this Act regarding the members of the management board and supervisory board of the acquiring company as well as confirmation from the applicant regarding the reliability and impeccable reputation of such persons; </inglise>
<eesti>3) omandajaks oleva &auml;ri&uuml;hingu viimase kahe majandusaasta aruanne ja auditeeritud vahearuanne esimese poolaasta kohta, kui viimase majandusaasta l&otilde;ppemisest on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud rohkem kui &uuml;heksa kuud. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the annual reports of the acquiring company for the past two financial years and an audited interim report for the first six months if more than nine months have passed since the end of the previous financial year. </inglise>
<eesti>Aruannetele tuleb lisada audiitori j&auml;reldusotsus; </eesti>
<inglise>The auditor's report shall be added to the reports; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kontserni koosseisu kuuluva &auml;ri&uuml;hingu poolt osaluse omandamise korral kontserni struktuuri kirjeldus koos sinna kuuluvate &auml;ri&uuml;hingute osaluse n&auml;itamisega ning kontserni viimase kahe majandusaasta aruanded ja audiitori j&auml;reldusotsused; </eesti>
<inglise>4) if the qualifying holding is being acquired by a company which is a member of a group, a description of the group structure, stating the shares of the holdings of the companies belonging to the group, and the annual reports and auditor's reports of the group for the past two financial years; </inglise>
<eesti>5) omandajaks oleva f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku puhul k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktis 2 nimetatud andmed ning andmed raha p&auml;ritolu kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>5) if the qualifying holding is being acquired by a natural person, information specified in clause 2) of this subsection and information concerning the origin of the money; </inglise>
<eesti>6) t&otilde;end riigil&otilde;ivu tasumise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>6) proof of payment of the state fee. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui olulist osalust soovib omandada v&auml;lisriigi investeerimis&uuml;hing, krediidiasutus, kindlustusselts v&otilde;i investeerimisfond, tuleb lisaks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud andmetele esitada inspektsioonile v&auml;lisriigi vastava j&auml;relevalveasutuse t&otilde;end selle kohta, et nimetatud v&auml;lisriigi &uuml;hing omab kehtivat tegevusluba ja t&auml;idab kehtivaid n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a foreign investment firm, credit institution, insurance company or investment fund wishes to acquire a qualifying holding, confirmation from the relevant foreign supervisory authority to the effect that the foreign firm holds a valid activity licence and observes the established requirements shall also be submitted to the Supervision Authority in addition to the documents specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 74. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 74. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa taotluse menetlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Processing of application for permission </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 73 l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 nimetatud andmete ja dokumentide p&otilde;hjal ei ole v&otilde;imalik veenduda, kas loa taotleja vastab k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele, v&otilde;ib inspektsioon n&otilde;uda t&auml;iendavate andmete ja dokumentide esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Supervision Authority may demand the submission of additional information and documents if it is not convinced on the basis of the information and documents specified in subsections 73 (2) and (3) of this Act as to whether the applicant for permission meets the requirements prescribed in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Taotleja poolt esitatud andmete kontrollimiseks v&otilde;ib inspektsioon n&otilde;uda t&auml;psustavate andmete ja dokumentide esitamist ning teostada kohapealset kontrolli. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to verify the information submitted by the applicant, the Supervision Authority may demand the submission of additional information and documents and may carry out an on-site inspection. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui taotlejaks on lepinguriigis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hing, krediidiasutus, kindlustusselts v&otilde;i investeerimisfond, k&uuml;sib inspektsioon enne otsustamist lepinguriigi vastava j&auml;relevalveasutuse seisukohta loa andmise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the applicant is an investment firm, credit institution, insurance company or investment fund registered in a Contracting State, the Supervision Authority shall seek the opinion of the relevant supervisory agency of the Contracting State regarding the grant of permission prior to making a decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Otsuse loa andmise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise kohta teeb inspektsioon kolme kuu jooksul, arvates loa taotluse esitamisest, kuid mitte hiljem kui &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates k&otilde;igi n&otilde;utud andmete ja dokumentide esitamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Supervision Authority shall make a decision regarding the grant of or refusal to grant permission within three months after submission of the relevant application, but not later than within one month after submission of all the necessary documents and information. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus saadetakse viivitamata taotlejale tema taotluses m&auml;rgitud asukohta. </eesti>
<inglise>The decision shall be sent immediately to the applicant at the address stated in the application. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Loa andmisel v&otilde;ib inspektsioon m&auml;&auml;rata olulise osaluse omandamiseks v&otilde;i osaluse suurendamiseks m&otilde;istliku t&auml;htaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) When granting permission, the Supervision Authority may establish a reasonable term during which the qualifying holding is to be acquired or the holding is to be increased. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa andmisest keeldumisel peab otsus sisaldama p&otilde;hjendust. </eesti>
<inglise>Any decision to refuse to grant permission shall contain the justification therefor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 75. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 75. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa andmisest keeldumine </eesti>
<inglise>Refusal to grant permission </inglise>
<eesti>Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib keelduda loa andmisest investeerimis&uuml;hingus olulise osaluse omandamiseks v&otilde;i suurendamiseks, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>The Supervision Authority may refuse to grant permission to acquire or increase a qualifying holding in an investment firm, if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) osaluse omandamine v&otilde;i suurendamine v&otilde;ib oluliselt piirata konkurentsi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiturul; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the acquisition or increase of the holding could significantly restrict competition on the securities market; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ilmneb, et osaluse omandaja ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 72 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) it becomes clear that the person acquiring the holding does not meet the requirements of &sect; 72 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) osaluse omandamine v&otilde;i suurendamine v&otilde;ib oluliselt kahjustada investorite huve v&otilde;i investeerimis&uuml;hingu vastavust k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the acquisition or increase of the holding could significantly damage the interests of investors or the compliance of the investment firm with the requirements prescribed by this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) taotleja raamatupidamise aruanded ei v&otilde;imalda &otilde;igesti hinnata taotleja finantsseisundit; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the applicant's accounting reports do not enable the financial situation of the applicant to be adequately evaluated; </inglise>
<eesti>5) taotleja, kes taotleb &uuml;le 50 protsendi investeerimis&uuml;hingu aktsiakapitalist v&otilde;i aktsiatega esindatud h&auml;&auml;lte arvust, finantsseisund ei ole piisav, tagamaks investeerimis&uuml;hingu usaldusv&auml;&auml;rset ja korrap&auml;rast tegevust; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the applicant is seeking to acquire more than 50% of the share capital or votes represented by shares of the investment firm and the financial situation of the applicant is not sufficient to ensure the reliable and regular operation of the investment firm; </inglise>
<eesti>6) taotleja ei ole esitanud t&auml;htaegselt v&otilde;i on keeldunud esitamast inspektsioonile k&auml;esoleva seadusega etten&auml;htud v&otilde;i inspektsiooni poolt n&otilde;utud andmeid, dokumente v&otilde;i teavet. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the applicant fails to submit on time or refuses to submit the information or documents prescribed by this Act or requested by the Supervision Authority to the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 76. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 76. </inglise>
<eesti>Loata olulise osaluse omandamise tagaj&auml;rjed </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of acquiring qualifying holding without permission </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Olulise osaluse omandamise v&otilde;i suurendamise tehing, mis on tehtud ilma inspektsiooni loata, on t&uuml;hine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A transaction by which a qualifying holding is acquired or increased and which is conducted without the permission of the Supervision Authority is null and void. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellisel juhul ei omanda tehingu teinud isik aktsiatega kaasnevat h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;igust ning aktsiatega esindatud h&auml;&auml;li ei arvata &uuml;ldkoosoleku kvoorumisse. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the person who conducted the transaction shall not acquire the voting rights accompanying the acquired shares and the votes thus acquired shall not be taken into account when determining the quorum of the general meeting. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui ilma inspektsiooni loata tehtud tehinguga omandatud v&otilde;i suurendatud olulist osalust esindavad h&auml;&auml;led arvati &uuml;ldkoosoleku kvoorumisse ja need m&otilde;jutasid &uuml;ldkoosoleku otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmist, v&otilde;ib kohus inspektsiooni v&otilde;i teise aktsion&auml;ri v&otilde;i &auml;ri&uuml;hingu n&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;i juhatuse liikme avalduse alusel tunnistada &uuml;ldkoosoleku otsuse kehtetuks, kui avaldus on esitatud kolme kuu jooksul &uuml;ldkoosoleku otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If voting rights representing a qualifying holding acquired or increased by a transaction conducted without the permission of the Supervision Authority are included in the quorum of the general meeting and influence the adoption of a resolution of the general meeting, a court may declare the resolution of the general meeting invalid on the basis of a petition of the Supervision Authority, another shareholder or a member of the management board or supervisory board of the company, if the petition is submitted within three months as of the adoption of the adoption of the resolution of the general meeting. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 77. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 77. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of permission </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib olulise osaluse omandamise loa kehtetuks tunnistada, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Supervision Authority may revoke permission to acquire a qualifying holding if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) taotleja on loa taotlemisel esitanud eksitavaid, tegelikkusele mittevastavaid andmeid v&otilde;i dokumente; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the applicant has submitted misleading or inaccurate information or documents upon application for permission; </inglise>
<eesti>2) olulist osalust omava aktsion&auml;ri v&otilde;i tema esindaja tegevus ohustab oluliselt investeerimis&uuml;hingu kindlat ja usaldusv&auml;&auml;rset juhtimist. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the activities of the shareholder who has a qualifying holding or the representative thereof cause a significant risk to the sound and prudent management of the investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Loa kehtetuks tunnistamise korral kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 76 s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The provisions of &sect; 76 of this Act shall apply with respect to the revocation of permission. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 78. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 78. </inglise>
<eesti>Olulisest osalusest teavitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Giving notification of qualifying holding </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui isik kavatseb v&otilde;&otilde;randada aktsiaid ulatuses, millega ta kaotab olulise osaluse investeerimis&uuml;hingus, v&otilde;i v&auml;hendab oma osalust alla k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 73 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ra, peab ta sellest teavitama inspektsiooni 10 p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates vastava tehingu toimumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a person intends to transfer shares in an amount which would result in its losing a qualifying holding in an investment firm or decreases its holding below the rate prescribed in subsection 73 (1) of this Act, the person shall inform the Supervision Authority thereof within ten days as of the relevant transaction being conducted. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hing on olulise osaluse omandamise tehingust teada saamise korral kohustatud sellest viivitamata teavitama inspektsiooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon learning of a transaction to acquire a qualifying holding, an investment firm shall immediately inform the Supervision Authority thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud kohustus kehtib ka k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud tehingute suhtes ning juhul, kui osalust suurendatakse &uuml;le k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 73 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ra. </eesti>
<inglise>This obligation also applies to transactions specified in subsection (1) of this section and if the holding is increased beyond the rate specified in subsection 73 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Investeerimis&uuml;hing on kohustatud koos majandusaasta aruandega esitama inspektsioonile olulist osalust omavate aktsion&auml;ride nimed ja nende osaluse suuruse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An investment firm is required to present the names of shareholders who have a qualifying holding and the size of their holding to the Supervision Authority together with its annual report. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 79. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 79. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtidele esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for managers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhiks v&otilde;ib valida v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;rata &uuml;ksnes isikuid, kellel on investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhtimiseks vajalik haridus, kogemused, kutsealane sobivus ning laitmatu reputatsioon. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Only persons who have the education, experience and professional qualifications necessary to manage an investment firm and who have an impeccable reputation may be elected or appointed managers of investment firms. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhatusel peab olema v&auml;hemalt kaks liiget. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The management board of an investment firm shall have at least two members. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhatuse liikmel peab olema akadeemiline k&otilde;rgharidus v&otilde;i sellega v&otilde;rdsustatud haridus ja investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhtimiseks vajalik t&ouml;&ouml;kogemus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Members of the management board of an investment firm shall have an academic degree or education corresponding thereto, and the experience necessary for managing an investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhiks, samuti investeerimis&uuml;hingu emaettev&otilde;tja juhatuse liikmeks ei v&otilde;i olla isik, kelle tegevus v&otilde;i tegevusetus on kaasa toonud &auml;ri&uuml;hingu pankroti v&otilde;i sundlikvideerimise v&otilde;i &auml;ri&uuml;hingule antud tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamise v&otilde;i kellel on &auml;rikeeld v&otilde;i kelle tegevus on n&auml;idanud, et ta ei ole suuteline korraldama &auml;ri&uuml;hingu juhtimist selliselt, et &auml;ri&uuml;hingu aktsion&auml;ride, osanike, liikmete, v&otilde;lausaldajate ja klientide huvid oleksid piisavalt kaitstud. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person whose prior activities or omissions have led to the bankruptcy or compulsory liquidation of a company or the revocation of an activity licence issued to a company or who is subject to a prohibition on business or whose activities have demonstrated inability to organise the management of a company in a manner which would sufficiently protect the interests of shareholders, members, creditors and clients may not be manager of an investment firm, nor a member of the management board of the parent undertaking of an investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhid ning t&ouml;&ouml;tajad on kohustatud tegutsema nendelt oodatava etten&auml;gelikkuse ja p&auml;devusega ning vastavalt nende ametikohale esitatavatele n&otilde;uetele, l&auml;htudes investeerimis&uuml;hingu ning selle klientide huvidest. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The managers and employees of an investment firm are required to act with the prudence and competence expected of them and according to the requirements for their positions and the interests of the investment firm and its clients. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 80. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 80. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtidest ja audiitorist teavitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Giving notification of officers and auditor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhi valimisel v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;ramisel peab valitav v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;ratav isik investeerimis&uuml;hingule esitama: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the election or appointment of a manager of an investment firm, the person to be elected or appointed shall present the following to the investment firm: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 54 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 6 nimetatud andmed; </eesti>
<inglise>1) information specified in clause 54 (1) 6) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kinnituse, et tal puuduvad k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud asjaolud, mis v&auml;listavad &otilde;iguse olla juht. </eesti>
<inglise>2) confirmation that no circumstances prescribed in this Act which would preclude his or her right to act as manager apply to him or her,. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hing on kohustatud juhtide ning audiitori valimisest v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;ramisest, samuti nende tagasiastumisest v&otilde;i tagasikutsumise algatamisest enne volituste t&auml;htaja l&otilde;ppemist inspektsiooni teavitama ja esitama k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud dokumendid inspektsioonile 10 p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates vastava otsuse tegemisest v&otilde;i avalduse saamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An investment firm is required to inform the Supervision Authority of the election or appointment of managers and an auditor, and of their resignation or the initiation of their removal before the expiry of their term of office, and to submit the documents specified in subsection (1) of this section within ten days as of the relevant decision being made or the relevant application being received. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 81. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 81. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhi tagasikutsumine </eesti>
<inglise>Removal of manager </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsiooni ettekirjutusega v&otilde;ib investeerimis&uuml;hingult n&otilde;uda juhi tagasikutsumist, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Supervision Authority may issue a precept to an investment firm to remove a manager if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) juht ei vasta k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the manager does not meet the requirements provided for in this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) seoses tema valimise v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;ramisega on esitatud eksitavaid, mittet&auml;ielikke v&otilde;i tegelikkusele mittevastavaid andmeid v&otilde;i dokumente; </eesti>
<inglise>2) misleading, incomplete or incorrect information or documents have been submitted in connection with his or her election or appointment; </inglise>
<eesti>3) juhi tegevus investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhtimisel on n&auml;idanud, et ta ei ole suuteline korraldama investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhtimist selliselt, et investorite, teiste klientide ja v&otilde;lausaldajate huvid oleksid piisavalt kaitstud. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the activities of the manager in managing the investment firm have demonstrated his or her inability to organise the management of the investment firm such that the interests of investors, other clients and creditors are sufficiently protected. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui investeerimis&uuml;hing ei ole t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i t&auml;htaegselt t&auml;itnud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud ettekirjutust, on inspektsioonil &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda juhi tagasikutsumist kohtu poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an investment firm fails to comply with a precept specified in subsection (1) of this section in full or within the prescribed term, the Supervision Authority has the right to demand the removal of the manager by a court. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 82. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 82. </inglise>
<eesti>Sise-eeskirjad </eesti>
<inglise>Policies and procedures </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingus peavad olema kehtestatud juhtide ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate tegevust reguleerivad sise-eeskirjad v&otilde;i protseduurireeglid (edaspidi sise-eeskirjad), mis peavad kindlustama investeerimis&uuml;hingu tegevust reguleerivate &otilde;igusaktide ja investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhtimisorganite otsuste t&auml;itmise. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An investment firm shall establish policies and procedures or rules of procedure regulating the activities of managers and employees (hereinafter policies and procedures), the aim of which is to ensure that legislation regulating the activities of the investment firm is complied with and that decisions taken by the directing bodies thereof are duly observed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Sise-eeskirjadega m&auml;&auml;ratakse muu hulgas kindlaks: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The policies and procedure shall include: </inglise>
<eesti>1) investeerimis&uuml;hingu huvide ja juhtide ning t&ouml;&ouml;tajate isiklike majanduslike huvide konfliktide v&auml;ltimise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the procedure for prevention of conflicts between the interests of the investment firm and the personal economic interests of the managers and employees; </inglise>
<eesti>2) investeerimis&uuml;hingusisese teabe ja dokumentide liikumise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the procedure for the communication of information and movement of documents within the investment firm; </inglise>
<eesti>3) investeerimisteenuste ja investeerimisk&otilde;rvalteenuste osutamise kord, sealhulgas ajaliselt m&auml;&auml;ratletud ja m&auml;&auml;ratlemata piirangud tehingute tegemisel; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the procedure for the provision of investment services and non-core services, including restrictions valid for a definite or indefinite period of time on the conduct of transactions; </inglise>
<eesti>4) alluvussuhted, aruandluse esitamise protseduur ja &otilde;iguste delegeerimine, s&auml;testades funktsioonide lahususe investeerimis&uuml;hingu nimel kohustuste v&otilde;tmisel, teenuste kajastamisel raamatupidamises ja aruandluses ning riskide hindamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>4) relationships of subordination, the procedure for reporting and the delegation rights, and shall provide the separation of functions upon assumption of obligations in the name of the investment firm, the recording of services for accounting and reporting purposes and the assessment of risks. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Rahandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega v&otilde;ib kehtestada t&auml;psemad n&otilde;uded sise-eeskirjade koostamise ning sisu kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Minister of Finance may specify the requirements for the preparation of policies and procedures and for the contents thereof by a regulation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 83. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 83. </inglise>
<eesti>Sisekontroll </eesti>
<inglise>Internal control </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingus peab toimima piisav sisekontrolli s&uuml;steem, mis h&otilde;lmab investeerimis&uuml;hingu k&otilde;iki juhtimis- ja tegevustasandeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An investment firm shall have in place an adequate internal control system which covers all management and operations levels of the investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingus tuleb moodustada s&otilde;ltumatu siseauditi all&uuml;ksus, m&auml;&auml;rata s&otilde;ltumatu t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i s&otilde;lmida leping siseaudiitori funktsioonide t&auml;itmiseks audiitoriga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An investment firm shall establish an independent internal audit unit, appoint an independent employee or enter into an agreement with an auditor for performance of the functions of internal auditor. </inglise>
<eesti>Sisekontrolli teostavad isikud (edaspidi siseaudiitor) peavad vastama k&auml;esolevas seaduses juhtidele s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>Persons conducting internal control (hereinafter internal auditors) shall meet the requirements for managers established in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Siseaudiitor ei tohi olla s&otilde;ltuv investeerimis&uuml;hingu teistest t&ouml;&ouml;tajatest v&otilde;i all&uuml;ksustest, kes t&auml;idavad tema poolt kontrollitavaid funktsioone, ega seotud nendega. </eesti>
<inglise>An internal auditor may not be dependent upon or associated with other employees or structural units of the investment firm which perform the functions monitored by the internal auditor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Siseaudiitor peab kontrollima investeerimis&uuml;hingu tegevuse vastavust &otilde;igusaktidele, inspektsiooni ettekirjutustele, reguleeritud turu reglemendile, headele tavadele ning investeerimis&uuml;hingu sise-eeskirjadele ja juhtimisorganite otsustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An internal auditor shall monitor the compliance of the activities of the investment firm with legislation, precepts issued by the Supervision Authority, the rules and regulations of the regulated market, good practices, and the policies and procedures of the investment firm and decisions taken by the directing bodies of the investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhatus tagab siseaudiitorile k&otilde;ik tema &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks vajalikud &otilde;igused ja t&ouml;&ouml;tingimused, sealhulgas &otilde;iguse saada selgitusi ja teavet investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhtidelt ning j&auml;lgida avastatud puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamist ja tehtud ettepanekute t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The management board of an investment firm shall ensure that the internal auditor has the rights and working conditions necessary to perform his or her duties, including the right to obtain explanations and information from the managers of the investment firm and to observe the elimination of any deficiencies discovered and compliance with any precepts issued. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Siseaudiitor on kohustatud talle investeerimis&uuml;hingu kohta teatavaks saanud teabe, mis osutab &otilde;iguserikkumisele v&otilde;i klientide huvide kahjustamisele, viivitamata kirjalikult edastama investeerimis&uuml;hingu n&otilde;ukogule ja juhatusele, vastavale reguleeritud turu korraldajale ning inspektsioonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The internal auditor is required to communicate in writing any information which becomes known to him or her and which points to a violation of law or to damage to the interests of clients to the supervisory board and management board of the investment firm, the relevant operator of the regulated market and the Supervision Authority immediately. </inglise>
<eesti>10. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 10 </inglise>
<eesti>Investeerimis&uuml;hingu tegevusele esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for Activities of Investment Firms </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 84. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 84. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva peat&uuml;ki kohaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of this Chapter </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas peat&uuml;kis investeerimis&uuml;hingule kehtestatud n&otilde;udeid kohaldatakse ka v&auml;lisriigi isikutele, kes osutavad investeerimisteenuseid isikutele, kelle elu- v&otilde;i asukoht on Eestis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The requirements for investment firms established in this Chapter also apply to foreign persons who provide investment services to persons whose residence or location is in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolevas peat&uuml;kis investeerimis&uuml;hingule kehtestatud n&otilde;udeid ei kohaldata k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud v&auml;lisriigi isikutele, kes osutavad investeerimisteenuseid &uuml;ksnes v&auml;lisriigis ja kelle investeerimisteenuseid ei pakuta isikutele Eestis. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The requirements for investment firms established in this Chapter do not apply to foreign persons specified in subsection (1) of this section who provide investment services solely in a foreign state and whose investment services are not offered to persons in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Investeerimisteenused loetakse pakutuks isikutele Eestis, kui neid teenuseid reklaamitakse Eestis v&otilde;i kui nende pakkumise viisist v&otilde;i sisust, sealhulgas pakkumise keelest v&otilde;ib j&auml;reldada, et see on suunatud isikutele, kelle elu- v&otilde;i asukoht on Eestis. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Investment services are deemed as being offered to persons in Estonia if the services are advertised in Estonia or if the manner of the offer or the contents thereof, including the language of the offer, enable the conclusion to be made that the offer is aimed at persons whose residence or location is in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 85. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 85. </inglise>
<eesti>Investeerimis&uuml;hingu kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of investment firms </inglise>
<eesti>Investeerimis&uuml;hing on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>An investment firm is required: </inglise>
<eesti>1) osutama investeerimisteenuseid ja investeerimisk&otilde;rvalteenuseid piisava asjatundlikkuse, t&auml;psuse ja hoolikusega, l&auml;htudes eelk&otilde;ige oma kliendi parimatest huvidest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to provide investment services and non-core services with due professionalism, precision and care, proceeding primarily from the best interests of the client; </inglise>
<eesti>2) arvestama oma tegevuses v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru usaldusv&auml;&auml;rse ja korrap&auml;rase toimimisega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to take the reliable and regular operation of the securities market into consideration when pursuing its activities; </inglise>
<eesti>3) mitte tegema tehinguid, millest tulenevad investeerimis&uuml;hingu huvid on vastuolus tema kliendi huvidega (huvide konflikt) ning v&auml;ltimatu huvide konflikti puhul tegutsema kliendi huvides; </eesti>
<inglise>3) to refrain from conducting transactions in which the interests of the investment firm are in conflict with those of the client (conflict of interests) and, in the event a conflict of interests cannot be avoided, to act in the interests of the client; </inglise>
<eesti>4) investeerimisteenuste osutamisel taotlema ja hoolitsema selle eest, et investeerimis&uuml;hingu ja tema kliendi v&otilde;i erinevate investeerimis&uuml;hingu klientide vahelised huvide konfliktid oleksid v&auml;lditud v&otilde;i v&otilde;imalikult v&auml;iksed; </eesti>
<inglise>4) when providing investment services, to ensure that conflicts of interests between the investment firm and the client or between different clients of the investment firm are avoided or as small as possible; </inglise>
<eesti>5) t&auml;itma kliendi tehingukorraldused nende saabumise j&auml;rjekorras p&otilde;hjendamatu viivituseta ja kliendile v&otilde;imalikult soodsatel tingimustel, arvestades tehingukorraldusega antud tehingu suurusest ja hinnast tulenevate v&otilde;imalike erisustega. </eesti>
<inglise>5) execute the transaction orders of a client in the order they are received without undue delay and under the best possible conditions for the client, by taking into account the possible special nature of the transaction order deriving from the volume and price of the transaction. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 86. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 86. </inglise>
<eesti>Kliendi teavitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Notifying client </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Igal investeerimis&uuml;hingu kliendil on &otilde;igus tutvuda k&otilde;ikide kohustuslikule avalikustamisele kuuluvate andmetega ja investeerimis&uuml;hing on kohustatud kliendi n&otilde;udmisel need temale esitama. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Each client of an investment firm has the right to access all information subject to mandatory disclosure and the investment firm is required to present such information to the client at the request thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hing on kohustatud kliendi n&otilde;udmisel andma talle teavet: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) At the request of a client, an investment firm is required to provide information to the client: </inglise>
<eesti>1) investeerimis&uuml;hingus olulist osalust omavate aktsion&auml;ride (juriidilise isiku puhul v&auml;hemalt - &auml;rinimi, registrikood selle olemasolul, f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku puhul v&auml;hemalt - ees- ja perekonnanimi, isikukood v&otilde;i selle puudumisel s&uuml;nniaeg) ja nende osaluse suuruse kohta investeerimis&uuml;hingu aktsiakapitalis; </eesti>
<inglise>1) on shareholders having a qualifying holding in the investment firm (with regard to legal persons - at least the business name and the registry code if applicable; with regard to natural persons - at least the given name and surname, and personal identification code or date of birth in the absence of a personal identification code) and the size of their holding in the share capital of the investment firm; </inglise>
<eesti>2) investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhtide kohta (ees- ja perekonnanimi, isikukood v&otilde;i selle puudumisel s&uuml;nniaeg, hariduse kirjeldus, viimase viie aasta t&ouml;&ouml;- ja ametikohtade t&auml;ielik loetelu); </eesti>
<inglise>2) on managers of the investment firm (given name and surname, personal identification code or date of birth in the absence of a personal identification code, educational background, and a complete list of places of employment and positions held during the last five years); </inglise>
<eesti>3) lisaks k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktis 2 s&auml;testatule ka investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhatuse liikmete &uuml;lesannete kohta investeerimis&uuml;hingus. </eesti>
<inglise>3) in addition to the provisions of clause (2) of this subsection, on the duties of the members of the management board of the investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 87. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 87. </inglise>
<eesti>Teavitamine teenuste osutamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Notification upon provision of services </inglise>
<eesti>Teenuste osutamisel on investeerimis&uuml;hing kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the provision of services, an investment firm is required: </inglise>
<eesti>1) n&otilde;udma oma klientidelt teavet nende investeerimisteenuste ja investeerimisk&otilde;rvalteenustega seotud teadmiste v&otilde;i kogemuste ning &auml;ritehingutega seotud eesm&auml;rkide ja asjaolude kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to request information from its clients regarding their knowledge of or experience in investment services and non-core services, and regarding the goals and circumstances of their business transactions; </inglise>
<eesti>2) edastama oma klientidele kogu asjakohase teabe kavatsetavate tehingute ning nendega seotud riskide kohta, arvestades kliendi huvisid ja asjatundlikkust ning kavatsetavate tehingute liiki ja mahtu; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to convey to its clients all relevant information pertaining to transactions which are being contemplated and risks related thereto, taking into account the interests and expertise of the client and the type and volume of the transactions which are being contemplated; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teavitama oma klienti kohaldatavast investori kaitse skeemist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) to notify the client of the investor protection scheme applicable; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teavitama oma klienti olukorrast, kus kliendi tehingukorralduse alusel tehtud tehingu teiseks pooleks on ta ise, kui investeerimis&uuml;hing ja klient ei ole kirjalikult ja selges&otilde;naliselt kokku leppinud teisiti; </eesti>
<inglise>4) to inform the client of any situation where the client is the other party to a transaction conducted on the basis of the client's transaction order, unless the investment firm and the client have expressly agreed otherwise in writing; </inglise>
<eesti>5) andma kliendi n&otilde;udmisel, kuid v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kord kolme kuu jooksul, teavet v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiportfelli valitsemisel kliendi varadega tehtud tehingute, vara v&auml;&auml;rtuse, v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiportfelli koosseisu ja muude teenuse osutamisega seotud asjaolude kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>5) upon the request of the client, to provide the client at least once every three months with information regarding the transactions conducted with the assets of the client when managing the securities portfolio, and regarding the value of the assets, the composition of the securities portfolio and other circumstances related to the provision of services. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 88. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 88. </inglise>
<eesti>Kliendi varade hoidmine ja kaitse </eesti>
<inglise>Maintenance and protection of assets of client </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hing on kohustatud talle usaldatud kliendi vara hoidma lahus enda ja investeerimis&uuml;hingu teiste klientide varast, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui klient ja investeerimis&uuml;hing on kirjalikult ja s&otilde;naselgelt kokku leppinud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An investment firm is required to keep the assets of the client entrusted to it separate from its own assets and those of other clients of the investment firm, unless the investment firm and the client have expressly agreed otherwise in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>Kliendi kirjalikus vormis ning s&otilde;naselgelt v&auml;ljendatud n&otilde;usolek on muu hulgas vajalik kliendi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite hoidmiseks esindajakontol. </eesti>
<inglise>The express written agreement of the client is also necessary to hold the securities of the client in a nominee account. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hing on kohustatud v&otilde;tma tarvitusele piisavad abin&otilde;ud kliendile kuuluva vara ja kliendi &otilde;iguste kaitseks ning tagama kliendi vara hoidmise ja investeerimise vastavalt kokkulepitud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An investment firm is required to take adequate measures to protect assets belonging to the client and the rights of the client and to ensure that the assets of the client are maintained and invested in accordance with the agreed conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Investeerimis&uuml;hing on kohustatud mitte kasutama kliendile kuuluvat vara enda huvides, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An investment firm is required not to use assets belonging to a client in its own interests, unless: </inglise>
<eesti>1) klient on andnud selleks kirjalikus vormis s&otilde;naselge n&otilde;usoleku v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>1) the client has expressly agreed to this in writing, or </inglise>
<eesti>2) raha kasutatakse krediidiasutuste arvel ja nimel krediidiasutuste seaduse &sect; 4 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatu kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the money is being used for the account and in the name of a credit institution in accordance with the provisions of subsections 4 (1) and (2) of the Credit Institutions Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Investeerimis&uuml;hing v&otilde;ib oma nimel kliendi vara pantida &uuml;ksnes kliendi kirjalikus vormis antud s&otilde;naselgel n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An investment firm may pledge assets of a client in its own name only with the express written agreement of the client. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Investeerimis&uuml;hing, kes hoiab klientide vara esindajakontol v&otilde;i &uuml;hingu enda nimel avatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi- v&otilde;i pangakontol, on kohustatud pidama arvestust eraldi iga kliendi vara suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An investment firm which keeps the assets of clients in a nominee account or in a securities account or bank account opened in the name of the investment firm is required to keep separate account of the assets of each client. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt valitsetav klientide vara, sealhulgas investeerimis&uuml;hingu enda nimel hoitav klientide vara, samuti selle arvel omandatud vara, kuulub vastavatele klientidele ning ei kuulu investeerimis&uuml;hingu pankrotivara hulka ning selle arvel ei saa rahuldada investeerimis&uuml;hingu v&otilde;lausaldajate n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Assets of clients managed by an investment firm, including assets of clients maintained in the name of the investment firm as well as assets acquired on account of such assets, belong to the respective clients and shall not be included in the bankruptcy estate of the investment firm, nor shall the claims of the creditors of the investment firm be satisfied on account of such assets. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89. </inglise>
<eesti>Keelatud tegevused tehingute tegemisel </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibited activities upon conducting transactions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingul ja temaga seotud &auml;ri&uuml;hingul on keelatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) It is prohibited for an investment firm and a company associated therewith to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) soovitada investeerimis&uuml;hingu kliendile tehingute tegemist v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega, kui need soovitused ei ole koosk&otilde;las kliendi huvidega, millest investeerimis&uuml;hing oli teadlik, v&otilde;i kui tehingu eesm&auml;rgiks on turuga manipuleerimine k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 200 t&auml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise>1) recommend transactions with securities to a client of the investment firm if such recommendations are not in the interests of the client of which the investment firm is aware or if the purpose of the transaction is to manipulate the market in the meaning of &sect; 200 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teha tehinguid oma arvel v&otilde;i kolmanda isiku arvel v&otilde;i kolmanda isiku nimel hinnaga, mis on v&otilde;rdne v&otilde;i parem, kui klientidelt saadud tehingukorralduste hind samale v&auml;&auml;rtpaberile, enne, kui investeerimis&uuml;hing on t&auml;itnud k&otilde;ik sellised klientide korraldused tehingute tegemiseks sama v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiga, samuti on tehingute tegemine oma arvel keelatud, kui investeerimis&uuml;hing on teadlik sellest, et tema klient soovib esitada korralduse sama iseloomuga tehingu tegemiseks v&otilde;i kui see v&otilde;ib muul viisil kliendile kahju p&otilde;hjustada. </eesti>
<inglise>2) conduct transactions for own account or for the account of a third party or in the name of a third party at a price which is equal to or better than the price proposed by clients in transaction orders for the same security before the investment firm has executed all such orders of clients for conducting transactions with the same security, and also to conduct transactions for own account if the investment firm is aware that the client wishes to submit an order to conduct a transaction of a similar nature or if this may harm the client in any other manner. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingul, tema juhtidel ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel ning muudel isikutel, kellele on usaldatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitehingute t&auml;itmine, v&auml;&auml;rtpaberianal&uuml;&uuml;s v&otilde;i investeerimiskonsultatsioonid, on keelatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruga manipuleerimine k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 200 t&auml;henduses, sealhulgas: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) It is prohibited for an investment firm, the managers and employees thereof and other persons who are entrusted with the task of conducting securities transactions, carrying out securities analyses or providing investment consultations to manipulate the market in the meaning of &sect; 200 of this Act, including: </inglise>
<eesti>1) investeerimis&uuml;hingu kliendile v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitehingu tegemine v&otilde;i soovituste andmine tehingu tegemiseks eesm&auml;rgiga luua eksitav mulje v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi hinnast v&otilde;i tehingute tegemise aktiivsusest v&otilde;i eesm&auml;rgiga m&otilde;jutada v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite hindu kindlas suunas; </eesti>
<inglise>1) conducting a securities transaction for a client of the investment firm or providing recommendations for the conduct of a transaction, with the objective of creating a misleading impression of the price of a security or the volume of transactions or of influencing securities prices in a specific direction; </inglise>
<eesti>2) alusetu v&otilde;i eksitava teabe avalikustamine v&otilde;i avalikustamisele kuuluva teabe avalikustamata j&auml;tmine v&otilde;i sellega p&otilde;hjendamatu viivitamine, kui teave ja selle avalikustamine v&otilde;ib oluliselt m&otilde;jutada v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi hinda v&otilde;i tehingute tegemise aktiivsust; </eesti>
<inglise>2) disclosing unfounded or misleading information, failing to disclose information which is subject to disclosure or unfounded delay in the disclosure thereof if such information and the disclosure thereof may have a significant impact on the price of a security or the volume of transactions; </inglise>
<eesti>3) mis tahes tegevus, mis v&otilde;ib luua vale v&otilde;i eksitava mulje v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi n&otilde;udlusest turul, selle hinnast v&otilde;i sellega kaasnevatest &otilde;igustest v&otilde;i mis v&otilde;ib ajendada teist isikut v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiga tehingut tegema v&otilde;i sellest hoiduma v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiga kaasnevaid &otilde;igusi kasutama v&otilde;i nende kasutamisest loobuma. </eesti>
<inglise>3) any activity which may create a wrong or misleading impression of the demand for a security in the market, its price or the accompanying rights or which may induce another person to conduct a transaction with such security or refrain from doing so or induce a person to use the rights accompanying the security or refrain from using such rights. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 90. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 90. </inglise>
<eesti>Registreerimis- ja s&auml;ilitamiskohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Registration and preservation obligation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hing on kohustatud investeerimisteenuse osutamisel registreerima j&auml;rgmised andmed: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An investment firm is required to register the following information when providing investment services: </inglise>
<eesti>1) korralduse andja nimi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name of the person issuing the order; </inglise>
<eesti>2) korraldus koos kliendi juhistega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the order together with the instructions of the client; </inglise>
<eesti>3) andmed korralduse t&auml;itmise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) information regarding execution of the order; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;taja nimi, kes kliendi korralduse vastu v&otilde;ttis; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the name of the employee who received the order of the client; </inglise>
<eesti>5) korralduse andmise ja t&auml;itmise kuup&auml;ev ning kellaaeg. </eesti>
<inglise>5) the date and time of receipt and execution of the order. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahandusminister v&otilde;ib oma m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestada t&auml;psema andmete registreerimise korra ning lisaks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatule t&auml;iendavalt registreerimisele kuuluvate andmete loetelu, kui see on vajalik investeerimis&uuml;hingu kohustuste t&auml;itmise &uuml;le j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks inspektsiooni poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Finance may, by a regulation, establish a more precise procedure for the registration of information and a list of information subject to registration in addition to that prescribed in subsection (1) of this section, if this is necessary for the Supervision Authority to exercise supervision over the performance of the obligations of the investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Registreeritud andmeid tuleb s&auml;ilitada v&auml;hemalt seitse aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Registered information shall be preserved for at least seven years. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 91. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 91. </inglise>
<eesti>Tehingutest teavitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Giving notification of transactions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hing on kohustatud reguleeritud turu korraldajat, kelle poolt korraldataval reguleeritud turul investeerimis&uuml;hing osaleb, teavitama igast tehingust v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega, mis on lubatud sellel reguleeritud turul kauplemisele, kui need tehingud on tehtud seoses investeerimisteenuste osutamisega (edaspidi k&auml;esolevas peat&uuml;kis tehing). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An investment firm is required to notify the operator of the regulated market in which the investment firm participates of each transaction with securities which are admitted for trading on the regulated market, if such transactions are conducted in connection with the provision of investment services (hereinafter in this Chapter transaction). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Igast tehingust tuleb teavitada reguleeritud turu korraldajat hiljemalt tehingu tegemisele j&auml;rgneval t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval teabekandjatel v&otilde;i &uuml;ldkasutatava andmesidev&otilde;rgu kaudu, kui vastava reguleeritud turu reglemendiga ei ole m&auml;&auml;ratud l&uuml;hemat t&auml;htaega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The operator of the regulated market shall be notified of each transaction at the latest on the working day following the transaction and by means of data carriers or the public data communication network, unless a shorter term is set out in the rules and regulations of the relevant regulated market. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teavitamisel tuleb esitada j&auml;rgmised andmed: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The following information shall be presented upon notification: </inglise>
<eesti>1) v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi nimetus ja identifitseerimisnumber; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name and identification number of the security; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tehingu tegemise kuup&auml;ev ja kellaaeg; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the date and time the transaction is conducted; </inglise>
<eesti>3) v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite hind ja kogus; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the price and volume of securities; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tehingus osalevad investeerimis&uuml;hingud, kusjuures eraldi m&auml;rgitakse &auml;ra omandaja ja v&otilde;&otilde;randaja ning klient, kelle arvel tehing tehakse; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the investment firms participating in the transaction, whereupon the acquirer and transferor and the client in whose name the transaction is conducted shall be set out individually; </inglise>
<eesti>5) reguleeritud turu nimetus, kui on tegemist reguleeritud turu tehinguga; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the name of the regulated market in the case of a regulated market transaction; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kood tehingu identifitseerimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>6) a code for identifying the transaction. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Eraldi tuleb &auml;ra m&auml;rkida tehingud, mis investeerimis&uuml;hing on teinud oma arvel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Transactions conducted by an investment firm for own account shall be marked as such. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Rahandusminister v&otilde;ib oma m&auml;&auml;rusega: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Minister of Finance may, by a regulation: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kehtestada t&auml;psustavaid n&otilde;udeid teavitamise sisu, ulatuse ja vormi kohta ning lubatud andmekandjate ja &uuml;lekandmisviiside kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) specify the requirements regarding the content, scope and format of notification, as well as the permitted data carriers and methods of transmission; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kehtestada t&auml;iendavalt teavitamisele kuuluvate andmete loetelu, kui see on vajalik reguleeritud turul j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) establish a list of additional information subject to notification, if this is needed to exercise supervision over the regulated market; </inglise>
<eesti>3) lubada tehingute puhul, mille objektiks on v&otilde;lakirjad v&otilde;i kindlat liiki tuletisv&auml;&auml;rtpaberid, andmete edastamata j&auml;tmist v&otilde;i nende koondatult edastamist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) lift the requirement to communicate information or to communicate aggregate information in the case of transactions the objects of which are bonds or a specific type of derivative instruments; </inglise>
<eesti>4) lubada mitte teavitada tehingutest, mida tehakse lepinguriigi reguleeritud turul, kui selles riigis on teavitamiskohustusele kehtestatud samad n&otilde;uded. </eesti>
<inglise>4) lift the requirement to give notification of transactions conducted in a regulated market of a Contracting State, if that State imposes the same requirements with respect to the notification obligation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 92. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 92. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;uete t&auml;psustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Specification of requirements </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 85, 87, 88 ja 89 s&auml;testatud investeerimis&uuml;hingu tegevusele esitatavate n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise &uuml;le otsustamiseks tavap&auml;raste juhtumite puhul v&otilde;ib rahandusminister oma m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestada t&auml;psemad kriteeriumid. </eesti>
<inglise>More specific criteria for deciding whether the requirements prescribed in &sect;&sect; 85, 87, 88 and 89 of this Act for the operations of investment firms have been met in routine cases may be established by a regulation of the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>11. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 11 </inglise>
<eesti>Usaldatavusn&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Prudential Requirements </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 93. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 93. </inglise>
<eesti>Aktsiakapital </eesti>
<inglise>Share capital </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu aktsiakapital peab olema v&auml;hemalt: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The share capital of an investment firm shall be equivalent to at least: </inglise>
<eesti>1) 125 000 eurot, kui ta osutab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 43 punktides 1, 2, 3, 5 v&otilde;i 7 nimetatud teenuseid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) 125 000 euro, if the firm is providing services specified in clauses 43 1), 2), 3), 5) or 7) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) 730 000 eurot, kui ta osutab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 43 punktides 4 v&otilde;i 6 v&otilde;i &sect; 44 punktis 1 nimetatud teenuseid. </eesti>
<inglise>2) 730 000 euro, if the firm is providing services specified in clauses 43 4) or 6) or clause 44 1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui investeerimis&uuml;hing osutab v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiportfelli valitsemise teenust ning tema aktsiakapital on v&auml;iksem kui 730 000 eurot, on tal &otilde;igus teha tehinguid v&otilde;i hoida v&auml;&auml;rtpabereid oma arvel &uuml;ksnes juhul, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an investment firm provides securities portfolio management services and its share capital is less than 730 000 euro, it has the right to conduct transactions or maintain the securities for own account only if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) positsioon tekkis investeerimis&uuml;hingu v&otilde;imetusest kliendi korraldust t&auml;ita; </eesti>
<inglise>1) this position arose from the inability of the investment firm to execute the client's order; </inglise>
<eesti>2) k&otilde;igi selliste positsioonide turuv&auml;&auml;rtus kokku ei &uuml;leta 18 750 eurot; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the total market value of all such positions does not exceed 18 750 euro; </inglise>
<eesti>3) selline positsioon on juhusliku ja ajutise iseloomuga; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the position is of occasional and temporary nature; </inglise>
<eesti>4) sellise positsiooni kestmise aeg on rangelt piiratud ajaga, mis on vajalik k&otilde;nealuse eba&otilde;nnestunud tehingu t&auml;itmiseks ja </eesti>
<inglise>4) the duration of the position is strictly limited to the time needed to conduct the unsuccessful transaction in question; </inglise>
<eesti>5) investeerimis&uuml;hing vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 103 ja 105 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>5) the investment firm meets the requirements provided for in &sect;&sect; 103 and 105 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 94. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 94. </inglise>
<eesti>Usaldatavusnormatiivid </eesti>
<inglise>Prudential ratios </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimisteenuste osutamisega seotud riskide v&auml;hendamiseks on investeerimis&uuml;hing kohustatud pidevalt j&auml;rgima usaldatavusnormatiive, millega m&auml;&auml;ratakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to reduce the risks related to providing investment services, an investment firm is required at all times to adhere to prudential rates which set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) neto-omavahendite minimaalsuurus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the minimum amount of net own funds; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kapitali adekvaatsuse m&auml;&auml;r; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the capital adequacy ratio; </inglise>
<eesti>3) riskide kontsentreerumise piirm&auml;&auml;rad; </eesti>
<inglise>3) limitations on concentration of exposures; </inglise>
<eesti>4) v&auml;lisvaluuta avatud netopositsiooni piirm&auml;&auml;rad. </eesti>
<inglise>4) limitations on net open currency positions. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu usaldatavusnormatiivid, nende arvutamise juhendi ja aruandluse korra kehtestab rahandusminister oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The prudential ratios for investment firms, the instructions for assessment thereof and the procedure for reporting shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Investeerimis&uuml;hing on kohustatud v&otilde;tma tarvitusele meetmed, mis tagavad v&otilde;imaluse usaldatavusnormatiivide arvutamiseks piisava t&auml;psusega igal ajahetkel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Investment firms are required to take measures rendering it possible to assess the prudential ratios at all times with sufficient precision. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 95. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 95. </inglise>
<eesti>Konsolideerimisgrupi usaldatavusnormatiivid </eesti>
<inglise>Prudential ratios of consolidation group </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui investeerimis&uuml;hing kuulub konsolideerimisgruppi, kuuluvad kapitali adekvaatsuse m&auml;&auml;r ja riskide kontsentreerumise piirm&auml;&auml;rad t&auml;itmisele ja j&auml;rgimisele nii investeerimis&uuml;hingu kohta eraldi kui ka konsolideeritud alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an investment firm is a member of a consolidation group, the capital adequacy rate and limitations on concentration of exposures shall be complied with and observed both separately with regard to each investment firm and also on a consolidated basis. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu konsolideerimisgrupi moodustavad investeerimis&uuml;hing, selle emaettev&otilde;tja ning samasse kontserni kuuluvad finantseerimisasutused, samuti finantseerimisasutused, mille aktsia- v&otilde;i osakapitalist v&otilde;i aktsiate v&otilde;i osaga esindatud h&auml;&auml;ltest investeerimis&uuml;hing omab v&auml;hemalt 20 protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The consolidation group of an investment firm comprises the investment firm, its parent undertaking and financial institutions belonging to the same group, as well as financial institutions in which the investment firm owns at least 20% of the share capital or votes represented by shares. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui investeerimis&uuml;hingu konsolideerimisgruppi kuulub v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks krediidiasutus, k&auml;sitatakse konsolideerimisgruppi krediidiasutuse konsolideerimisgrupina ja sellele kohaldatakse krediidiasutuste seaduses ja selle alusel s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If at least one credit institution belongs to the consolidation group of an investment firm, the consolidation group is deemed to be the consolidation group of the credit institution and the provisions of the Credit Institutions Act and legislation established on the basis thereof shall apply with respect to the group. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Inspektsiooni n&otilde;usolekul ei arvata investeerimis&uuml;hingu konsolideerimisgruppi ettev&otilde;tjat, kelle: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) With the consent of the Supervision Authority, the consolidation group of an investment firm shall not include an undertaking: </inglise>
<eesti>1) konsolideerimisgruppi arvamine moonutaks inspektsiooni hinnangul investeerimis&uuml;hingu konsolideerimisgrupi tegelikku finantsmajanduslikku olukorda; </eesti>
<inglise>1) whose inclusion in the consolidation group would, in the opinion of the Supervision Authority, distort the actual financial and economic situation of the consolidation group of the investment firm; </inglise>
<eesti>2) asukoht on v&auml;ljaspool lepinguriiki ja kellelt vajaliku aruandluse saamine on takistatud tulenevalt asukohariigis kehtivatest &otilde;igusaktidest v&otilde;i muudel p&otilde;hjustel. </eesti>
<inglise>2) which is not located in a Contracting State and from which the possibility of obtaining the necessary reports is restricted due to the legislation of its home country or for other reasons. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 96. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 96. </inglise>
<eesti>Investeerimis&uuml;hingu omavahendid </eesti>
<inglise>Own funds of investment firm </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu omavahendid on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following are the own funds of an investment firm: </inglise>
<eesti>1) esimese taseme omavahendid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) Tier 1 own funds; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teise taseme omavahendid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) Tier 2 own funds; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kolmanda taseme omavahendid. </eesti>
<inglise>3) Tier 3 own funds. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Esimese ja teise taseme omavahendid kokku moodustavad bruto-omavahendid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Tier 1 and Tier 2 own funds together constitute gross own funds. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Neto-omavahendid saadakse, arvates rahandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatava korra kohaselt bruto-omavahenditest maha: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In order to calculate net own funds, the following shall be deducted from gross own funds pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Finance: </inglise>
<eesti>1) osalused teistes krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutustes; </eesti>
<inglise>1) holdings in other credit and financial institutions; </inglise>
<eesti>2) allutatud n&otilde;uded ja muud nimetatud instrumentidega sarnased kapitali iseloomuga n&otilde;uded krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutustele, mis kuuluvad nende asutuste omavahenditesse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) subordinated claims and other claims of a capital nature which are similar thereto and held in respect of credit and financial institutions and which are part of the own funds of such institutions; </inglise>
<eesti>3) riski kontsentratsiooni piirm&auml;&auml;rasid &uuml;letavad summad. </eesti>
<inglise>3) amounts which exceed the limitations on the concentration of exposures. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 97. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 97. </inglise>
<eesti>Allutatud laen </eesti>
<inglise>Subordinated debt </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Allutatud laen on n&otilde;ue investeerimis&uuml;hingu vastu, mis investeerimis&uuml;hingu l&otilde;petamise v&otilde;i pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamise korral rahuldatakse p&auml;rast k&otilde;igi teiste v&otilde;lausaldajate &otilde;igustatud n&otilde;uete rahuldamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Subordinated debt is a claim against an investment firm which, in the event of the dissolution of the investment firm or the declaration of the investment firm bankrupt, is satisfied after the justified claims of all other creditors have been satisfied. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Allutatud laenu v&otilde;ib kaasata investeerimis&uuml;hingu omavahendite koosseisu, kui see vastab j&auml;rgmistele tingimustele: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Subordinated debt may be included in the own funds of an investment firm if it meets the following conditions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) investeerimis&uuml;hing ei anna tagatist selle kohustuse t&auml;itmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the investment firm does not issue a guarantee for the performance of such obligation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) s&auml;tted ei sisalda tingimust, mille kohaselt teatud asjaolude korral tekib investeerimis&uuml;hingul kohustus tasuda laen ennet&auml;htaegselt, v&auml;lja arvatud investeerimis&uuml;hingu l&otilde;petamise korral; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the provisions do not include a condition pursuant to which the investment firm would, under certain circumstances, be required to repay the loan before the agreed due date, except in the case of the dissolution of the investment firm; </inglise>
<eesti>3) s&auml;tted ei sisaldada tingimust, mis v&otilde;ib muuta laenu esialgselt kokkulepitust kallimaks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the provisions do not include a condition which could make the loan more expensive than originally agreed; </inglise>
<eesti>4) lepingus ei ole s&auml;testatud fikseeritud kulusid; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the contract does not prescribe fixed costs; </inglise>
<eesti>5) allutatud laenu summasid saab piiranguteta kasutada tavap&auml;raste riskide katmiseks enne kahjumi kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramist; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the amounts of the subordinated debt can be used without restrictions to cover ordinary risks prior to determining loss; </inglise>
<eesti>6) lepingus on s&auml;testatud investeerimis&uuml;hingu &otilde;igus mitte maksta intressi, kui investeerimis&uuml;hingu omavahendid ei ole piisavad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 94 nimetatud usaldatavusnormatiivide t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the contract prescribes the right of the investment firm not to pay interest if the own funds of the investment firm are insufficient to comply with the prudential ratios specified in &sect; 94 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu omavahendite koosseisu kaasatud allutatud laenu ennet&auml;htaegne tagasimaksmine on lubatud vaid laenusaaja algatusel ja inspektsiooni eelneva kirjaliku n&otilde;usoleku alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Repayment of subordinated debt included in the own funds of an investment firm before the agreed due date is only permitted on the initiative of the borrower and on the basis of prior written consent from the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Inspektsioon annab investeerimis&uuml;hingule n&otilde;usoleku k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud allutatud laenu ennet&auml;htaegseks tagasimaksmiseks vaid juhul, kui p&auml;rast tagasimakse teostamist on investeerimis&uuml;hingu omavahendid piisavad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 94 nimetatud usaldatavusnormatiivide t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Supervision Authority shall grant its consent to an investment firm for repayment of the subordinated debt specified in subsection (3) of this section before the agreed due date only on the condition that, after repayment, the own funds of the investment firm will be sufficient to comply with the prudential ratios specified in &sect; 94 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu pankroti korral toimub k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 99 ja 100 s&auml;testatud omavahenditest tulenevate tunnustatud n&otilde;uete rahuldamine p&auml;rast t&auml;htaegselt esitamata, kuid tunnustatud n&otilde;uete rahuldamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In the event of the bankruptcy of an investment firm, the accepted claims deriving from the own funds prescribed in &sect;&sect; 99 and 100 of this Act shall be satisfied after satisfaction of accepted claims not filed by the due date. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 98. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 98. </inglise>
<eesti>Esimese taseme omavahendid </eesti>
<inglise>Tier 1 own funds </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Esimese taseme omavahendid on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Tier 1 own funds consist of: </inglise>
<eesti>1) sissemakstud aktsiakapital, v&auml;lja arvatud &auml;riseadustikus s&auml;testatud eelisaktsiate eest tasutud summad; </eesti>
<inglise>1) paid-in share capital, except for amounts paid for preferred shares prescribed by the Commercial Code; </inglise>
<eesti>2) aa&zcaron;io; </eesti>
<inglise>2) share premium accounts; </inglise>
<eesti>3) seaduse ja p&otilde;hikirjaga etten&auml;htud kasumi arvel moodustatud reservid ja reservkapital; </eesti>
<inglise>3) reserves formed on the basis of law and the articles of association on account of the profits, and reserve capital; </inglise>
<eesti>4) eelmiste aastate jaotamata kasum v&otilde;i kahjum; </eesti>
<inglise>4) retained profits or losses from previous years; </inglise>
<eesti>5) jooksva majandusaasta kasum, mille kohta audiitor on andnud hinnangu; </eesti>
<inglise>5) profits for the current financial year, approved by an auditor; </inglise>
<eesti>6) muud k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktides 1-3 nimetatutega sarnased kapitali iseloomuga inspektsiooni poolt esimese taseme omavahenditena aktsepteeritavad instrumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>6) other financial instruments which are similar to those specified in clauses 1) -3) of this subsection, are of capital nature and are accepted as Tier 1 own funds by the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Esimese taseme omavahendite suuruse leidmiseks arvatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 loetletud kirjete kogusummast maha: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to calculate the size of the Tier 1 own funds, the following shall be deducted from the total of the entries specified in subsection (1) of this section: </inglise>
<eesti>1) oma aktsiad soetusmaksumuses; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the acquisition cost of own shares; </inglise>
<eesti>2) immateriaalne p&otilde;hivara j&auml;&auml;kv&auml;&auml;rtuses; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the residual value of intangible assets; </inglise>
<eesti>3) jooksva majandusaasta kahjum. </eesti>
<inglise>3) losses for the current financial year. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Investeerimis&uuml;hingul peab olema v&otilde;imalik viivitamata ja piiranguteta kasutada kahjumite v&otilde;i riskide katmiseks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud esimese taseme omavahendeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Tier 1 own funds specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be available to the investment firm for immediate and unrestricted use to cover losses or risks. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 99. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 99. </inglise>
<eesti>Teise taseme omavahendid </eesti>
<inglise>Tier 2 own funds </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teise taseme omavahenditena v&otilde;etakse arvesse reaalselt laekunud rahasumma. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Only amounts actually received shall be taken into account as Tier 2 own funds. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teise taseme omavahendid on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Tier 2 own funds consist of: </inglise>
<eesti>1) allutatud laenud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 97 t&auml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise>1) subordinated debt in the meaning of &sect; 97 of this Act </inglise>
<eesti>2) eelisaktsiad &auml;riseadustiku t&auml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise>2) preferred shares in the meaning of the Commercial Code; </inglise>
<eesti>3) muud inspektsiooni poolt teise taseme omavahenditena aktsepteeritavad k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktides 1 ja 2 nimetatutega sarnased kohustused ning kapitali iseloomuga instrumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>3) other commitments which are similar to those specified in clauses 1) and 2) of this subsection, are of a capital nature and are accepted as Tier 2 own funds by the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teise taseme omavahendid jagunevad: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Tier 2 own funds are divided into: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &uuml;lemised omavahendid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) upper Tier 2 own funds; </inglise>
<eesti>2) alumised omavahendid. </eesti>
<inglise>2) lower Tier 2 own funds. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Teise taseme &uuml;lemiste omavahendite hulka kuuluvad instrumendid peavad vastama j&auml;rgmistele tingimustele: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Instruments included in upper Tier 2 own funds shall meet the following conditions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) lepingus ei ole s&auml;testatud tagastamise t&auml;htaega (t&auml;htajatu leping); </eesti>
<inglise>1) the term for repayment is not provided in the contract (contract concluded for an unspecified term); </inglise>
<eesti>2) lepingus on s&auml;testatud kohustus teatada laenu tagasimaksmise n&otilde;udest ette v&auml;hemalt viis aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the contract provides that the repayment of debt is subject to at least five years' notice. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Teise taseme alumiste omavahendite hulka kuuluvad k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud instrumendid, kui lepingu kohaselt on nende tagasimaksmise t&auml;htaeg pikem kui viis aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Lower Tier 2 own funds include instruments specified in subsection (2) of this section if, pursuant to the contract, the term for repayment thereof is longer than five years. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Lepingu l&otilde;ppemise v&otilde;i l&otilde;petamise p&auml;evale eelneva viie aasta jooksul tuleb igal j&auml;rgneval aastal teise taseme alumiste omavahendite hulka kuuluvat summat j&auml;rk-j&auml;rgult v&auml;hendada 20 protsendi v&otilde;rra laenu algsummast. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) During the five years before the date of expiry or termination of the contract, the amount included in lower Tier 2 own funds shall be reduced each year by 20 per cent of the original amount of debt. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;henduse arvestamine toimub kvartaalselt. </eesti>
<inglise>The reduction shall be calculated on a quarterly basis. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 100. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 100. </inglise>
<eesti>Kolmanda taseme omavahendid </eesti>
<inglise>Tier 3 own funds </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kolmanda taseme omavahendite hulka kuuluvad allutatud laenud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 97 t&auml;henduses, mis on rahalise sissemaksena t&auml;ielikult antud investeerimis&uuml;hingu k&auml;sutusse, ja kui on t&auml;idetud k&otilde;ik j&auml;rgmised tingimused: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Tier 3 own funds consist of subordinated debt in the meaning of &sect; 97 of this Act which has been placed at the full disposal of an investment firm in the form of monetary contributions, on the condition that each of the following conditions is met: </inglise>
<eesti>1) lepingus s&auml;testatud allutatud laenu tagasimaksmise t&auml;htaeg on v&auml;hemalt kaks aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the term for repayment of the subordinated debt prescribed in the contract is at least two years; </inglise>
<eesti>2) lepingus on s&auml;testatud investeerimis&uuml;hingu &otilde;igus lepingu t&auml;htaja saabumisel mitte maksta laenu ja intresse, kui tema omavahendid ei ole piisavad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 94 nimetatud usaldatavusnormatiivide t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the right of the investment firm not to repay the loan or pay interest upon the maturity thereof is prescribed in the contract, if the own funds of the investment firm are insufficient to comply with the prudential ratios specified in &sect; 94 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hing on kohustatud inspektsiooni teavitama kolmanda taseme omavahendite koosseisu kuuluvate allutatud laenude ja intresside maksmisest, kui tema omavahendid on v&auml;iksemad kui 120 protsenti k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 103 l&otilde;ike 2 kohaselt kehtestatud kapitali adekvaatsuse m&auml;&auml;rale vastavatest omavahenditest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An investment firm is required to notify the Supervision Authority of the repayment of loans and payment of interest included in Tier 3 own funds if its own funds are less than 120 per cent of the own funds corresponding to the capital adequacy ratio prescribed in subsection 103 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 101. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 101. </inglise>
<eesti>Investeerimis&uuml;hingu kauplemisportfell </eesti>
<inglise>Trading portfolio of investment firm </inglise>
<eesti>Investeerimis&uuml;hingu kauplemisportfell koosneb k&otilde;igist j&auml;rgmistest instrumentidest: </eesti>
<inglise>The trading portfolio of an investment firm consists of each of the following instruments: </inglise>
<eesti>1) v&auml;&auml;rtpaberid, kaubad ja tuletisinstrumendid, mis on soetatud edasim&uuml;&uuml;miseks ja kasumi teenimiseks tegelike ning oodatavate ostu- ja m&uuml;&uuml;gihindade erinevustelt v&otilde;i muudelt hinna ja intressim&auml;&auml;rade k&otilde;ikumistelt l&uuml;hiajalise perioodi jooksul; </eesti>
<inglise>1) securities, goods and derivative instruments which have been acquired with a view to re-sale and earning profits on differences between the actual and expected purchase and selling prices or on other fluctuations in prices and interest rates during short periods; </inglise>
<eesti>2) k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi punktis 1 nimetatud instrumentidega seotud riskide katmiseks v&otilde;etud kohustused ja soetatud instrumendid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) commitments made and instruments acquired in order to cover risks related to instruments specified in clause (1) of this section; </inglise>
<eesti>3) instrumendid, mis on oma iseloomult sarnased k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi punktides 1 ja 2 nimetatud instrumentidega. </eesti>
<inglise>3) instruments which are of a similar nature to those specified in clauses 1) or 2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 102. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 102. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavahenditele kehtestatud piirangud </eesti>
<inglise>Limitations on own funds </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 99 loetletud teise taseme omavahendite hulka arvatud allutatud laenude ja &auml;riseadustikus s&auml;testatud eelisaktsiate summa ei tohi &uuml;letada 50 protsenti esimese taseme omavahenditest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The total amount of subordinated debt and of preferred shares prescribed in the Commercial Code included in Tier 2 own funds specified in &sect; 99 of this Act shall not exceed 50 per cent of Tier 1 own funds. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teise taseme omavahendid, mida kasutatakse kauplemisportfelliga mitteseotud riskide katmiseks, ei tohi &uuml;letada 100 protsenti samal otstarbel kasutatavatest esimese taseme omavahenditest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The total amount of Tier 2 own funds which are used to cover risks unrelated to the trading portfolio shall not exceed 100 per cent of the Tier 1 own funds used for the same purpose. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teise ja kolmanda taseme omavahendite summa kokku ei tohi &uuml;letada 100 protsenti investeerimis&uuml;hingu esimese taseme omavahenditest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The total amount of Tier 2 and Tier 3 own funds shall not exceed 100 per cent of the Tier 1 own funds of an investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kauplemisportfelli riskide katmiseks kasutatavad teise taseme omavahendid ja kolmanda taseme omavahendid kokku ei tohi &uuml;letada 200 protsenti kauplemisportfelli riskide katmiseks kasutatavatest esimese taseme omavahenditest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The total amount of Tier 2 and Tier 3 own funds used to cover risks related to the trading portfolio shall not exceed 200 per cent of the Tier 1 own funds used to cover risks related to the trading portfolio. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1-4 s&auml;testatud piirm&auml;&auml;rasid &uuml;letavaid teise ja kolmanda taseme omavahendeid ei tohi arvestada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 94 nimetatud usaldatavusnormatiivide arvutamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Tier 2 and Tier 3 own funds in excess of the limitations provided for in subsections (1) -(4) of this section shall not be taken into account for the purposes of assessing the prudential ratios specified in &sect; 94 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 103. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 103. </inglise>
<eesti>Kapitali adekvaatsus </eesti>
<inglise>Capital adequacy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kapitali adekvaatsus v&auml;ljendab investeerimis&uuml;hingu omavahendite suuruse vastavust investeerimis&uuml;hingu kauplemisportfellist ning kogu &auml;ritegevusest tulenevatele riskidele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Capital adequacy is an expression of the correspondence of the own funds of an investment firm to risks arising from the trading portfolio and business activities of the investment firm in general. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu omavahendid peavad igal ajahetkel olema v&otilde;rdsed v&otilde;i &uuml;letama j&auml;rgneva suuruse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The own funds of an investment firm shall at all times be equal to or larger than the following amounts: </inglise>
<eesti>1) krediidiriski katmiseks n&otilde;utav omavahendite suurus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the amount of own funds required to cover credit risk; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kauplemisportfelli positsiooni riski katmiseks n&otilde;utav omavahendite suurus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the amount of own funds required to cover the position risk of the trading portfolio; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kauplemisportfelli &uuml;lekande- ja vastaspoole riski katmiseks n&otilde;utav omavahendite suurus; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the amount of own funds required to cover the transfer and counter-party risk of the trading portfolio; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kogu majandustegevusest tuleneva valuutariski katmiseks n&otilde;utav omavahendite suurus; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the amount of own funds required to cover the foreign exchange risk arising from business activities in general; </inglise>
<eesti>5) riskikontsentratsiooni piirm&auml;&auml;ra &uuml;letavatelt summadelt n&otilde;utav omavahendite suurus. </eesti>
<inglise>5) the amount of own funds required from amounts exceeding the limitation on the concentration of exposures. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu vastava kirjaliku taotluse alusel on inspektsioonil &otilde;igus vabastada investeerimis&uuml;hing kohustusest arvutada kauplemisportfelliga seotud positsiooni- ning &uuml;lekande- ja vastaspoole riski katmiseks n&otilde;utav omavahendite suurus j&auml;rgmiste asjaolude esinemisel: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) On the basis of a corresponding written application from an investment firm, the Supervision Authority has the right to release the investment firm from the obligation to calculate the amount of own funds required to cover the position, transfer and counter-party risks of the trading portfolio, subject to the following circumstances: </inglise>
<eesti>1) investeerimis&uuml;hingu kauplemisportfelli v&auml;&auml;rtus ei &uuml;leta rohkem kui viie p&auml;eva jooksul viit protsenti koguvara ja bilansiv&auml;liste kohustuste kogusummast; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the value of the trading portfolio of the investment firm does not exceed 5 per cent of the total amount of total assets and off-balance sheet items for more than five days; </inglise>
<eesti>2) investeerimis&uuml;hingu kauplemisportfelli v&auml;&auml;rtus ei &uuml;leta rohkem kui viie p&auml;eva jooksul 15 miljonit eurot; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the value of the trading portfolio of the investment firm does not exceed 15 million euro for more than five days; </inglise>
<eesti>3) investeerimis&uuml;hingu kauplemisportfelli v&auml;&auml;rtus ei &uuml;leta &uuml;helgi ajahetkel 20 miljonit eurot ega kuut protsenti koguvara ja bilansiv&auml;liste kohustuste kogusummast. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the value of the trading portfolio of the investment firm does not at any time exceed 20 million euro or 6 per cent of the total amount of total assets and off-balance sheet items. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu vastava kirjaliku taotluse alusel on inspektsioonil &otilde;igus vabastada investeerimis&uuml;hing kapitali adekvaatsuse arvutamise kohustusest juhul, kui investeerimis&uuml;hingul ei ole investeerimisteenuste osutamisel &uuml;helgi ajahetkel kliendi ees varalisi kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) On the basis of a corresponding written application from an investment firm, the Supervision Authority has the right to release the investment firm from the obligation to calculate capital adequacy if the investment firm does not have any proprietary obligations with respect to any client at any time during the provision of investment services. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 104. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 104. </inglise>
<eesti>Likviidsus </eesti>
<inglise>Liquidity </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hing peab paigutama oma vara selliselt, et igal ajal oleks tagatud kreeditoride &otilde;igustatud n&otilde;uete rahuldamine ehk likviidsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An investment firm shall invest its assets such that the satisfaction of justified claims of creditors, i.e. the liquidity, is guaranteed at all times. </inglise>
<eesti>Selleks peab investeerimis&uuml;hing s&auml;ilitama vajalikku likviidsete vahendite ja jooksvate kohustuste vahekorda. </eesti>
<inglise>For that purpose, an investment firm shall maintain the necessary ratio of liquid assets and current liabilities. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui see on vajalik investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt osutatavate teenuste iseloomu v&otilde;i investeerimis&uuml;hingu finantsseisundi t&otilde;ttu, v&otilde;ib inspektsioon kehtestada igale investeerimis&uuml;hingule eraldi likviidsuse piirm&auml;&auml;ra. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If necessary due to the nature of the services provided by an investment firm or the financial situation of an investment firm, the Supervision Authority may establish a separate liquidity requirement for each investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 105. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 105. </inglise>
<eesti>Riskide kontsentreerumise piirm&auml;&auml;rad </eesti>
<inglise>Limitations on concentration of exposures </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riskide kontsentreerumine on investeerimis&uuml;hingu &uuml;hest kliendist v&otilde;i omavahel seotud osapooltest tulenevate n&otilde;uete, sealhulgas tuletisv&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega seotud n&otilde;uete, osaluste ja bilansiv&auml;liste kohustuste summa suhe investeerimis&uuml;hingu neto-omavahenditesse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Concentration of exposures is the ratio of the total of the claims, including claims arising from derivative instruments, holdings and off-balance sheet items, of a client of an investment firm or a group of connected parties to the net own funds of the investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>Riskide kontsentreerumine on suur, kui nimetatud suhe on suurem kui 10 protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise>The concentration of exposures is deemed to be large if this ratio is greater than 10 per cent. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu riskide kontsentreerumine &uuml;he kliendi v&otilde;i omavahel seotud isikute suhtes ei v&otilde;i &uuml;helgi juhul &uuml;letada 25 protsenti investeerimis&uuml;hingu neto-omavahenditest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The concentration of exposures of an investment firm with respect to a client or group of connected persons shall in no case exceed 25 per cent of the net own funds of the investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Omavahel seotud isikuteks loetakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The following are deemed to be groups of connected persons: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kahte v&otilde;i enamat isikut, kes kujutavad endast investeerimis&uuml;hingule v&otilde;i selle konsolideerimisgrupile &uuml;hist riski, kuna neist &uuml;ks omab kas otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt kontrolli teise v&otilde;i teiste tegevuse &uuml;le v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>1) two or more persons who constitute a single risk to an investment firm or the consolidation group thereof because one of the persons, whether directly or indirectly, has control over the activities of the other or others, or </inglise>
<eesti>2) kahte v&otilde;i enamat isikut, kelle vahel ei ole k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktis 1 nimetatud seost, kuid kes kujutavad endast investeerimis&uuml;hingule v&otilde;i tema konsolideerimisgrupile &uuml;hist riski omavahelise seotuse t&otilde;ttu nii, et neist &uuml;he finantsseisundi halvenemisel ilmnevad t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt makseraskused ka teisel v&otilde;i k&otilde;igil teistel. </eesti>
<inglise>2) two or more persons between whom there is no relationship specified in clause (1) of this subsection but who constitute a single risk to an investment firm or the consolidation group thereof because they are so interconnected that, if one of the persons were to experience financial problems, the other or all of the others would be likely to encounter repayment difficulties. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui klient v&otilde;i omavahel seotud isikud on investeerimis&uuml;hingu emaettev&otilde;tja, t&uuml;tar- v&otilde;i sidusettev&otilde;tjad v&otilde;i investeerimis&uuml;hingu emaettev&otilde;tja t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja, siis riskide kontsentreerumine nende suhtes ei v&otilde;i &uuml;letada 20 protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a client is or groups of connected persons are the parent undertaking, subsidiaries or affiliated undertakings of an investment firm or a subsidiary of the parent undertaking of the investment firm, the concentration of exposures with respect thereto shall not exceed 20 per cent. </inglise>
<eesti>Piirm&auml;&auml;r ei kehti konsolideeritud j&auml;relevalve alla kuuluva emaettev&otilde;tja ja t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>This limitation does not apply to the parent undertaking and subsidiaries subject to supervision on a consolidated basis. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu suurte riskide kontsentreerumiste kogusumma k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 t&auml;henduses ei tohi olla suurem kui 800 protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The total of large concentrations of exposures of an investment firm within the meaning of subsection (1) of this section shall not exceed 800 per cent. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 106. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 106. </inglise>
<eesti>Teavitamiskohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Notification obligation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hing peab viivitamata teavitama inspektsiooni ning esitama omapoolse selgituse, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An investment firm shall immediately inform the Supervision Authority and provide an explanation if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) investeerimis&uuml;hingu neto-omavahendite suurus v&auml;heneb rohkem kui viie protsendi v&otilde;rra; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the size of the net own funds of the investment firm decreases by more than 5 per cent; </inglise>
<eesti>2) investeerimis&uuml;hingu kapitali adekvaatsus v&auml;heneb rohkem kui &uuml;he protsendi v&otilde;rra; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the capital adequacy of the investment firm decreases by more than 1 per cent; </inglise>
<eesti>3) investeerimis&uuml;hing &uuml;letab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 102 v&otilde;i &sect; 105 l&otilde;igetes 2, 4 ja 5 s&auml;testatud piiranguid v&otilde;i ei t&auml;ida k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 98 l&otilde;ikes 3, &sect; 103 l&otilde;ikes 2 v&otilde;i &sect; 104 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud usaldatavusnormatiivi. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the investment firm exceeds the limitations provided for in &sect; 102 or subsections 105 (2), (4) and (5) of this Act or fails to comply with the prudential ratios provided for in subsections 98 (3), 103 (2) or 104 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hing peab viivitamata teavitama inspektsiooni k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 100 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud allutatud laenude ja muude samasuguste kohustuste tagasimaksetest, kui investeerimis&uuml;hingu k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 103 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud omavahendite suurus langeb alla 120 protsendi usaldatavusnormatiivist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An investment firm shall immediately inform the Supervision Authority of the repayment of any subordinated debt and other similar obligations specified in subsection 100 (2) of this Act, if the size of the own funds provided for in subsection 103 (2) of this Act falls below 120 per cent of the prudential ratio. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Investeerimis&uuml;hing peab teavitama inspektsiooni k&otilde;igist suurtest riskide kontsentreerumistest v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kord aastas, kusjuures aasta jooksul teatatakse igast uuest suurest riskide kontsentreerumisest ning olemasolevate suurte riskide kontsentreerumiste v&auml;hemalt 20-protsendilisest suurenemisest, v&otilde;rreldes eelmise teatamisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An investment firm shall inform the Supervision Authority of any large concentrations of exposures at least once a year, whereupon the Supervision Authority shall be notified in the course of the year of each new large concentration of exposure and of each increase of at least 20 per cent in existing large concentrations of exposures in comparison with the preceding notification. </inglise>
<eesti>12. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 12 </inglise>
<eesti>Investeerimis&uuml;hingu raamatupidamine ja aruandlus </eesti>
<inglise>Accounting and Reporting by Investment Firms </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 107. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 107. </inglise>
<eesti>Raamatupidamise korraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of accounting </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu raamatupidamisarvestust ja -aruandlust korraldatakse, l&auml;htudes raamatupidamise seadusest (RT I 1994, 48, 790; 1995, 26-28, 355; 92, 1604; 1996, 40, 773; 42, 811; 49, 953; 1998, 59, 941; 1999, 55, 584; 101, 903), k&auml;esolevast seadusest, muudest &otilde;igusaktidest ja investeerimis&uuml;hingu p&otilde;hikirjast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The accounting and reporting of investment firms shall be organised pursuant to the Accounting Act (RT I 1994, 48, 790; 1995, 26-28, 355; 92, 1604; 1996, 40, 773; 42, 811; 49, 953; 1998, 59, 941; 1999, 55, 584; 101, 903), this Act, other legislation and the articles of association of the investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu raamatupidamine peab tagama t&otilde;ese teabe saamise investeerimis&uuml;hingu majandustegevuse ja finantsseisundi kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The accounting of an investment firm shall provide truthful information relating to the business activities and the financial situation of the investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu konsolideerimisgrupi emaettev&otilde;tja on kohustatud korraldama konsolideeritud raamatupidamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The parent undertaking of a consolidation group of an investment firm is required to organise consolidated accounting. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 108. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 108. </inglise>
<eesti>Aruanded </eesti>
<inglise>Reports </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hing koostab, esitab inspektsioonile ning avalikustab majandusaasta aruande ja vahearuanded (edaspidi aruanded) seadusega s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An investment firm shall prepare annual reports and interim reports (hereinafter reports), submit them to the Supervision Authority and disclose them pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vahearuanne on raamatupidamise aruanne, mille aluseks olev aruandeperiood algab majandusaasta algusest ja on l&uuml;hem kui &uuml;ks majandusaasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An interim report is an accounting report, and the period which serves as the basis therefor commences at the beginning of the financial year and is shorter than one financial year. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu konsolideerimisgrupi emaettev&otilde;tja esitab inspektsioonile konsolideeritud aruandlust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The parent undertaking of a consolidation group of an investment firm shall present consolidated accounts to the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Rahandusminister kehtestab oma m&auml;&auml;rusega investeerimis&uuml;hingule: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Minister of Finance shall, by a regulation, establish the following for investment firms: </inglise>
<eesti>1) aruannete sisu, koostamise metoodika ning esitamise korra; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the contents, methods of preparation and procedure for submission of reports; </inglise>
<eesti>2) konsolideeritud aruandluse n&otilde;uded. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the requirements for consolidated accounting. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 109. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 109. </inglise>
<eesti>Aruannete sisu ja esitamise sagedus </eesti>
<inglise>Contents and frequency of submission of reports </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 43 s&auml;testatud investeerimisteenuseid osutav investeerimis&uuml;hing on kohustatud inspektsioonile esitama aruandeid j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An investment firm providing investment services prescribed in &sect; 43 of this Act is required to submit reports to the Supervision Authority as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kui ta osutab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 43 punktides 4 v&otilde;i 6 v&otilde;i &sect; 44 punktis 1 nimetatud teenuseid, esitab ta &uuml;ks kord kuus, kuid mitte hiljem kui 10 p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast aruandeperioodi l&otilde;ppu, vahearuande koos &sect; 94 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud usaldatavusnormatiivide arvutustega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) if the investment firm provides services specified in clauses 43 4) or 6) or clause 44 1) of this Act, it shall submit an interim report once a month, but not later than within ten days after the end of the period under review, together with an assessment of the prudential ratios provided for in subsection 94 (1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kui ta osutab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 43 punktides 1, 2, 3, 5 v&otilde;i 7 nimetatud teenuseid, esitab ta &uuml;ks kord kvartalis, kuid mitte hiljem kui 20 p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast aruandeperioodi l&otilde;ppu, vahearuande koos k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 94 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud usaldatavusnormatiivide arvutustega. </eesti>
<inglise>2) if the investment firm provides services specified in clauses 43 1), 2), 3), 5) or 7) of this Act, it shall submit an interim report once a quarter, but not later than within twenty days after the end of the period under review, together with an assessment of the prudential ratios provided for in subsection 94 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hing esitab auditeeritud majandusaasta aruande nelja kuu jooksul p&auml;rast aruandeperioodi l&otilde;ppu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An investment firm shall submit an audited annual report within four months after the end of the period under review. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu konsolideerimisgrupi emaettev&otilde;tja esitab konsolideeritud poolaasta- v&otilde;i aastaaruanded kolme kuu jooksul p&auml;rast aruandeperioodi l&otilde;ppu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The parent undertaking of a consolidation group of an investment firm shall submit consolidated semi-annual and annual reports within three months after the end of the period under review. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 110. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 110. </inglise>
<eesti>Aruannete avalikustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Disclosure of reports </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu avalikustatav aruanne peab olema k&auml;ttesaadav investeerimis&uuml;hingu asukohas, tema k&otilde;igis filiaalides ja esindustes ning investeerimis&uuml;hingu veebilehel, selle puudumisel esitab investeerimis&uuml;hing avalikustatava aruande inspektsioonile avalikustamiseks inspektsiooni veebilehel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Reports subject to disclosure by an investment firm shall be available at the seat and all branches and representative offices of the investment firm as well as on its website, or if the investment firm does not have its own website, it shall submit the report subject to disclosure to the Supervision Authority for disclosure thereof on the website of the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahandusminister kehtestab oma m&auml;&auml;rusega avalikustamisele kuuluvate andmete miinimumloetelu, aruannete vormid, koostamise metoodika ja avalikustamise t&auml;htajad. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The minimum amount of information to be disclosed, the reporting forms, the methods of preparing reports and term for disclosure thereof shall be established by regulation of the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 111. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 111. </inglise>
<eesti>Audiitorkontroll </eesti>
<inglise>Audit </inglise>
<eesti>Investeerimis&uuml;hinguga samasse konsolideerimisgruppi kuuluvaid &auml;ri&uuml;hinguid peab kontrollima v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks &uuml;hine audiitor. </eesti>
<inglise>Companies belonging to the same consolidation group as an investment firm shall be audited by at least one common auditor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 112. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 112. </inglise>
<eesti>Audiitori nimetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Appointment of auditor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu audiitoriks v&otilde;ib nimetada investeerimis&uuml;hingu auditeerimiseks piisavate teadmiste ja kogemustega usaldusv&auml;&auml;rse isiku. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A trustworthy person with adequate expertise and experience to audit investment firms may be appointed auditor of an investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu audiitori v&otilde;ib nimetada &uuml;hekordse audiitorkontrolli tegemiseks v&otilde;i teatud t&auml;htajaks, kuid kokku mitte kauemaks kui viieks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The auditor of an investment firm may be appointed to conduct a single audit or for a specific term which shall not exceed five years. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu asukohaj&auml;rgne kohus m&auml;&auml;rab inspektsiooni avalduse alusel audiitori, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An auditor shall be appointed by a court of the seat of the investment firm on the basis of a petition from the Supervision Authority if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &uuml;ldkoosolek ei ole audiitorit nimetanud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the general meeting has not appointed an auditor; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;ldkoosoleku poolt nimetatud audiitor loobus audiitorkontrolli l&auml;biviimisest ja investeerimis&uuml;hingu &uuml;ldkoosolek ei ole &uuml;he kuu jooksul nimetanud uut audiitorit. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the auditor appointed by the general meeting refuses to conduct an audit and the general meeting of the investment firm fails to appoint another auditor within one month. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kohtu poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud audiitori volitused kestavad kuni uue audiitori nimetamiseni &uuml;ldkoosoleku poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The authority of a court-appointed auditor shall continue until appointment of a new auditor by the general meeting. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 113. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 113. </inglise>
<eesti>Audiitori teavitamiskohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Notification obligation of auditor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Audiitor on kohustatud viivitamata kirjalikult inspektsiooni teavitama investeerimis&uuml;hingu auditeerimise k&auml;igus talle teatavaks saanud asjaoludest, mille tulemuseks on v&otilde;i v&otilde;ib olla: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An auditor is required to notify the Supervision Authority promptly in writing of any circumstances of which he or she becomes aware in the course of conducting an audit of the investment firm and which result or may result in: </inglise>
<eesti>1) investeerimis&uuml;hingu tegevust reguleerivate &otilde;igusaktide oluline rikkumine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) material violation of legislation regulating the activities of investment firms; </inglise>
<eesti>2) investeerimis&uuml;hingu tegevuse peatumine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) interruption of the activities of the investment firm; </inglise>
<eesti>3) investeerimis&uuml;hingu t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja tegevuse peatumine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) interruption of the activities of a subsidiary of the investment firm; </inglise>
<eesti>4) audiitori m&auml;rkustega j&auml;reldusotsus investeerimis&uuml;hingu raamatupidamise aastaaruande v&otilde;i konsolideeritud raamatupidamise aastaaruande kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a qualified report by the auditor concerning the annual accounts or consolidated accounts of the investment firm; </inglise>
<eesti>5) olukord v&otilde;i oht olukorra tekkimiseks, kus investeerimis&uuml;hing ei ole v&otilde;imeline t&auml;itma oma kohustusi; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a situation, or the risk of a situation arising, in which the investment firm is unable to perform its obligations; </inglise>
<eesti>6) juhi v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja tegudest tulenev oluline varaline kahju investeerimis&uuml;hingule, tema kliendile v&otilde;i klientidele. </eesti>
<inglise>6) an act by a manager or employee causing significant proprietary damage to the investment firm or to a client or clients thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioonile andmete edastamise n&otilde;udele ei laiene &otilde;igusakti v&otilde;i lepinguga audiitorile pandud andmete mitteavalikustamise kohustus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An obligation not to disclose information, which is imposed on an auditor by legislation or a contract, does not apply to the requirement to forward information to the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>13. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 13 </inglise>
<eesti>Investeerimis&uuml;hingu &uuml;hinemine </eesti>
<inglise>Merger of Investment Firms </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 114. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 114. </inglise>
<eesti>Jagunemise keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition of division </inglise>
<eesti>Investeerimis&uuml;hingu jagunemine ei ole lubatud. </eesti>
<inglise>Division of an investment firm is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 115. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 115. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hinemise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Special merger rules </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu &uuml;hinemine toimub &auml;riseadustikus s&auml;testatud korras, kui k&auml;esolevast peat&uuml;kist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The merger of an investment firm shall be performed pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Commercial Code, unless otherwise prescribed in this Chapter. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hing v&otilde;ib &uuml;hineda &uuml;ksnes investeerimis&uuml;hinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An investment firm may only merge with another investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui investeerimis&uuml;hingud &uuml;hinevad uue &auml;ri&uuml;hingu asutamise teel, l&otilde;pevad k&otilde;igi &uuml;hinevate investeerimis&uuml;hingute tegevusload. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If investment firms merge by founding a new company, the activity licences of all the merging investment firms expire. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 116. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 116. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hinemisleping ja &uuml;hinemisaruanne </eesti>
<inglise>Merger agreement and merger report </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu &uuml;hinemisleping ei v&otilde;i olla s&otilde;lmitud edasil&uuml;kkava v&otilde;i &auml;ramuutva tingimusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The merger agreement of an investment firm shall not be entered into with a suspensive or resolutive condition. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingute vahelise &uuml;hinemislepingu s&otilde;lmimisest peab teavitama inspektsiooni kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul &uuml;hinemislepingu s&otilde;lmimisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority shall be notified of entry into a merger agreement between investment firms within three working days as of the merger agreement being entered into. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Investeerimis&uuml;hingute &uuml;hinemisel tuleb koostada &uuml;hinemisaruanne, mida kontrollib audiitor. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon the merger of investment firms, a merger report shall be prepared and the report shall be audited by an auditor. </inglise>
<eesti>&Auml;riseadustiku &sect; 419 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud vahebilanss tuleb &uuml;hinemisel koostada, kui majandusaasta aruanne on koostatud varem kui kolm kuud enne &uuml;hinemislepingu s&otilde;lmimist. </eesti>
<inglise>The interim balance sheet provided for in subsection 419 (3) of the Commercial Code shall be prepared if the annual report has been prepared more than three months before the merger agreement is entered into. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Audiitori aruandes antakse hinnang aktsiate vahetussuhtele ja selle m&auml;&auml;ramisele ning arvamus selle kohta, kas &uuml;hendav v&otilde;i asutatav investeerimis&uuml;hing vastab k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud usaldatavusnormatiividele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The auditor's report shall provide an opinion on the exchange ratio of shares and the determination thereof and on whether the acquiring investment firm or the investment firm being founded meets the prudential ratios provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 117. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 117. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hinemisluba </eesti>
<inglise>Authorisation for merger </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingute &uuml;hinemiseks on vaja inspektsiooni luba (edaspidi &uuml;hinemisluba). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Authorisation is necessary from the Supervision Authority for the merger of investment firms (hereinafter authorisation for merger). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;hinemisloa saamiseks esitab &uuml;hendav investeerimis&uuml;hing v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 115 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud juhul esitavad &uuml;hinevad investeerimis&uuml;hingud &uuml;hiselt inspektsioonile vastava taotluse, millele lisatakse allj&auml;rgnevad andmed ja dokumendid: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to be granted authorisation for merger, the acquiring investment firm or, in the case prescribed in subsection 115 (3) of this Act, the merging investment firms jointly shall submit an application to the Supervision Authority to which the following information and documents are appended: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &uuml;hinemisleping v&otilde;i selle notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud &auml;rakiri; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the merger agreement or a notarised copy thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;hinemisaruanne; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the merger report; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &uuml;hinemisotsused; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the merger resolutions; </inglise>
<eesti>4) audiitori aruanne; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the auditor's report; </inglise>
<eesti>5) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 54 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 12 nimetatud &auml;riplaan &uuml;hinemisele j&auml;rgneva kolme aasta kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the business plan specified in clause 54 (1) 12) of this Act for the three years following the merger; </inglise>
<eesti>6) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 54 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 5, 6 ja 13 nimetatud andmed ja dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the information and documents specified in clauses 54 (1) 5), 6) and 13) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;hinemisloa taotlusele kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 53 ja &sect; 55 l&otilde;igetes 1-4 tegevusloa taotluse ja selle l&auml;bivaatamise kohta s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The provisions of &sect; 53 and subsections 55 (1) -(4) of this Act regarding applications for activity licences and the review thereof shall apply with respect to applications for authorisation for merger. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 118. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 118. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus &uuml;hinemisloa kohta </eesti>
<inglise>Decision regarding authorisation for merger </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Otsuse &uuml;hinemisloa andmise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise kohta v&otilde;i &uuml;hinemise tulemusena asutatavale investeerimis&uuml;hingule tegevusloa andmise kohta teeb inspektsioon 30 p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates k&otilde;igi n&otilde;utud andmete ja dokumentide esitamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A decision to grant or to refuse to grant authorisation for merger or to issue an activity licence to an investment firm founded as a result of a merger shall be taken by the Supervision Authority not later than within thirty days as of submission of all the required information and documents. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsusest teatatakse viivitamata taotlejale. </eesti>
<inglise>The applicant shall be informed of the decision immediately. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib keelduda &uuml;hinemisloa andmisest, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority may refuse to grant authorisation for merger if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &uuml;hinemisloa taotlemisel esitatud andmed v&otilde;i dokumendid ei vasta k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i need on eba&otilde;iged, eksitavad v&otilde;i mittet&auml;ielikud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the information or documents submitted upon applying for authorisation for merger do not meet the requirements provided for in this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof or such information is or such documents are inaccurate, misleading or incomplete; </inglise>
<eesti>2) taotleja ei esitanud t&auml;htaegselt v&otilde;i on keeldunud esitamast inspektsioonile &uuml;hinemisloa taotlemisel esitamisele kuuluvaid v&otilde;i muid inspektsiooni poolt n&otilde;utud andmeid, dokumente v&otilde;i teavet; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the applicant fails, within the prescribed term, or refuses to submit the information or documents subject to submission to the Supervision Authority upon applying for authorisation for merger; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &uuml;hinemise tulemusena tekkiv investeerimis&uuml;hing ei vasta k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i &uuml;hinemine muul p&otilde;hjusel kahjustaks investeerimis&uuml;hingu klientide huve; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the investment firm founded as a result of the merger does not meet the requirements provided for in this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof or if the merger harm the interests of clients of the investment firm for some other reason; </inglise>
<eesti>4) inspektsiooni hinnangul &uuml;hinemise tulemusena tekkiva investeerimis&uuml;hingu juht, siseaudiitor v&otilde;i taotlejas olulist osalust omav isik ei vasta k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a manager or internal auditor of the investment firm resulting from the merger or a person having a qualifying holding therein does not meet the requirements provided for in this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>5) &uuml;hinemine v&auml;hendab oluliselt t&otilde;husat konkurentsi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiturul v&otilde;i muul p&otilde;hjusel kahjustaks v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru korrap&auml;rast toimimist. </eesti>
<inglise>5) the merger would significantly reduce effective competition in the securities market or would harm the regular operation of the securities market for some other reason. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 119. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 119. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hinemise avalikustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Disclosure of merger </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;hinevad investeerimis&uuml;hingud peavad &uuml;hinemisloa saamise viivitamata avalikustama. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Merging investment firms shall immediately make public the fact of being granted authorisation for merger. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu &uuml;hinemise ning uue investeerimis&uuml;hingu tegevuse alustamise avalikustab investeerimis&uuml;hing seitsme p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast &auml;riregistrisse vastava kande tegemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An investment firm shall make public the merger of the investment firm or the commencement of activities of the new investment firm within seven days after the relevant entry is made in the commercial register. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 nimetatud teave avalikustatakse v&auml;hemalt &uuml;hes &uuml;leriigilise levikuga p&auml;evalehes ning &uuml;hendava investeerimis&uuml;hingu veebilehel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The information specified in subsections (1) and (2) of this section shall be published in at least one national daily newspaper and on the website of the acquiring investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>IV osa </eesti>
<inglise>Part IV </inglise>
<eesti>Reguleeritud turg </eesti>
<inglise>Regulated Market </inglise>
<eesti>14. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 14 </inglise>
<eesti>Tegutsemise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right to Operate </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 120. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 120. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusluba </eesti>
<inglise>Activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Reguleeritud turu (edaspidi k&auml;esolevas osas turg) korraldamiseks p&uuml;siva tegevusalana tuleb inspektsioonilt taotleda vastav tegevusluba (edaspidi k&auml;esolevas osas tegevusluba). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to operate a regulated market (hereinafter in this Part market) as a permanent area of activity, a corresponding activity licence (hereinafter (hereinafter in this Part activity licence) shall be applied for from the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusluba tuleb taotleda iga turu korraldamiseks eraldi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A separate activity licence shall be applied for for operating each market. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Igal turul v&otilde;ib olla &uuml;ksnes &uuml;ks turu korraldaja (edaspidi k&auml;esolevas osas korraldaja). </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Each market may have only one operator of the market (hereinafter in this Part operator). </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Korraldajana tegutsemiseks on &otilde;igus &uuml;ksnes aktsiaseltsil. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Only public limited companies have the right to operate as operators. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Korraldajal ei ole &otilde;igust tegeleda tegevusaladega, mis ei ole seotud turu korraldamisega v&otilde;i mis seavad ohtu turu korrap&auml;rase ja usaldusv&auml;&auml;rse toimimise v&otilde;i tema korraldajana tegutsemise. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An operator does not have the right to engage in other areas of activity which are not related to operating the market or which endanger the regular and reliable operations of the market or its activities as an operator. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 121. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 121. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa taotlemine ja selle menetlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Application for and processing of activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korraldaja tegevusloa suhtes kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 48 l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3, &sect; 51 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 3, &sect;-s 52, &sect; 53 l&otilde;ikes 3, &sect; 55 l&otilde;igetes 1-5 ja &sect;-s 57 s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The provisions of subsections 48 (2) and (3), subsections 51 (1) and (3), &sect; 52, subsection 53 (3), subsections 55 (1) -(5) and &sect; 57 of this Act shall apply with respect to activity licences of operators. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusloa taotlemisel esitab taotleja vastava kirjaliku avalduse ning k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 54 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-11 ja 15 nimetatud andmed ja dokumendid ning k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 127 nimetatud reguleeritud turu reglemendi projekti ja taotleja &auml;riplaani j&auml;rgneva kolme aasta kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon application for an activity licence, the applicant shall submit a corresponding written application, the information and documents specified in clauses 54 (1) 1) -11) and 15) of this Act, the draft rules and regulations of the regulated market specified in &sect; 127 of this Act and its business plan for the next three years. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotluse vormi kehtestab rahandusminister oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The format of applications shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud &auml;riplaan peab sisaldama turu kauplemis-, arveldus-, teabe- ja muude s&uuml;steemide toimimise t&auml;pset kirjeldust, samuti taotleja organisatsioonilise &uuml;lesehituse, tegevuskohtade, rakendatavate infotehnoloogiliste ja muude tehniliste vahendite ning majandusn&auml;itajate kirjeldust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The business plan specified in subsection (2) of this section shall contain a precise description of the trading, settlement, information and other systems of the market as well as a description of the applicant's organisational structure, places of business and the information technology and other technical measures to be implemented, and its economic indicators. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Rahandusminister v&otilde;ib kehtestada oma m&auml;&auml;rusega t&auml;psemad n&otilde;uded k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud &auml;riplaanile. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Minister of Finance may, by a regulation, establish more specific requirements for the business plan specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 122. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 122. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa andmisest keeldumine </eesti>
<inglise>Refusal to issue activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioon keeldub tegevusloa andmisest, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Supervision Authority shall refuse to issue an activity licence if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tegevusloa taotlemisel esitatud andmed v&otilde;i dokumendid ei vasta k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i need on eba&otilde;iged, eksitavad v&otilde;i mittet&auml;ielikud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the information or documents submitted upon application for the activity licence do not meet the requirements provided for in this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof or are inaccurate, misleading or incomplete; </inglise>
<eesti>2) taotleja ei esitanud t&auml;htaegselt v&otilde;i on keeldunud esitamast inspektsioonile tegevusloa taotlemisel esitamisele kuuluvaid v&otilde;i muid inspektsiooni poolt n&otilde;utud andmeid, dokumente v&otilde;i teavet; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the applicant fails, within the prescribed term, or refuses to submit the information or documents subject to submission upon application for an activity licence or requested by the Supervision Authority to the Supervision Authority; </inglise>
<eesti>3) taotleja ei suuda tulenevalt oma organisatsioonilisest &uuml;lesehitusest, &otilde;iguslikest ja tehnilistest lahenditest ning vara ja omakapitali ebapiisavusest t&auml;ita k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktidega korraldajale ja turule kehtestatud n&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the applicant, due to its organisational structure, legal and technical solutions or insufficiency of assets and owners' equity, is not able to meet the requirements established by this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof for operators and the market; </inglise>
<eesti>4) taotleja muud tegevusalad seavad ohtu turu korra- v&otilde;i &otilde;igusp&auml;rase toimimise v&otilde;i korraldajana tegutsemise; </eesti>
<inglise>4) other areas of activity of the applicant endanger the regular and lawful operation of the market or its activities as an operator; </inglise>
<eesti>5) inspektsiooni hinnangul taotleja n&otilde;ukogu ja juhatuse liikmed ei oma piisavalt turu korraldamiseks vajalikke teadmisi v&otilde;i ei ole v&otilde;imelised korraldama turu korra- ja &otilde;igusp&auml;rast toimimist, samuti kui taotleja juhil ei ole oma kohustuste t&auml;itmiseks vajalikku haridust, teadmisi, kogemusi v&otilde;i laitmatut reputatsiooni; </eesti>
<inglise>5) in the opinion of the Supervision Authority, the members of the supervisory board and management board of the applicant do not have sufficient knowledge for operating a market or they are unable to operate the market in a regular and lawful manner, or that manager of the applicant is lacking the education, knowledge, experience or impeccable reputation necessary to perform his or her duties; </inglise>
<eesti>6) juht on olnud pankrotiv&otilde;lgnik v&otilde;i tema suhtes on pankrotimenetlus raugenud, juhi tegevus v&otilde;i tegevusetus on p&otilde;hjustanud isiku pankroti, sundl&otilde;petamise v&otilde;i tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamise v&otilde;i juhi tegevus v&otilde;i tegevusetus on n&auml;idanud tema suutmatust korraldada v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalise v&otilde;i kutselise investori tegevust selliselt, et v&otilde;lausaldajate huvid oleksid k&uuml;llaldaselt kaitstud; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a manager has been a bankrupt or if bankruptcy proceedings with respect to this person have been terminated by abatement, or if the activities or omissions of the manager have led to the bankruptcy, compulsory dissolution or revocation of the activity licence of a person or if the activities or omissions of the manager have shown his or her inability to organise the activities of a professional securities market participant or professional investor in a manner that would sufficiently protect the interests of its creditors; </inglise>
<eesti>7) taotleja ei ole t&auml;itnud k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the applicant fails to meet the requirements provided for in this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>8) taotleja on olulisel m&auml;&auml;ral v&otilde;i korduvalt rikkunud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;udeid v&otilde;i taotleja tegevus v&otilde;i tegevusetus ei vasta headele &auml;ritavadele. </eesti>
<inglise>8) the applicant has materially or repeatedly violated requirements provided for in legislation or the activities or omissions of the applicant are in contradiction with good business practices. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusluba omav korraldaja on kohustatud tegevusloa kehtivuse ajal v&auml;ltima asjaolusid, mis on aluseks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud tegevusloa andmisest keeldumisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) During the period of validity of its activity licence, an operator shall prevent circumstances which would serve as a basis for refusal to issue the activity licence as provided for in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 123. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 123. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korraldaja tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamisele kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 58 l&otilde;igetes 1, 3 ja 4 s&auml;testatut, kui k&auml;esolevast paragrahvist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Unless otherwise prescribed by this section, the provisions of subsections 58 (1), (3) and (4) shall apply with respect to revocation of the activity licence of an operator. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus tunnistada tegevusluba kehtetuks, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority has the right to revoke an activity licence if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) korratus turul v&otilde;ib p&otilde;hjustada ohu riigi majandusele tervikuna v&otilde;i riigi avalikule korrale; </eesti>
<inglise>1) disorder in the market may endanger the economy of the state as a whole or law and order in the state; </inglise>
<eesti>2) korraldaja seab oma tegevuse v&otilde;i tegevusetusega ohtu turu korra- v&otilde;i &otilde;igusp&auml;rase toimimise; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the operator endangers the regular and lawful operation of the market through its activities or omissions; </inglise>
<eesti>3) korraldaja ei suuda oma p&auml;devuse piires tagada turuga seotud investorite huvide kaitset; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the operator is unable to ensure, to the extent of its competence, protection of the interests of investors related to the market; </inglise>
<eesti>4) korraldaja suhtes esineb k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 122 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud tegevusloa andmisest keeldumise alus; </eesti>
<inglise>4) grounds for refusal to issue an activity licence provided for in subsection 122 (1) of this Act exist with respect to the operator; </inglise>
<eesti>5) korraldaja rikub oluliselt k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktis s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uet; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the operator materially violates a requirement provided for in this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>6) korraldaja ei ole t&auml;ies ulatuses v&otilde;i t&auml;htaegselt t&auml;itnud inspektsiooni poolt tehtud ettekirjutust; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the operator fails to comply in full or within the prescribed term with a precept issued by the Supervision Authority; </inglise>
<eesti>7) korraldaja on oma tegevuse v&otilde;i tegevusetuse t&otilde;ttu kaotanud usalduse; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the activities or omissions of the operator have led to a loss of confidence therein; </inglise>
<eesti>8) korraldaja ei ole alustanud turu korraldamist kuue kuu jooksul tegevusloa andmisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>8) the operator fails to commence operating the market within six months as of the issue of the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 124. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 124. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusriski maandamine </eesti>
<inglise>Operating risk management </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korraldaja poolt turu korraldamiseks kasutatav infotehnoloogiline s&uuml;steem v&otilde;i muu tehingute tegemist vahendav ja andmeid salvestav s&uuml;steem peab olema t&ouml;&ouml;kindel ning usaldusv&auml;&auml;rne ja v&auml;hendama tegevusriske turul ning sellel osalejate suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The information technology system or other system used by the operator to conduct transactions and record information in order to operate the regulated market shall be reliable and dependable and reduce operating risks in the market and with respect to market participators. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahandusminister v&otilde;ib oma m&auml;&auml;rusega t&auml;psustada t&ouml;&ouml;kindla ning usaldusv&auml;&auml;rse infotehnoloogilise v&otilde;i muu k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud s&uuml;steemi kriteeriumid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Finance may, by a regulation, specify the criteria for a reliable and dependable information technology system or other system specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Korraldaja peab juhtimis- ja tegevusriskide maandamiseks rakendama piisavaid sisekontrolli meetmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In order to manage management and operating risks, an operator shall apply sufficient internal control measures. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Korraldaja n&otilde;ukogu ja juhatuse liikmetele kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 79 l&otilde;ikes 5 ja &sect;-s 80 investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhtide suhtes s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The provisions of subsection 79 (5) and &sect; 80 of this Act pertaining to managers of an investment firm shall apply with respect to members of the supervisory board and management board of an operator. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 125. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 125. </inglise>
<eesti>Finantsriski maandamine </eesti>
<inglise>Financial risk management </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korraldaja aktsiakapital peab olema v&auml;hemalt 125 000 eurot. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The share capital of an operator shall be at least 125 000 euro. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korraldaja omakapital peab olema v&auml;hemalt v&otilde;rdne summaga, mis on vajalik vastava turu korraldamiseks vajalike viie kuu tegevuskulude katmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The owners' equity of an operator shall be at least equal to the operating costs needed to operate the relevant market for five months. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui korraldaja ei ole alustanud tegevust, arvestatakse turu korraldamiseks vajalike tegevuskulude suurus l&auml;htuvalt &auml;riplaanist, mille taotleja esitab tegevusloa taotlemisel inspektsioonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the operator has not commenced operations, the operating costs needed to operate the market shall be determined on the basis of the business plan submitted to the Supervision Authority by the applicant upon application for an activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>15. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 15 </inglise>
<eesti>Isereguleerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Self-regulation </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 126. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 126. </inglise>
<eesti>Isereguleerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Self-regulation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korraldaja peab oma juhtimise ja organisatsioonilise &uuml;lesehitusega tagama turu korra- ja &otilde;igusp&auml;rase toimimise ning j&auml;relevalve teostamise turul osalejate ja emitentide ning nende tegevuse &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An operator shall, through its management and organisational structure, ensure the regular and lawful operation of the market and supervision of the participators and issuers on the market and the activities thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turu korra- ja &otilde;igusp&auml;rase tegevuse tagamiseks kehtestab korraldaja turu reglemendi (edaspidi reglement). </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to ensure the regular and lawful operation of the market, the operator shall establish the rules and regulations of the market (hereinafter rules and regulations). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Reglemendis s&auml;testatakse korraldaja poolt isikule turul osalemise &otilde;iguse andmiseks selle isikuga s&otilde;lmitava lepingu ja v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite turule kauplemisele v&otilde;tmiseks nende v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite emitendiga s&otilde;lmitava lepingu t&uuml;&uuml;ptingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The rules and regulations shall set out standard conditions on agreements to be entered into with a person for the operator to grant that person the right to participate in the market and on agreements to be entered into with issuers of securities for the admission of such securities for trading to the market. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 127. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 127. </inglise>
<eesti>Reglement </eesti>
<inglise>Rules and regulations </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Reglemendi &uuml;lesanne on tagada turul osalejate ja emitentide kohustuste t&auml;itmine turul, arvestades avalikke ja majanduslikke huve ning investorite kaitset. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The purpose of the rules and regulations is to ensure that the obligations of the participators and issuers in the market are performed, taking into account public and economic interests and the protection of investors. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Reglemendis s&auml;testatakse v&auml;hemalt: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The rules and regulations shall prescribe at least: </inglise>
<eesti>1) turu ja selle korraldaja organisatsiooniline &uuml;lesehitus korraldaja p&otilde;hikirjas kajastamata osas; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the organisational structure of the market and its operator, to the extent that this is not described in the articles of association of the operator; </inglise>
<eesti>2) v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi kauplemisele v&otilde;tmise, kauplemise peatamise ja kauplemise l&otilde;petamise alused, tingimused ning kord; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the bases, conditions and procedure for admitting a security for trading and for the suspension and termination of trading; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kauplemisele v&otilde;etud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitendi peamised &otilde;igused ning kohustused korraldaja, turul osalejate ja teiste turule kauplemisele v&otilde;etud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitentide suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the principal rights and obligations of the issuer of securities admitted for trading with respect to the operator, market participators and issuers of other securities admitted to be traded on the market; </inglise>
<eesti>4) korraldajale teabe edastamise alused, tingimused ja kord; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the bases, conditions and procedure for forwarding information to the operator; </inglise>
<eesti>5) turule lubamise ja osaleja turult eemaldamise alused, tingimused ja kord; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the bases, conditions and procedure for admitting a person to the regulated market and removing a participator therefrom; </inglise>
<eesti>6) turul osaleja peamised &otilde;igused ning kohustused korraldaja, teiste turul osalejate, turul osaleja klientide v&otilde;i v&otilde;lausaldajate ja turule kauplemisele v&otilde;etud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite emitentide suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the principal rights and obligations of a market participator with respect to the operator, other market participators, clients or creditors of the market participator and issuers of securities admitted to be traded on the market; </inglise>
<eesti>7) tehingu tegemine turul, tehingust teatamine, tehingu t&auml;itmiseks vajaliku teabe edastamine, v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi hinnanoteeringu ja muude selliste andmete avalikustamine; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the conducting of a transaction in a market, giving of notification of a transaction, forwarding of information necessary to conduct a transaction, and disclosure of the price quotations of a security and other similar information; </inglise>
<eesti>8) v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi kauplemisele v&otilde;tmist, kauplemise peatamist ja kauplemise l&otilde;petamist otsustava isiku, organi ja organi liikme &otilde;igused ning kohustused, samuti valimise v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;ramise alused, tingimused ja kord; </eesti>
<inglise>8) the rights and obligations of the person, body or member thereof who decides on the admittance of a security for trading or the suspension or termination of trading therewith, and the bases, conditions and procedure for the election or appointment thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>9) j&auml;relevalvet teostava isiku, organi ja organi liikme &otilde;igused ning kohustused j&auml;relevalve teostamisel, samuti valimise v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;ramise alused, tingimused ja kord; </eesti>
<inglise>9) the rights and obligations of the person, body or member thereof who exercises supervision upon the exercise of supervision, and the bases, conditions and procedure for the election or appointment thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>10) leppetrahvid k&auml;esoleva seaduse, selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusakti ja reglemendi rikkumise eest; </eesti>
<inglise>10) contractual penalties for violation of this Act, legislation established on the basis thereof and the rules and regulations; </inglise>
<eesti>11) garantiifondiga seonduv, kui reguleeritud turul on garantiifond. </eesti>
<inglise>11) matters pertaining to the guarantee fund, in the event there is a guarantee fund in the regulated market. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Reglemendi suhtes ei kohaldata seadusega ebam&otilde;istlikult kahjustavate t&uuml;&uuml;ptingimuste kohta s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The provisions of law regarding unreasonably harmful standard conditions shall not apply with respect to rules and regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Korraldajaga s&otilde;lmitud leping teenustasu suuruse ja maksmise kohta turul osalemise, v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi kauplemisele lubamise, turul tehingute tegemise ja muude teenuste eest ei ole reglement. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Any agreement entered into by an operator regarding service fees and payment thereof in return for participation in the market, admission of a security to be traded on the market, conducting of transactions on the market and other services is not deemed to be part of the rules and regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 128. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 128. </inglise>
<eesti>Reglemendi muutmine </eesti>
<inglise>Amendment of rules and regulations </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korraldajal on &otilde;igus reglementi &uuml;hepoolselt muuta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Operators have the right to amend rules and regulations unilaterally. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Reglemendi muutmise korral esitatakse reglemendi muudatused koosk&otilde;lastamiseks inspektsioonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the event of amendment of the rules and regulations, the amendments shall be submitted to the Supervision Authority for approval. </inglise>
<eesti>Koosk&otilde;lastamise taotlemisel esitatakse inspektsioonile vastav kirjalik avaldus, reglemendi projekt koos muudatuste selgitustega ja hinnanguga nende m&otilde;ju kohta turul osalejatele ning turu toimimisele. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon application for approval, a corresponding written application shall be submitted to the Supervision Authority accompanied by the draft rules and regulations together with explanations of the amendments and an estimate of their impact on the market participators and the operation of the market. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda reglemendi muudatuste t&auml;psustamiseks ja m&otilde;ju hindamiseks korraldajalt t&auml;iendavate andmete ja dokumentide esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Supervision Authority may request the operator to submit additional information and documents in order to specify the amendments to the rules and regulations and estimate the impact thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Inspektsioon teeb otsuse reglemendi muudatuste koosk&otilde;lastamise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise kohta 30 p&auml;eva jooksul vastava avalduse esitamisest arvates, kuid mitte hiljem kui 20 p&auml;eva p&auml;rast k&otilde;igi k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud andmete esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Supervision Authority shall make a decision approving the amendments to the rules and regulations or refusing approval thereof within thirty days as of submission of a corresponding application, but not later than within twenty days as of submission of all the information specified in subsection (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Inspektsioon keeldub koosk&otilde;lastamisest, kui reglemendi muudatused on vastuolus &otilde;igusaktidega, on vastuolulised, eksitavad v&otilde;i mittet&auml;ielikud v&otilde;i kui nende rakendamine ei taga k&uuml;llaldaselt investorite v&otilde;i reglemendi poolteks olevate isikute huvide kaitset. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Supervision Authority shall refuse approval if the amendments to the rules and regulations are not in compliance with legislation or are contradictory, misleading or incomplete or if implementation thereof would not guarantee sufficient protection of the interests of investors or of persons serving as parties to the rules and regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 129. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 129. </inglise>
<eesti>Reglemendi muudatuste j&otilde;ustumine </eesti>
<inglise>Entry into force of amendments to rules and regulations </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Reglemendi muudatused j&otilde;ustuvad nende avalikustamisel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 130 s&auml;testatud korras, kui muudatustes ei ole m&auml;&auml;ratud hilisemat t&auml;htaega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Amendments to the rules and regulations shall enter into force upon their disclosure pursuant to the procedure prescribed in &sect; 130 of this Act, unless a later term is set out in the amendments. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Avalikustada v&otilde;ib &uuml;ksnes inspektsiooni poolt koosk&otilde;lastatud reglemendi muudatusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Only amendments to the rules and regulations which are approved by the Supervision Authority may be disclosed. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 130. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 130. </inglise>
<eesti>Reglemendi avalikustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Disclosure of rules and regulations </inglise>
<eesti>Korraldaja avalikustab reglemendi oma veebilehel. </eesti>
<inglise>The operator shall disclose the rules and regulations on its website. </inglise>
<eesti>16. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 16 </inglise>
<eesti>Turu korraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Operation of Market </inglise>
<eesti>1. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 1 </inglise>
<eesti>Turul osaleja ja emitent </eesti>
<inglise>Market Participator and Issuer </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 131. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 131. </inglise>
<eesti>Korraldaja &uuml;ldine kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>General obligation of operator </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korraldaja kehtestab reglemendi ja rakendab reglementi turu t&otilde;hususe ning l&auml;bipaistvuse tagamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The operator shall establish and implement the rules and regulations in order to ensure the efficiency and transparency of the market. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&otilde;hususe all k&auml;esoleva osa t&auml;henduses m&otilde;istetakse olukorda, kus turul osalejate ofertide ja tehingute tegemine on korraldatud viisil, mis tagab teabe kohese k&auml;ttesaadavuse selliste ofertide ja tehingute tegemise kohta, samuti et turul osalejate tehingute tegemine ja t&auml;itmine toimub n&otilde;uetekohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Part, efficiency denotes a situation where the offers and transactions of market participators are organised in a manner which ensures the immediate availability of information concerning such offers and transactions and that the transactions of market participators are conducted and executed pursuant to requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&auml;bipaistvuse all k&auml;esoleva osa t&auml;henduses m&otilde;istetakse olukorda, kus k&otilde;ik turul osalejad saavad viivitamata ja &uuml;heaegselt &otilde;iget teavet v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega kauplemise ja nende v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite emitentide kohta ning nimetatud teave on avalikkusele k&auml;ttesaadav. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) For the purposes of this Part, transparency denotes a situation where all market participators receive accurate information regarding securities trading and the issuers of such securities immediately and at the same time and where the general public has the opportunity to obtain such information. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 132. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 132. </inglise>
<eesti>V&otilde;rdne kohtlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Equal treatment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Iga&uuml;hel on &otilde;igus osaleda turul v&otilde;i anda emiteeritud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberid kauplemiseks turule, kui ta vastab k&auml;esolevas seaduses, selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides ja korraldaja kehtestatud reglemendis s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Everyone meeting the conditions provided for in this Act, legislation established on the basis thereof and the rules and regulations established by the operator have the right to participate in a market or put issued securities on the market for trading. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korraldaja v&otilde;imaldab turul kaubelda &uuml;ksnes selliste v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega, mille emitent kohustub t&auml;itma reglementi ja maksma korraldajale tema poolt kehtestatud teenustasu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An operator shall only permit securities to be traded on the market if the issuer thereof undertakes to observe the rules and regulations and pay the operator a service fee established by the latter. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Korraldaja v&otilde;imaldab turul osaleda &uuml;ksnes isikul, kes kohustub t&auml;itma reglementi ja maksma korraldajale tema poolt kehtestatud teenustasu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An operator shall only permit persons to participate in the market who undertake to observe the rules and regulations and pay the operator a service fee established by the latter. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Turu reglement ja teenustasud kehtivad &uuml;hetaoliselt, neid muudetakse ja rakendatakse samadel alustel k&otilde;igi turul osalejate suhtes, samuti osalemist taotlejate, turul kaubeldavate v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite emitentide ja v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite turule kauplemisele v&otilde;tmist taotlejate suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The rules and regulations of the market and service fees apply uniformly and they shall be applied and amended uniformly with respect to all market participators as well as applicants to participate, issuers of securities traded on the market and applicants seeking their securities to be admitted for trading on the market. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 133. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 133. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluste lahendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Resolution of disputes </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isikul on &otilde;igus esitada kohtusse v&otilde;i poolte kokkuleppel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 202 nimetatud vahekohtusse hagi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi kauplemisele v&otilde;tmise &otilde;iguse tunnustamiseks ja korraldaja sundimiseks v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi kauplemisele v&otilde;tmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person has the right to file an action with a court or, subject to agreement between the parties, the arbitral tribunal specified in &sect; 202 of this Act for recognition of the right of a security to be admitted for trading and for obliging the operator to admit the security for trading. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isikul on &otilde;igus esitada kohtusse v&otilde;i poolte kokkuleppel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 202 nimetatud vahekohtusse hagi turul osalemise &otilde;iguse tunnustamiseks ja korraldaja sundimiseks isikule turul osalemise &otilde;iguse andmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person has the right to file an action with a court or, subject to agreement between the parties, the arbitral tribunal specified in &sect; 202 of this Act for recognition of the right to participate in the regulated market and for obliging the operator to grant the person the right to participate in the market. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 134. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 134. </inglise>
<eesti>Turul osaleja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of market participator </inglise>
<eesti>Turul osaleja on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>A market participator is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&auml;itma reglementi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) observe the rules and regulations; </inglise>
<eesti>2) andma korraldajale &otilde;igusakti v&otilde;i reglemendi alusel n&otilde;utud ulatuses &otilde;iget, t&auml;pset ja t&auml;ielikku teavet &otilde;igusaktis ja reglemendis s&auml;testatud kohustuste t&auml;itmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) supply the operator with accurate, precise and complete information to the extent demanded on the basis of legislation or the rules and regulations for the purpose of performing its obligations provided for in the legislation and rules and regulations; </inglise>
<eesti>3) andma korraldaja poolt n&otilde;utud v&otilde;i reglemendis s&auml;testatud ulatuses teavet v&auml;ljaspool turgu sellel turul kaubeldavate v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega oma arvel v&otilde;i kolmanda isiku arvel tehtud tehingutest; </eesti>
<inglise>3) supply information, to the extent requested by the operator or prescribed by the rules and regulations, regarding transactions conducted outside the regulated market for own account or for the account of a third party with securities traded on the regulated market; </inglise>
<eesti>4) mitte manipuleerima turuga ning j&auml;rgima ausa ja &otilde;iglase kauplemise p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid ning turul kehtivaid h&auml;id tavasid. </eesti>
<inglise>4) refrain from manipulating the market and to follow the principles of fair and equitable trading and generally accepted market principles. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 135. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 135. </inglise>
<eesti>Turul kaubeldava v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitendi kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of issuer of security traded on market </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turul kaubeldava v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitent on kohustatud t&auml;itma k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 134 punktides 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The issuer of a security traded on the market is required to perform the obligations prescribed in clauses 134 1) and 2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turul kaubeldava v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitendi t&auml;isosanikud, n&otilde;ukogu ja juhatuse liikmed, t&ouml;&ouml;tajad ning isikud, kellele emitent on kontrollitav &auml;ri&uuml;hing, on kohustatud j&auml;rgima selle emitendi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega turul tehingute tegemisel ausa ja &otilde;iglase kauplemise p&otilde;him&otilde;tet. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Full partners, members of the management board and supervisory board and employees of an issuer of a security traded on the market, as well as persons to whom the issuer is a controlled company, shall follow the principles of fair and equitable trading when conducting transactions on the market with the securities of this issuer. </inglise>
<eesti>2. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Tehingud turul </eesti>
<inglise>Transactions on Market </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 136. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 136. </inglise>
<eesti>Kauplemise peatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension of trading </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investorite huvide kaitseks, turu korra- v&otilde;i &otilde;igusp&auml;rase toimimise ohustamise v&auml;ltimiseks v&otilde;i muu olulise &otilde;iguse kaitseks v&otilde;i ohu v&auml;ltimiseks on inspektsioonil &otilde;igus teha korraldajale ettekirjutus: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to protect the interests of investors, to avoid danger to the regular and lawful operation of the market or to protect any other significant interest or avoid any other threat, the Supervision Authority has the right to issue a precept to an operator: </inglise>
<eesti>1) v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega tehingute tegemise peatamiseks turul; </eesti>
<inglise>1) for suspension of trading with securities on the market; </inglise>
<eesti>2) k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud peatamise korralduse muutmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) for amendment of the suspension order provided for in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korraldajal on &otilde;igus peatada v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega tehingute tegemine turul, kui v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitent on korraldaja suhtes rikkunud &otilde;igusakti v&otilde;i reglemendi alusel tekkinud kohustust, investorite huvide kaitseks, turu korra- v&otilde;i &otilde;igusp&auml;rase toimimise ohustamise v&auml;ltimiseks v&otilde;i muul reglemendis s&auml;testatud alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to protect the interests of investors or to avoid danger to the regular and lawful operation of the market or on some other grounds provided for in the rules and regulations, the operator has the right to suspend trading with a security on the market if the issuer of the security has violated an obligation with respect to the operator and arising from legislation or the rules and regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 137. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 137. </inglise>
<eesti>Kauplemise l&otilde;petamine </eesti>
<inglise>Cessation of trading </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus teha korraldajale ettekirjutus v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega tehingute tegemise l&otilde;petamiseks turul investorite huvide kaitseks, turu korra- v&otilde;i &otilde;igusp&auml;rase toimimise ohustamise v&auml;ltimiseks v&otilde;i muu olulise &otilde;iguse kaitseks v&otilde;i ohu v&auml;ltimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to protect the interests of investors, to avoid danger to the regular and lawful operation of the market or to protect any other significant interest or avoid any other threat, the Supervision Authority has the right to issue a precept to an operator for the cessation of trading with securities on the market. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korraldajal on &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega tehingute tegemine turul nende v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite emitendi avalduse alusel, kui emitent on korraldaja suhtes n&otilde;uetekohaselt t&auml;itnud k&otilde;ik &otilde;igusaktide ja reglemendi alusel tekkinud kohustused. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An operator has the right to cease trading with a security on the market on the basis of an application from the issuer of the security if the issuer has duly performed its obligations with respect to the operator and arising from legislation and the rules and regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Korraldajal on &otilde;igus l&otilde;petada v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega tehingute tegemine turul, kui nende v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite emitent on korraldaja suhtes oluliselt rikkunud &otilde;igusakti v&otilde;i reglemendi alusel tekkinud kohustust, turul ei tehta nende v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega korra- v&otilde;i &otilde;igusp&auml;raseid tehinguid v&otilde;i muul reglemendis s&auml;testatud alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An operator has the right to cease trading with a security on the market if the issuer of the security has significantly violated an obligation arising from legislation or the rules and regulations with respect to the operator of the market, if regular and lawful transactions are not conducted with this security on the market, or on some other grounds prescribed in the rules and regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Inspektsioonil on k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud alustel &otilde;igus teha korraldajale ettekirjutus k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatud toimingute muutmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Supervision Authority has the right to issue a precept on the grounds prescribed in subsection (1) of this section for amendment of the acts prescribed in subsections (2) and (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 138. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 138. </inglise>
<eesti>Tehingute registreerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Recording of transactions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korraldaja registreerib iga p&auml;ev kronoloogiliselt k&otilde;ik turul tehtud ja korraldajale teatatud tehingud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An operator shall keep a daily chronological record of all transactions conducted on the market and reported to the operator. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korraldaja registreerib v&auml;hemalt tehingu tegemise aja, tehingu teinud turul osaleja andmed, tehingu esemeks olnud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberid, nende arvu, nimiv&auml;&auml;rtuse ja hinna. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An operator shall at least record the time at which the transaction is conducted, information regarding the market participator which conducted the transaction, the securities which served as the object of the transaction, and their number, nominal value and price. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Korraldaja s&auml;ilitab registrisse kantud andmeid v&auml;hemalt seitse aastat nende registreerimisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An operator shall preserve information entered in the register for at least seven years as of their entry in the register. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Korraldajal on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda registris kajastamiseks teavet tehingu olulistest tingimustest, tehingu teinud turul osaleja kliendi v&otilde;i v&otilde;lausaldaja isikuandmeid, kliendi v&otilde;i v&otilde;lausaldaja ja turul osaleja vahel k&auml;sundi v&otilde;i muu samasuguse suhte tekkimise, muutmise v&otilde;i t&auml;itmise aega ning muid andmeid vastavalt turu reglemendile. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An operator has the right to request information on the significant conditions of a transaction for the purpose of registration, as well as the personal data of the client or creditor of the market participator which conducts the transaction, the time that an obligation or other similar relationship between the client or creditor and the market participator arises and the time of amendment or execution thereof, and other information in accordance with the rules and regulations of the market. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 139. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 139. </inglise>
<eesti>Turu garantiifond </eesti>
<inglise>Market guarantee fund </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui korraldaja on v&otilde;tnud kohustuse tagada turul tehtud tehingute t&auml;itmine, peab ta moodustama garantiifondi v&otilde;i s&otilde;lmima vastava garantii- v&otilde;i kindlustuslepingu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an operator undertakes to guarantee the execution of transactions conducted on the market, the operator shall establish a guarantee fund or enter into a relevant guarantee or insurance contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Garantiifond on krediidiasutustes v&otilde;i Eesti Pangas pangakontol olev v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitesse investeeritud rahasumma, mida peamiselt kasutatakse v&otilde;i mis v&otilde;imaldab seda kasutada v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega turul tehtavate tehingute t&auml;itmise tagamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The guarantee fund is an amount of money held in a bank account in credit institutions or the Bank of Estonia or invested in securities which is mainly used or can be used for guaranteeing the execution of transactions with securities conducted on the market. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Garantiifondi valitseb korraldaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The guarantee fund shall be managed by the operator. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Rahandusminister kehtestab oma m&auml;&auml;rusega n&otilde;uded garantiifondi moodustamisele, selle suurusele ning kasutamisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Minister of Finance shall, by a regulation, establish the requirements for the formation of the guarantee fund and the size and use thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 140. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 140. </inglise>
<eesti>Pankroti erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Special rules for bankruptcy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turul osaleja pankrotihaldur ja turul kaubeldava v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitendi pankrotihaldur j&auml;tkavad reglemendi t&auml;itmist kuni osaleja v&otilde;i emitendi l&otilde;petamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The bankruptcy trustee of a market participator and the bankruptcy trustee of an issuer of a security traded on the market shall continue to execute the rules and regulations until the dissolution of the participator or issuer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turul osalejate poolt reglemendi kohaselt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 139 nimetatud garantiifondi tasutu ei kuulu tasuja ega garantiifondi valdaja pankrotivara hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Contributions made by market participators to the guarantee fund specified in &sect; 139 of this Act shall not be included in the bankruptcy estate of the contributor or the possessor of the guarantee fund. </inglise>
<eesti>3. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Teabe edastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Communication of Information </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 141. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 141. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalikustamisele mittekuuluva teabe hoidmine </eesti>
<inglise>Maintenance of confidentiality of information not subject to disclosure </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korraldaja, selle organi liige ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja hoiavad t&auml;htajatult saladuses teavet, mille nad said oma ametikohustuste t&auml;itmisel korraldaja suhtes v&otilde;i seoses ametiseisundiga v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;ga turul v&otilde;i inspektsioonilt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 149 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud koost&ouml;&ouml; raames ning mis ei kuulu avalikustamisele vastavalt &otilde;igusaktidele, kohtuotsusele v&otilde;i turu reglemendile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Operators and members of bodies and employees thereof shall maintain indefinitely the confidentiality of any information which is obtained when performing their official duties with respect to the operator or in connection with their position or duties in the market or from the Supervision Authority within the framework of co-operation referred to in subsection 149 (2) of this Act and which is not subject to disclosure in accordance with legislation, a court judgement or the rules and regulations of the market. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korraldaja organi liige ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;ivad k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud teavet edastada sama korraldaja organile, selle liikmele ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajale vastavalt korraldaja p&otilde;hikirjas ning reglemendis s&auml;testatule, samuti isikutele, keda seadus kohustab hoidma saadud teavet saladuses, ning juhtudel, kui sellise teabe avalikustamise kohustus tuleneb seadusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A member of a body and an employee of an operator may forward the information provided for in subsection (1) of this section to the body of the same operator or a member or employee thereof pursuant to the provisions of the articles of association and the rules and regulations of the operator, and to persons who are required by law to maintain the confidentiality of information obtained, and in cases where the obligation to disclose such information arises from law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 142. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 142. </inglise>
<eesti>Teabe edastamise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Obligation to communicate information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korraldajale edastatav teave peab olema &otilde;ige, selge, t&auml;pne ja t&auml;ielik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Information communicated to the operator shall be accurate, clear, precise and complete. </inglise>
<eesti>Teave edastatakse korraldajale viivitamata, kui k&auml;esolevas seaduses, selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides v&otilde;i reglemendis ei s&auml;testata teistsugust t&auml;htaega. </eesti>
<inglise>Information shall be communicated to the operator immediately unless a different term is prescribed by this Act, legislation established on the basis thereof or the rules and regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turul kaubeldava v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitent on kohustatud tema suhtes kehtiva reglemendi kehtivuse ajal viivitamata teavitama korraldajat k&otilde;ikidest olulistest asjaoludest oma tegevuses, juhtimises, majandus- ja finantsseisundis ning muudest v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega seotud olulistest asjaoludest, mis v&otilde;ivad m&otilde;jutada v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi hinda turul v&otilde;i selle v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitendi kohustust kohaselt t&auml;ita v&auml;&auml;rtpaberist tulenevaid emitendi kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) During the term that the rules and regulations apply to an issuer of a security traded on the market, the issuer is required to inform the operator immediately of all significant circumstances pertaining to the activities, management and economic and financial situation of the issuer and of other significant circumstances pertaining to the securities which may affect the price of the security on the market or the obligation of the issuer of the security to perform the obligation of the issuer arising from the security. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Korraldajal on &otilde;igus reglemendis s&auml;testada t&auml;iendavad andmed v&otilde;i t&auml;psustada andmed, mida turul kaubeldava v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitent edastab korraldajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An operator has the right to prescribe additional or more specific information in the rules and regulations which the issuer of securities traded on the market shall communicate to the operator. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Turul osalejad edastavad viivitamata korraldajale vajalikku teavet k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 144 l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatud kohustuste t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Market participators shall immediately communicate the information necessary to perform the obligations prescribed in subsections 144 (2) and (3) of this Act to the operator. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 143. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 143. </inglise>
<eesti>Korraldaja poolt teabe avalikustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Disclosure of information by operator </inglise>
<eesti>Korraldaja avalikustab k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides ning reglemendis s&auml;testatud ulatuses ja korras turu osalejatelt, emitentidelt ja muudelt isikutelt saadud teabe v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru l&auml;bipaistvuse tagamise eesm&auml;rgil. </eesti>
<inglise>In order to guarantee the transparency of the securities market, an operator shall disclose information obtained from market participators, issuers and other persons to the extent and pursuant to the procedure prescribed in this Act, legislation established on the basis thereof and the rules and regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 144. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 144. </inglise>
<eesti>Kauplemisteabe avalikustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Disclosure of trading information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korraldaja on kohustatud tagama pideva teabe k&auml;ttesaadavuse turul kaubeldavate v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite kohta, sealhulgas teabe v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite omandamise ja v&otilde;&otilde;randamise hinna, viimaste hindade, hinnamuutuse, madalaima ja k&otilde;rgeima hinna ning tehingu mahtude ning arvu kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An operator is required to ensure constant access to information on the securities traded on the market, including the acquisition and transfer price of the securities, recent prices, price changes, the highest and lowest prices and the volume and number of transactions. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahandusminister kehtestab oma m&auml;&auml;rusega t&auml;psemad n&otilde;uded avalikustatavale kauplemisteabele, selle mahule, sagedusele ja muudele tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Finance shall, by a regulation, establish more specific requirements for the trading information to be disclosed and for the volume and frequency thereof and other requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib korraldaja taotlusel teha rahandusministri poolt kehtestatud korras erandeid kauplemisteabe avalikustamise tingimuste suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) On the application of an operator, the Supervision Authority may, pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Finance, make exceptions regarding the conditions for the disclosure of trading information. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui turul osalejatel on pidev eelnev juurdep&auml;&auml;s v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi hinnateabele ja omandada v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randada soovitavate v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite arvu kirjeldavatele ettepanekutele, siis: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If market participators have permanent prior access to price information regarding a security and to offers describing the number of securities put up for acquisition or transfer: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tagab korraldaja sellise teabe pideva k&auml;ttesaadavuse kogu kauplemisperioodi jooksul; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the operator shall ensure permanent access to such information for the whole trading period; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teatavaks tehtud hinnaga ja teatud koguse v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite omandamiseks v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randamiseks tehtud ettepanek peab olema tingimusteta aktseptitav ning seda ettepanekut ei saa muuta ega tagasi v&otilde;tta. </eesti>
<inglise>2) an offer made at a disclosed price for the acquisition or transfer of a certain amount of securities shall be unconditionally acceptable and the offer may not be amended or withdrawn. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 145. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 145. </inglise>
<eesti>Teabe avalikustamise viis </eesti>
<inglise>Manner of disclosure of information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korraldaja on kohustatud avalikustama k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 143 nimetatud teabe oma veebilehel, ringh&auml;&auml;lingus v&otilde;i &uuml;leriigilise levikuga ajalehes. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An operator is required to disclose the information specified in &sect; 143 of this Act on its website, through the broadcast media or in a national newspaper. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 144 nimetatud kauplemisteabe on korraldaja kohustatud avalikustama oma veebilehel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An operator is required to disclose the trading information specified in &sect; 144 of this Act on its website. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 ja 2 nimetatud teave avalikustatakse eesti keeles. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Information specified in subsections (1) and (2) of this section shall be disclosed in Estonian. </inglise>
<eesti>Lisaks eesti keelele v&otilde;ib vastava teabe avalikustada ka m&otilde;nes muus keeles. </eesti>
<inglise>In addition to Estonian, the information may also be disclosed in another language. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 146. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 146. </inglise>
<eesti>Teabe edastamise ja avalikustamise kohustusest vabastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Release from obligation to communicate and disclose information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud teabe korraldajale edastamise ja avalikustamise kohustuse v&otilde;ib korraldaja n&otilde;usolekul j&auml;tta t&auml;itmata turu reglemendis s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) With the consent of the operator and on the bases and pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the rules and regulations of the market, the obligation referred to in this Act to communicate information to the operator and to disclose information may be lifted. </inglise>
<eesti>Korraldaja on antud n&otilde;usolekust kohustatud viivitamata teavitama inspektsiooni. </eesti>
<inglise>The operator is required to notify the Supervision Authority immediately of any such consent granted. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib oma ettekirjutusega kohustada korraldajat taganema k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 alusel antud n&otilde;usolekust, kui inspektsioon leiab, arvestades turu v&otilde;i emitendi seisundit ja investorite &otilde;igusi, et korraldaja vastav n&otilde;usolek ei ole p&otilde;hjendatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority may issue a precept obliging the operator to withdraw its consent granted on the basis of subsection (1) of this section if, given the standing of the market or the issuer and the rights of investors, the Supervision Authority is of the opinion that the consent of the operator is not justified. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Inspektsioon loetakse n&otilde;ustunuks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud korraldaja n&otilde;usolekuga, kui inspektsioon ei ole &uuml;he t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva m&ouml;&ouml;dudes, arvates n&otilde;usolekust teada saamisest, teinud korraldajale k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud ettekirjutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Supervision Authority is deemed to have agreed to the consent of the operator specified in subsection (1) of this section if, after one working day has passed since learning of the grant of consent, the Supervision Authority has not issued a precept specified in subsection (2) of this section to the operator. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 147. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 147. </inglise>
<eesti>Kauplemisteabe mitteavalikustamise tingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Conditions for non-disclosure of trading information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 144 s&auml;testatud kohustusest v&otilde;ib korraldaja kirjaliku p&otilde;hjendatud taotluse alusel ja inspektsiooni n&otilde;usolekul k&otilde;rvale kalduda, kui seda tingib erakorraline olukord turul kaubeldava v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiga, selle emitendiga, selle turuga v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruga tervikuna. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) On the basis of a justified written application and with the consent of the Supervision Authority, the operator need not perform the obligation prescribed in &sect; 144 of this Act if this is caused by an extraordinary situation with respect to the security traded on the market, the issuer thereof, the market or the securities market in general. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioon loetakse keeldunuks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;usoleku andmisest, kui inspektsioon ei ole &uuml;he t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva m&ouml;&ouml;dudes korraldaja vastava taotluse saamisest arvates n&otilde;usolekut andnud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority is deemed to have refused to grant the consent provided for in subsection (1) of this section if, after one working day has passed since receiving the corresponding application from the operator, the Supervision Authority has not granted consent. </inglise>
<eesti>Inspektsioon ei pea n&otilde;usoleku andmata j&auml;tmist p&otilde;hjendama. </eesti>
<inglise>The Supervision Authority need not justify its refusal to grant consent. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Rahandusminister kehtestab oma m&auml;&auml;rusega k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud erakorraliste olukordade t&auml;psemad kriteeriumid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Minister of Finance shall, by a regulation, establish more detailed criteria for the extraordinary situations specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>17. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 17 </inglise>
<eesti>Turuj&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>Market Supervision </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 148. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 148. </inglise>
<eesti>Korraldaja j&auml;relevalve teostamise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right of operator to exercise supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korraldaja teostab turul j&auml;relevalvet turul kaubeldava v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi hinna kujunemise, tehingute tegemise ja t&auml;itmise &uuml;le, avastamaks ning v&auml;hendamaks siseteabe alusel tehingute tegemist, turuga manipuleerimist ja teisi &otilde;iguserikkumisi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An operator shall exercise supervision over the market with respect to the price formation of securities traded on the market and the conducting and execution of transactions for the purpose of detecting and reducing transactions conducted on the basis of inside information, market manipulation and other violations of law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korraldaja teostab j&auml;relevalvet turul osaleja ja turul kaubeldava v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitendi &uuml;le &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud ulatuses, reglemendis s&auml;testatud alustel ja ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An operator shall exercise supervision over market participators and issuers of securities traded on the market to the extent prescribed by legislation and on the bases and to the extent prescribed in the rules and regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Korraldajal on &otilde;igus reglemendis s&auml;testada oma &otilde;igused j&auml;relevalve teostamisel lisaks &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An operator has the right to establish its rights in exercising supervision in the rules and regulations in addition to those prescribed in legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Korraldajal on &otilde;igus kontrollida turul osaleja tema turul osalemise &otilde;igusega seotud dokumente ning saada turul osalejalt j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks vajalikku teavet. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An operator has the right to verify the documents of market participators pertaining to their right to participate in the market, and to obtain information therefrom which is necessary for exercising supervision. </inglise>
<eesti>Korraldajal on sama &otilde;igus turul kaubeldava v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitendi suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>An operator has the same rights with respect to issuers of securities traded on the market. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 149. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 149. </inglise>
<eesti>Koost&ouml;&ouml; inspektsiooniga </eesti>
<inglise>Co-operation with Supervision Authority </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Korraldaja teatab viivitamata avastatud &otilde;iguserikkumisest inspektsioonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An operator shall inform the Supervision Authority immediately of any violation of law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korraldaja ja inspektsioon teevad koost&ouml;&ouml;d turuj&auml;relevalve teostamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The operator and the Supervision Authority shall co-operate in exercising market supervision. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Turuj&auml;relevalve teostamisel on inspektsioonil &otilde;igus avaldada korraldajale turuj&auml;relevalve teostamiseks vajalikku teavet, sealhulgas avalikustamisele mittekuuluvat teavet, mis inspektsioon on saanud k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon exercising market supervision, the Supervision Authority has the right to disclose information to the operator which is necessary for exercising market supervision, including information not subject to disclosure which the Supervision Authority has obtained in the course of exercising its duties prescribed in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Korraldaja v&otilde;imaldab inspektsiooni n&otilde;udel inspektsioonile vaba juurdep&auml;&auml;su j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks turu korraldamiseks kasutatavale infotehnoloogilisele s&uuml;steemile ja muule tehingute tegemist vahendavale ning andmeid salvestavale s&uuml;steemile. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If so requested by the Supervision Authority, an operator shall grant the Supervision Authority free access to the information technology system used to operate the market and to other systems used for the intermediation of transactions and recording of information for the purpose of exercising market supervision. </inglise>
<eesti>18. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 18 </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;&auml;rtpaberib&ouml;rs </eesti>
<inglise>Stock Exchange </inglise>
<eesti>1. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 1 </inglise>
<eesti>Tegutsemise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Special Rules for Operations </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 150. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 150. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;&auml;rtpaberib&ouml;rsi m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of stock exchange </inglise>
<eesti>(1) V&auml;&auml;rtpaberib&ouml;rs on turg, kus kaubeldakse noteeritud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A stock exchange is a market where listed securities are traded. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&auml;&auml;rtpaberib&ouml;rsile (edaspidi b&ouml;rs) ja b&ouml;rsi korraldajale (edaspidi b&ouml;rsikorraldaja) kohaldatakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses vastavalt turu ja selle korraldaja kohta s&auml;testatut, kui k&auml;esolevast peat&uuml;kist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Unless otherwise prescribed in this Chapter, the provisions of this Act regarding a market and its operator shall apply to a stock exchange (hereinafter exchange) and the operator of a stock exchange (hereinafter operator of an exchange) respectively. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 151. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 151. </inglise>
<eesti>B&ouml;rsi liige </eesti>
<inglise>Member of exchange </inglise>
<eesti>(1) B&ouml;rsikorraldajal on &otilde;igus oma p&otilde;hikirjas ja reglemendis s&auml;testada, et b&ouml;rsil v&otilde;ivad osaleda &uuml;ksnes b&ouml;rsi liikmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An operator of an exchange has the right to set out in its articles of association and the rules and regulations that only members of the exchange may participate in the exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) B&ouml;rsi liige on isik, kellele b&ouml;rsikorraldaja on andnud &otilde;iguse v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;iguse teha oferte ja tehinguid k&otilde;igi v&otilde;i teatud noteeritud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega b&ouml;rsil ning kes kohustub t&auml;itma b&ouml;rsi reglementi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A member of an exchange is a person to whom the operator of the exchange has granted the right or sole right to make offers and conduct transactions with all or certain listed securities and who undertakes to observe the rules and regulations of the exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) B&ouml;rsi liikmeks v&otilde;ib saada &uuml;ksnes v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutseline osaline. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Only professional securities market participants may become members of an exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) B&ouml;rsi liige on kohustatud maksma b&ouml;rsikorraldajale teenustasu, kui reglemendis ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Members of an exchange are required to pay service fees to the operator of the exchange, unless otherwise prescribed in the rules and regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) B&ouml;rsi liikmele kohaldatakse reguleeritud turul osaleja kohta s&auml;testatut, kui k&auml;esolevast peat&uuml;kist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The provisions regarding regulated market participators shall also apply with respect to members of an exchange, unless otherwise prescribed in this Chapter. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 152. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 152. </inglise>
<eesti>Finantsriskide maandamine </eesti>
<inglise>Financial risk management </inglise>
<eesti>(1) B&ouml;rsikorraldaja aktsiakapital peab olema v&auml;hemalt 375 000 eurot. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The share capital of an operator of an exchange shall be at least 375 000 euro. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) B&ouml;rsikorraldaja omakapital peab vastama k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 125 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The owners' equity of an operator of an exchange shall meet the requirements prescribed in &sect; 125 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>2. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Isereguleerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Self-regulation </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 153. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 153. </inglise>
<eesti>B&ouml;rsi reglement </eesti>
<inglise>Rules and regulations of exchange </inglise>
<eesti>B&ouml;rsi reglemendis s&auml;testatakse t&auml;iendavalt turu reglemendis s&auml;testatule: </eesti>
<inglise>The rules and regulations of an exchange shall set out the following in addition to the provisions of the rules and regulations of the market: </inglise>
<eesti>1) v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite noteerimise ja selle l&otilde;petamise alused, tingimused ja kord; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the bases, conditions and procedure for the listing of securities and the termination thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) noteeritud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitendi p&otilde;hilised kohustused b&ouml;rsikorraldaja suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the principal obligations of the issuer of a listed security with respect to the operator of the exchange; </inglise>
<eesti>3) b&ouml;rsi liikmeks vastuv&otilde;tmise ja liikmestaatuse l&otilde;ppemise alused, tingimused ja kord; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the bases, conditions and procedure for the admission of persons as members of the exchange and the termination of member status; </inglise>
<eesti>4) b&ouml;rsi liikme p&otilde;hilised &otilde;igused ning kohustused b&ouml;rsikorraldaja, b&ouml;rsi teiste liikmete ja b&ouml;rsi liikme klientide v&otilde;i v&otilde;lausaldajate suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the principal rights and obligations of members of the exchange with respect to the operator of the exchange, other members of the exchange, and clients or creditors thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>5) b&ouml;rsi vahendusel hinnanoteeringute ja tehingukorralduste edastamise ning vastuv&otilde;tmise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the procedure for the forwarding and receipt of quotations and transaction orders via the exchange; </inglise>
<eesti>6) v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi noteerimist otsustava isiku, organi ja selle liikme &otilde;igused ning kohustused, samuti valimise v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;ramise alused, tingimused ja kord. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the rights and obligations of the person, body and member thereof deciding on the listing of a security, and the bases, conditions and procedure for the election or appointment thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>3. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 3 </inglise>
<eesti>B&ouml;rsi korraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of Exchange </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 154. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 154. </inglise>
<eesti>Noteerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Listing </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Noteerimine k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi b&ouml;rsile kauplemisele v&otilde;tmine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, listing is the admission of a security for trading on an exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>B&ouml;rsil kaubeldakse b&ouml;rsinimekirja arvatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega. </eesti>
<inglise>Trading on the exchange shall also be in securities included in the exchange list. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) B&ouml;rsikorraldaja v&otilde;imaldab b&ouml;rsil kaubelda &uuml;ksnes v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiga, mis on k&auml;esoleva seaduse, selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide ja vastava reglemendi kohaselt v&otilde;etud b&ouml;rsinimekirja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The operator of an exchange shall only permit trading on the exchange with securities which have been listed in the exchange list on the basis of this Act, legislation established on the basis thereof and the relevant rules and regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&auml;&auml;rtpaberi noteerimisele, noteerimise peatamisele ja l&otilde;petamisele kohaldatakse v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi turule kauplemisele v&otilde;tmise, kauplemise peatamise ja l&otilde;petamise kohta s&auml;testatut, kui k&auml;esolevast peat&uuml;kist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Unless otherwise provided in this Chapter, the provisions regarding admission of securities for trading on the market and regarding suspension and termination of the trading thereof shall apply to the listing of securities and to suspension and termination of the listing thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 155. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 155. </inglise>
<eesti>Noteerimise tingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Conditions of listing </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Noteerida v&otilde;ib ainult vabalt v&otilde;&otilde;randatavaid v&auml;&auml;rtpabereid, mille tunnused ja emitendid ning nende teod vastavad &otilde;igusaktides ja vastava b&ouml;rsi reglemendis s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Only freely transferable securities the characteristics of which and the issuers of which and their acts meet the conditions prescribed in legislation and the rules and regulations of the relevant exchange may be listed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Noteerimisel peab v&auml;&auml;rtpaber ja selle emitent vastama v&auml;hemalt rahandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon listing, the security and its issuer shall meet at least the requirements established by a regulation of the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud n&otilde;uetes s&auml;testatakse v&auml;hemalt: </eesti>
<inglise>These requirements shall set out at least the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) n&otilde;uded emitendile, kelle emiteeritud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi noteerimist taotletakse, sealhulgas n&otilde;uded emitendi &otilde;igusliku staatuse, kapitali, finantsseisundi ning juhtimisorganite, nende tegevuse ja t&auml;htaegade kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) requirements for the issuer of the security for which listing is applied for, including requirements regarding the legal status, capital and financial situation of the issuer and its directing bodies, their operations and the terms therefor; </inglise>
<eesti>2) n&otilde;uded v&auml;&auml;rtpaberile, mille noteerimist taotletakse, sealhulgas n&otilde;uded v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi &otilde;igusliku staatuse, vaba v&otilde;&otilde;randatavuse erisuste, avaliku pakkumisega seonduva, v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite jaotuse, samaliigiliste v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite noteerimise ning v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi vormi kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>2) requirements for the security for which listing is applied for, including requirements regarding its legal status, special rules for free transferability, public offering, distribution, listing of securities of the same type, and the form of the security; </inglise>
<eesti>3) n&otilde;uded v&auml;lisriigi emitendi emiteeritud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberile; </eesti>
<inglise>3) requirements for securities issued by foreign issuers; </inglise>
<eesti>4) muud n&otilde;uded, sealhulgas n&otilde;uded noteeritava v&otilde;lav&auml;&auml;rtpaberi minimaalv&auml;&auml;rtuse ja vahetusv&otilde;lakirja noteerimise tingimuste kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>4) other requirements, including requirements regarding the minimum value of listed debt securities and the conditions of listing convertible bonds. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 156. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 156. </inglise>
<eesti>Noteerimise otsustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Decision regarding listing </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Noteerimise otsustab b&ouml;rsikorraldaja vastav organ. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Decisions about listing shall be taken by the relevant body of the operator of the exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Noteerimiseks esitab taotleja vastava kirjaliku avalduse, noteerimisprospekti ning muud vastava b&ouml;rsi reglemendis etten&auml;htud andmed ja dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to listing to take place, the applicant shall submit a corresponding written application, the listing particulars and other information and documents prescribed in the rules and regulations of the relevant exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>B&ouml;rsikorraldaja teavitab avalduse esitamisest viivitamata inspektsiooni, edastades talle noteerimisprospekti. </eesti>
<inglise>The operator of the exchange shall immediately notify the Supervision Authority of the receipt of an application and forward the listing particulars to the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Noteerimine otsustatakse kuue kuu jooksul k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud avalduse ning andmete ja dokumentide esitamisest arvates, kui vastava b&ouml;rsi reglemendis ei ole s&auml;testatud l&uuml;hemat t&auml;htaega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A decision on listing shall be taken within six months as of submission of the application, information and documents specified in subsection (2) of this section, unless a shorter term is prescribed in the rules and regulations of the relevant exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 157. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 157. </inglise>
<eesti>Noteerimisprospekt </eesti>
<inglise>Listing particulars </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Noteerimisprospekt peab vastama k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides ning vastava b&ouml;rsi reglemendis s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Listing particulars shall meet the requirements provided for in this Act, legislation established on the basis thereof and the rules and regulations of the relevant exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Noteerimisprospektile kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse teises osas prospekti suhtes s&auml;testatut, kui k&auml;esolevast jaost ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Unless otherwise prescribed in this Division, the provisions of Part II of this Act regulating prospectuses shall apply with respect to listing particulars. </inglise>
<eesti>Noteerimisprospektile ei kohaldata k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 16 s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>The provisions of &sect; 16 of this Act shall not apply to listing particulars. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&auml;htudes k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 17 ja &sect; 22 l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatust ning emitendi ja noteeritavate v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite erisustest, v&otilde;ib rahandusminister oma m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestada: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Based on the provisions of &sect; 17 and subsection 22 (5) of this Act as well as the special nature of the issuer and the securities listed, the Minister of Finance may, by a regulation, establish: </inglise>
<eesti>1) erandid noteerimisprospekti avalikustamise ja registreerimise kohustuse suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise>1) exceptions regarding the obligation to disclose and register the listing particulars; </inglise>
<eesti>2) n&otilde;uded noteerimisprospekti ja selles esitatava teabe kohta, samuti erisused noteerimisprospektis avalikustatavate andmete koosseisu suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>2) requirements for the listing particulars and the information presented therein, and special rules applicable to the composition of information to be disclosed in the listing particulars. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Rahandusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud ulatuses v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud erandite ja erisuste rakendamise otsustada inspektsioon. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Within the scope established by a regulation of the Minister of Finance, the Supervision Authority may decide on the implementation of the exceptions and special rules specified in subsection (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 158. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 158. </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vitamise n&otilde;uete kohaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of compensation requirement </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 25-28 s&auml;testatut kohaldatakse noteerimisprospektile, arvestades, et kahju tekitajal on &otilde;igus kahju h&uuml;vitada, omandades b&ouml;rsil noteeritud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi kannatanult hinna eest, mis kannatanu noteeritud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi omandamiseks tasus, v&otilde;i kohe p&auml;rast v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi b&ouml;rsil noteerimist kehtinud m&uuml;&uuml;gihinna eest. </eesti>
<inglise>The provisions prescribed in &sect;&sect; 25-28 of this Act shall apply with respect to the listing particulars, taking into account the fact that the person who causes the damage has the right to compensate the damage by acquiring a security listed on the exchange from the person that sustained the damage for the price that the latter paid for the security or for the sales price of the security immediately after its listing on the exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 159. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 159. </inglise>
<eesti>Teabe edastamise ja avalikustamise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Obligation to communicate and disclose information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rahandusminister kehtestab oma m&auml;&auml;rusega: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Minister of Finance shall, by a regulation, establish: </inglise>
<eesti>1) miinimumloetelu andmetest, mida noteeritud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitent peab edastama b&ouml;rsikorraldajale avalikustamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a minimum list of information which the issuer of a listed security shall forward to the operator of the exchange for disclosure; </inglise>
<eesti>2) miinimumloetelu kohustustest, mida noteeritud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitent on seoses noteerimisega kohustatud t&auml;itma; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a minimum list of obligations which the issuer of a listed security shall perform in connection with the listing; </inglise>
<eesti>3) k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktides 1 ja 2 nimetatud andmete avalikustamise viisi ning kohustuste t&auml;itmise t&auml;htajad. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the manner of disclosing the information and the terms of performing the obligations specified in clauses 1) and 2) of this subsection. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 2 nimetatud loetelu peab sisaldama v&auml;hemalt kohustusi seoses: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The list specified in clause (1) 2) of this section shall contain at least obligations pertaining to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) uute v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite emiteerimisega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the issue of new securities; </inglise>
<eesti>2) investorite v&otilde;rdse kohtlemisega v&otilde;rdsetel asjaoludel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the equal treatment of investors in equal circumstances; </inglise>
<eesti>3) p&otilde;hikirja muutmise kavandamisega; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the intended amendment of the articles of association; </inglise>
<eesti>4) majandusaasta aruandega ja poolaasta vahearuannetega; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the annual report and semi-annual interim reports; </inglise>
<eesti>5) oluliste asjaolude ilmnemisega emitendi tegevuses; </eesti>
<inglise>5) significant circumstances arising in the operations of the issuer; </inglise>
<eesti>6) v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitest tulenevate &otilde;iguste muutmisega. </eesti>
<inglise>6) changes of rights arising from the securities. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) B&ouml;rsikorraldajal on &otilde;igus reglemendiga l&uuml;hendada rahandusministri kehtestatud teabe edastamise ja avalikustamise t&auml;htaegu nende emitentide suhtes, kelle v&auml;&auml;rtpabereid b&ouml;rsil noteeritakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The operator of an exchange has the right to establish in the rules and regulations a shorter term than that established by the Minister of Finance for the forwarding and disclosure of information with regard to issuers whose securities are listed on the exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>4. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 4 </inglise>
<eesti>B&ouml;rsij&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>Exchange Supervision </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 160. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 160. </inglise>
<eesti>B&ouml;rsil osaleja, b&ouml;rsi liikme ja emitendi suhtes lepinguliste &otilde;iguskaitsevahendite rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of contractual legal remedies with regard to participator in exchange, member of exchange and issuer </inglise>
<eesti>Kui b&ouml;rsi reglemendis on lisaks muudele n&otilde;uetele ette n&auml;htud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 161 s&auml;testatud lepinguliste &otilde;iguskaitsevahendite (edaspidi &otilde;iguskaitsevahendid) rakendamise v&otilde;imalus, siis k&auml;esoleva seaduse, selle alusel kehtestatud muude &otilde;igusaktide, samuti b&ouml;rsi reglemendi t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise v&otilde;i mitten&otilde;uetekohase t&auml;itmise korral on b&ouml;rsikorraldajal &otilde;igus rakendada b&ouml;rsil osaleja, b&ouml;rsi liikme ja noteeritud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitendi suhtes k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 161 s&auml;testatud &otilde;iguskaitsevahendeid. </eesti>
<inglise>If, in addition to other requirements, the rules and regulations of an exchange set out the possibility of applying contractual legal remedies provided for in &sect; 161 of this Act (hereinafter legal remedies), the operator of the exchange has the right to apply the legal remedies provided for in &sect; 161 of this Act with respect to a participator in the exchange, member of the exchange and issuer of a listed security for failure to perform or inadequate performance of this Act, other legislation established on the basis thereof or the rules and regulations of the exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 161. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 161. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskaitsevahendite liigid </eesti>
<inglise>Types of legal remedy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskaitsevahendid on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The legal remedies are as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) b&ouml;rsi reglemendis s&auml;testatud leppetrahv; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a contractual penalty as prescribed in the rules and regulations of the exchange; </inglise>
<eesti>2) b&ouml;rsil osaleja v&otilde;i b&ouml;rsi liikme staatusega kaasnevate k&otilde;igi v&otilde;i osa &otilde;iguste peatamine 3-30 p&auml;evaks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) full or partial suspension of the rights accompanying the status of participator or member of the exchange for a term ranging from three to thirty days; </inglise>
<eesti>3) b&ouml;rsil osaleja v&otilde;i b&ouml;rsi liikme staatuse l&otilde;petamine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) termination of the status of participator or member of the exchange; </inglise>
<eesti>4) v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi noteerimise v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiga kauplemise peatamine 3-30 p&auml;evaks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) suspension of the listing of or trading with a security for a term ranging from three to thirty days; </inglise>
<eesti>5) v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi noteerimise v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiga kauplemise l&otilde;petamine. </eesti>
<inglise>5) termination of the listing of or trading with a security. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskaitsevahendite menetlus, nende rakendamine ja vaidlustamise kord s&auml;testatakse b&ouml;rsi reglemendis. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The procedure for processing, applying, and appealing against legal remedies shall be prescribed in the rules and regulations of the exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 162. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 162. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskaitsevahendite rakendamine ja vaidlustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of legal remedies and right of appeal </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 161 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud &otilde;iguskaitsevahendite rakendamise peale kaebuse esitamine ei takista ega peata &otilde;iguskaitsevahendite rakendamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The filing of a complaint against the application of legal remedies provided for in subsection 161 (1) of this Act shall not hinder or suspend the execution of the legal remedies. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isikul, kelle suhtes rakendati &otilde;iguskaitsevahendit, on selles asjas &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda kohtusse v&otilde;i poolte kokkuleppel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 202 nimetatud vahekohtusse 10 p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates &otilde;iguskaitsevahendite rakendamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person in respect of whom a legal remedy is applied has the right of recourse to a court or, on the agreement of the parties, the arbitral tribunal specified in &sect; 202 of this Act in the matter within ten days as of the day of application of the legal remedy. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 163. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 163. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskaitsevahendite rakendamise avalikustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Disclosure of application of legal remedies </inglise>
<eesti>B&ouml;rsikorraldajal on &otilde;igus avalikustada &otilde;iguskaitsevahendite rakendamise fakt ja aeg, nende liik ja isiku nimi, kelle suhtes neid rakendati. </eesti>
<inglise>The operator of an exchange has the right to make public the fact and time of legal remedies being applied, their type and the name of the person in respect of whom the remedies are applied. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellisel juhul ei loeta b&ouml;rsikorraldaja poolt &otilde;iguskaitsevahendite rakendamise fakti, aja, &otilde;iguskaitsevahendite liigi ja isiku, kelle suhtes &otilde;iguskaitsevahendit rakendati, avalikustamist isiku au teotamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Such disclosure of the fact and time of legal remedies being applied and of the type thereof and of the name of the person in respect of whom the legal remedies are applied is not deemed as dishonouring a person. </inglise>
<eesti>19. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 19 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Takeover Bids </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 164. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 164. </inglise>
<eesti>Rakendamise ulatus </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva peat&uuml;ki s&auml;tted laienevad &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisele, mis tehakse h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;iguse omandamiseks Eestis registreeritud aktsiaseltsides, mille k&otilde;iki aktsiaid v&otilde;i teatud liiki aktsiaid noteeritakse Eesti b&ouml;rsil v&otilde;i nendega kaubeldakse Eesti turul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The provisions of this Chapter shall apply to takeover bids made to acquire voting rights in public limited companies which are registered in Estonia and of which all or a certain type of their shares are listed on an Estonian exchange or traded on an Estonian market. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolevas peat&uuml;kis t&auml;hendab aktsia k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 2 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1 ja 7 nimetatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberit, samuti muud &uuml;leantavat &otilde;igust h&auml;&auml;letamiseks aktsion&auml;ride &uuml;ldkoosolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Chapter, a share is a security specified in clauses 2 (1) 1) and 7) of this Act as well as any other transferable right for voting at a general meeting of shareholders. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 165. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 165. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Takeover bid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumine k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on avalik pakkumine Eesti b&ouml;rsil noteeritud aktsia v&otilde;i Eesti turul kaubeldava aktsia emitendi (edaspidi sihtemitent) aktsion&auml;ridele (edaspidi sihtisikud) nendelt aktsiate omandamiseks raha v&otilde;i b&ouml;rsil noteeritud v&otilde;i turul kaubeldavate v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, a takeover bid is a public offer made to the shareholders (hereinafter target persons) of the issuer (hereinafter target issuer) of a share listed on an Estonian exchange or traded on an Estonian market to acquire their shares in exchange for money or securities listed on the exchange or traded on the market. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumiseks ei ole sihtemitendi avalik pakkumine oma aktsion&auml;ridele sihtemitendi aktsiate omandamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A public offer made by the target issuer to its own shareholders to acquire the shares of the target issuer is not deemed to be a takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 166. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 166. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tegemise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Obligation to make takeover bid </inglise>
<eesti>Sihtemitendi &uuml;le valitseva m&otilde;ju otse v&otilde;i koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutsevate isikutega koos saanud isik on kohustatud 20 p&auml;eva jooksul valitseva m&otilde;ju saamisest arvates tegema v&auml;hemalt 28 p&auml;eva kestva &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise sihtemitendi k&otilde;igi aktsiate suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>A person who has gained dominant influence over the target issuer either directly or together with other persons acting in concert is required to make a takeover bid for all shares of the target issuer with a duration of at least for twenty-eight days within twenty days as of gaining dominant influence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 167. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 167. </inglise>
<eesti>Valitsev m&otilde;ju </eesti>
<inglise>Dominant influence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Valitsev m&otilde;ju on olukord, kus sihtemitent on kontrollitav &auml;ri&uuml;hing k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 10 l&otilde;ike 2 t&auml;henduses, kusjuures h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;iguse arvestamisel l&auml;htutakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 10 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Dominant influence is a situation where the target issuer is a controlled company within the meaning of subsection 10 (2) of this Act, whereupon voting rights are determined on the basis of the provisions of subsection 10 (1) this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus igal &uuml;ksikjuhul, hinnates igak&uuml;lgselt k&otilde;iki asjaolusid, m&auml;&auml;ratleda valitseva m&otilde;ju saamine, omamine, &uuml;leandmine, puudumine ja ulatus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority has the right to determine the gaining, holding, transfer, absence and scope of dominant influence in each individual case by carefully considering all the relevant circumstances. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 168. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 168. </inglise>
<eesti>Koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutsevad isikud </eesti>
<inglise>Persons acting in concert </inglise>
<eesti>Koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutsevad isikud k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on kontrollitav &auml;ri&uuml;hing, seda &auml;ri&uuml;hingut kontrolliv isik ja teised selle isiku poolt kontrollitavad &auml;ri&uuml;hingud (edaspidi seotud isikud) ning samuti isikud, kes tegutsevad koos &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumist tegeva isiku (edaspidi &uuml;lev&otilde;tja) v&otilde;i sihtemitendiga suulise v&otilde;i kirjaliku kokkuleppe alusel eesm&auml;rgiga kas saavutada, s&auml;ilitada v&otilde;i suurendada valitsevat m&otilde;ju sihtemitendi &uuml;le v&otilde;i nurjata &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumine. </eesti>
<inglise>For the purposes of this Act, persons acting in concert are a controlled company, a person controlling this company and other companies controlled by this person (hereinafter connected persons), and persons who act together with the person making the takeover bid (hereinafter offerer) or the target issuer on the basis of an oral or written agreement in order to gain, maintain or increase dominant influence over the target issuer or in order to frustrate the takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 169. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 169. </inglise>
<eesti>Inspektsiooni &uuml;lesanded </eesti>
<inglise>Functions of Supervision Authority </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioon kontrollib &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise vastavust &otilde;igusaktidele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Supervision Authority shall monitor the compliance of the takeover bid with legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioon koos vastava b&ouml;rsikorraldaja v&otilde;i korraldajaga teostab j&auml;relevalvet &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumiste &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority shall execute supervision over the takeover bid together with the relevant operator of an exchange or the relevant operator. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda &uuml;lev&otilde;tjalt ja sihtemitendilt teavet seoses &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Supervision Authority has the right to request information from the offerer and target issuer about the takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 170. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 170. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tja ja temaga seotud isikute kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of offerer and connected persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise korral peab &uuml;lev&otilde;tja samaliigiliste aktsiate omanikke kohtlema v&otilde;rdselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the case of a takeover bid, the offerer shall treat all owners of shares of the same type equally. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tja ja sihtemitent peavad andma sihtisikutele &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise informeeritud kaalumiseks olulist, &otilde;iget, t&auml;pset, t&auml;ielikku ja &uuml;hesugust teavet. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The offerer and the target issuer must provide the target persons with significant, correct, accurate, complete and identical information for informed consideration of the takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tja teeb &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise, v&auml;lja arvatud kohustuslik &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumine, selle l&auml;biviimiseks k&uuml;llaldaste finantsvahendite ja v&otilde;imaluste olemasolul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The offerer shall make a takeover bid, except a mandatory takeover bid, if it has sufficient financial resources and the means to carry out the takeover. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tjal ja temaga koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutseval isikul ei ole &otilde;igust teha sama sihtemitendi suhtes uut &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumist kuue kuu jooksul &uuml;lev&otilde;tja poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise t&auml;htaja (edaspidi &uuml;lev&otilde;tmist&auml;htaeg) m&ouml;&ouml;dumisest arvates, kui inspektsioon investorite kaitse eesm&auml;rgil v&otilde;i muul m&otilde;juval p&otilde;hjusel ei luba teha uut &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumist varem. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The offerer and a person acting in concert therewith do not have the right to make a new takeover bid with respect to the same target issuer within six months as of the expiry of the term of the takeover bid as determined by the offerer (hereinafter term of takeover bid), unless the Supervision Authority permits a new takeover bid to be made earlier in order to protect investors or for other justified reasons. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 171. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 171. </inglise>
<eesti>Sihtemitendi ja temaga seotud isikute kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of target issuer and connected persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Sihtemitendi tegevjuhtkonna, n&otilde;ukogu ja juhatuse liikmed peavad &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise korral l&auml;htuma sihtemitendi huvidest ega v&otilde;i takistada sihtisikutel kaaluda &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the case of a takeover bid, members of the management, management board and supervisory board of the target issuer shall be guided by the interests of the target issuer and shall not hinder the consideration of the takeover bid by target persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Sihtemitendi n&otilde;ukogu koostab ning avalikustab oma arvamuse &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The supervisory board of the target issuer shall formulate and disclose its opinion regarding the takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise avalikustamisest kuni &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tulemuse avalikustamiseni ei v&otilde;i sihtemitent teha sihtemitendi varasid v&otilde;i kohustusi oluliselt muutvaid tehinguid, kui sihtemitendi aktsion&auml;ride &uuml;ldkoosolek ei anna n&otilde;usolekut selliste tehingute tegemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) During the period between the takeover bid and the results of the takeover bid being made public, the target issuer shall not conduct any transactions which would significantly change the assets or liabilities of the target issuer, unless the general meeting of the shareholders of the target issuer grants authorisation for such transactions to be conducted. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 172. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 172. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tja, sihtemitendi ja nendega koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutsevate isikute kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of offerer, target issuer and persons acting in concert therewith </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tja, sihtemitent ja nendega koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutsevad isikud on kohustatud &uuml;lev&otilde;tmist&auml;htajal hoiduma tegudest, mis p&otilde;hjustavad sihtemitendi aktsiate ebahariliku hinnak&otilde;ikumise. </eesti>
<inglise>The offerer, target issuer and persons acting in concert therewith are required to refrain from activities which would cause unusual fluctuations in the price of the shares of the target issuer during the term of a takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 173. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 173. </inglise>
<eesti>Erandid kohustuslikule &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisele </eesti>
<inglise>Exceptions to mandatory takeover bid </inglise>
<eesti>Sihtemitendi &uuml;le valitseva m&otilde;ju saanud isiku vastava kirjaliku avalduse alusel on inspektsioonil &otilde;igus teha erand kohustusliku &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise n&otilde;udest j&auml;rgneva asjaolu esinemisel: </eesti>
<inglise>On the basis of a relevant written application from the person who gains dominant influence over the target issuer, the Supervision Authority has the right to grant an exception to the requirement for a mandatory takeover bid if one of the following circumstances exists: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &auml;ri&uuml;hing sai sihtemitendi &uuml;le valitseva m&otilde;ju temaga samasse kontserni kuuluvalt &uuml;hingult ning p&auml;rast valitseva m&otilde;ju saamist kuulub &auml;ri&uuml;hing j&auml;tkuvalt samasse kontserni; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the company acquired dominant influence over the target issuer from another company belonging to the same group as the company and the company continues to belong to the same group thereafter; </inglise>
<eesti>2) valitsev m&otilde;ju saadi sihtemitendi aktsiakapitali v&auml;hendamise tulemusena; </eesti>
<inglise>2) dominant influence was gained reducing the share capital of the target issuer; </inglise>
<eesti>3) valitsev m&otilde;ju saadi &uuml;hinemise v&otilde;i jagunemise l&auml;biviimiseks enne &uuml;hinemis- v&otilde;i jagunemislepingu heakskiitmist &uuml;hinevate &uuml;hingute poolt v&otilde;i jaguneva sihtemitendi aktsion&auml;ride &uuml;ldkoosoleku poolt tingimusel, et sihtemitendi &uuml;hinemise v&otilde;i jagunemise t&otilde;ttu isiku v&otilde;i koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutsevate isikute valitsev m&otilde;ju l&otilde;peb; </eesti>
<inglise>3) dominant influence was gained for the purpose of carrying out a merger or division prior to approval of the merger or division agreement by the merging companies or by the general meeting of the shareholders of the target issuer being divided, on the condition that, as a result of the merger or division of the target issuer, the dominant influence of the person or persons acting in concert shall be terminated; </inglise>
<eesti>4) aktsiad omandati l&uuml;hikeseks t&auml;htajaks edasise v&otilde;&otilde;randamise eesm&auml;rgil, kuid sellega kaasnes valitseva m&otilde;ju omandamine, sealhulgas v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite omandamisel kauplemisportfelli, aktsiate emiteerimise tagamisel ja aktsiate omandamisel emitendi poolt; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the shares were acquired for a short term for the purpose of further transfer but the acquisition resulted in a dominant influence, including the acquisition of securities for a trading portfolio, underwriting of a share issue and acquisition of the shares by the issuer; </inglise>
<eesti>5) valitsev m&otilde;ju saadi eelneva kavatsuseta saada valitsev m&otilde;ju sihtemitendi &uuml;le ning valitseva m&otilde;ju saaja loobub sellest kolmanda isiku kasuks, kes ei ole temaga koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutsev isik, 10 t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates valitseva m&otilde;ju saamisest, tingimusel, et nimetatud t&auml;htaja jooksul ei toimu sihtemitendi aktsion&auml;ride &uuml;ldkoosolekut; </eesti>
<inglise>5) dominant influence was gained without any prior intention to gain dominant influence over the target issuer, and the acquirer of dominant influence surrenders it to a third party who is not a person acting in concert therewith within ten working days as of gaining dominant influence, on the condition that a general meeting of the shareholders of the target issuer is not held during this term; </inglise>
<eesti>6) aktsion&auml;r sai valitseva m&otilde;ju temale seaduse kohaselt kuulunud ning mitte teistelt isikutelt omandatud aktsiate m&auml;rkimisees&otilde;iguste teostamise t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>6) a shareholder gained dominant influence by exercising a pre-emptive right to subscribe to shares which arises from law and was not acquired from other persons. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 174. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 174. </inglise>
<eesti>Ostuhind &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumises </eesti>
<inglise>Purchase price in takeover bid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise esemeks olevate eriliigiliste aktsiate &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumises kajastatud ostuhindade suhe peab olema vastavuses aktsiatest tulenevate &otilde;iguste ja kohustustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The ratio of the purchase prices of shares of different type which serve as the object of a takeover bid shall be in proportion to the rights and obligations deriving from the shares. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohustusliku &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise esemeks oleva aktsia kohustuslikus &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumises kajastatud ostuhind peab olema &otilde;iglane. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The purchase price of a share which serves as the object of a mandatory takeover bid and is stated in the mandatory takeover bid shall be fair. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 175. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 175. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise koosk&otilde;lastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Approval of takeover bid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tja peab &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise koosk&otilde;lastama inspektsiooniga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The offerer shall obtain approval for the takeover bid from the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioon ei koosk&otilde;lasta &otilde;igusaktiga vastuolus olevat &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority shall not approve a takeover bid which violates legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Inspektsioon otsustab &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise koosk&otilde;lastamise v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 173 nimetatud erandi tegemise 15 p&auml;eva jooksul &uuml;lev&otilde;tjalt vastava kirjaliku avalduse saamisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Supervision Authority shall make a decision on the approval of a takeover bid or the grant of the exception specified in &sect; 173 of this Act within fifteen days as of receiving a corresponding written application from the offerer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 176. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 176. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise vaidlustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Right to contest takeover bid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Sihtisik v&otilde;i muu &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisega seotud isik ei v&otilde;i n&otilde;uda &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise t&uuml;histamist v&otilde;i selle tingimuste muutmist p&auml;rast selle koosk&otilde;lastamist inspektsiooni poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A target person or other person connected with the takeover bid may not demand cancellation of the takeover bid or modification of the conditions thereof after the Supervision Authority has approved the takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Sihtisik v&otilde;i muu &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisega seotud isik v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisega tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A target person or other person connected with the takeover bid may demand compensation of damage caused by the takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud n&otilde;ude aegumist&auml;htaeg on &uuml;ks aasta, arvates &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise koosk&otilde;lastamisest inspektsiooni poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The limitation period of a claim specified in subsection (2) of this section shall be one year as of approval of the takeover bid by the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 177. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 177. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise avalikustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Disclosure of takeover bid </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tja avalikustab vastava turu korraldaja veebilehel &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisprospekti, mis sisaldab t&auml;ies mahus &otilde;iget, t&auml;pset ja t&auml;ielikku teavet &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>The offerer shall publish the prospectus for the takeover bid on the website of the operator of the relevant market and the prospectus shall contain accurate, precise and complete information regarding the takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 178. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 178. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tulemused </eesti>
<inglise>Results of takeover bid </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rast &uuml;lev&otilde;tmist&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist avalikustab &uuml;lev&otilde;tja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 34 s&auml;testatud korras &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tulemused. </eesti>
<inglise>The offerer shall make public the results of the takeover bid after expiry of the term of the takeover bid pursuant to the procedure prescribed in &sect; 34 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 179. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 179. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmist&auml;htaja pikendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Extension of term of takeover bid </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise edasil&uuml;kkavate tingimuste saabumisel pikendab &uuml;lev&otilde;tja &uuml;lev&otilde;tmist&auml;htaega nende sihtisikute suhtes, kes ei olnud &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise raames teinud &uuml;lev&otilde;tjale ettepanekut v&otilde;i oferti aktsiate v&otilde;&otilde;randamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>If circumstances emerge which postpone the takeover bid, the offerer shall extend the term of the takeover bid with respect to these target persons who have not, within the framework of the takeover bid, made a proposal or an offer to the offerer to transfer the shares. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 180. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 180. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepingust taganemine </eesti>
<inglise>Withdrawal from contract </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise raames aktsia v&otilde;&otilde;randamiseks ettepaneku v&otilde;i oferdi teinud isikul ja ettepaneku v&otilde;i oferdi aktseptinud sihtisikul on k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud juhtudel ning korras &otilde;igus ettepanek v&otilde;i ofert tagasi v&otilde;tta ja lepingust taganeda. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the cases and pursuant to the procedure prescribed in this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof, a person who makes a proposal or an offer for the transfer of a share within the framework of a takeover bid and the target person who accepts the proposal or the offer have the right to withdraw from the offer or proposal and to withdraw from the agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise raames aktsia v&otilde;&otilde;randamiseks lepingu s&otilde;lminud sihtisikul on &otilde;igus &uuml;les &ouml;elda v&otilde;i taganeda s&otilde;lmitud ja veel t&auml;itmata v&otilde;&otilde;randamislepingust v&otilde;i n&otilde;uda t&auml;idetud v&otilde;&otilde;randamislepingu j&auml;rgi &uuml;leantu ning saadu tagastamist, selle v&otilde;imatuse korral aga kahju h&uuml;vitamist rahas k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud juhtudel ning korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the cases and pursuant to the procedure prescribed in this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof, a target person who enters into a contract for the transfer of a share within the framework of a takeover bid has the right to cancel or withdraw from a transfer contract which has been entered into but not yet executed or to demand the return of that which has been delivered or received on the basis of a transfer contract which has already been executed or, in the event this is impossible, to demand compensation for damage in money. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tjal ei ole sellisel juhul &otilde;igust esitada sihtisiku vastu n&otilde;uet kahju h&uuml;vitamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>In this case, the offerer does not have the right to file a claim against the target person for compensation of damage. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 181. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 181. </inglise>
<eesti>V&otilde;istlev &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Competitive takeover bid </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise esemeks olevate aktsiate suhtes teise &uuml;lev&otilde;tja poolt tehtava &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise (v&otilde;istlev pakkumine) korral on sihtisikul &otilde;igus valida &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumiste vahel ning selleks esialgse &uuml;lev&otilde;tmist&auml;htaja jooksul: </eesti>
<inglise>In the event another offerer makes a takeover bid with respect to the shares which are the object of the takeover bid (a competitive takeover bid), the target person has the right to choose between the offers and, in order to do so, to do the following during the term of the original takeover bid: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tagasi v&otilde;tta esialgse &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise raames aktsia v&otilde;&otilde;randamiseks &uuml;lev&otilde;tjale tehtud ettepanek; </eesti>
<inglise>1) withdraw the proposal made to the offerer, within the framework of the original takeover bid, to transfer the share; </inglise>
<eesti>2) taganeda &uuml;lev&otilde;tjaga esialgse &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise raames s&otilde;lmitud aktsia v&otilde;&otilde;randamislepingust. </eesti>
<inglise>2) withdraw from the agreement to transfer the shares entered into within the framework of the original takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 182. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 182. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igusvastase &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tagaj&auml;rjed </eesti>
<inglise>Consequences of illegal takeover bid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isiku poolt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 166 s&auml;testatud kohustuse rikkumisel, kui isikule ei olnud antud &otilde;igust loobuda kohustusliku &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tegemisest vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 173, v&otilde;i &sect; 175 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud kohustuse rikkumisel, ei saa isik kuni rikkumise l&otilde;ppemiseni teostada h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;igusi sihtemitendis ning neid h&auml;&auml;li ei arvata sihtemitendi &uuml;ldkoosoleku kvoorumisse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a person violates the obligation prescribed in &sect; 166 of this Act but the person is not granted the right to withdraw from making a mandatory takeover bid in accordance with &sect; 173 of this Act or if a person violates the obligation prescribed in subsection 175 (1) of this Act, the person may not exercise voting rights in the target issuer and these votes shall not be included in the quorum of the general meeting of the target issuer until such time as the violation is eliminated. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus teha Eesti v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite keskregistri pidajale viivitamatuks t&auml;itmiseks kohustuslik ettekirjutus kuni 20 p&auml;evaks keelata &uuml;lev&otilde;tja ja temaga koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutseva isiku v&auml;&auml;rtpaberikontol olevate v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite kasutamine ja k&auml;sutamine &otilde;igusvastase &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tegemise korral v&otilde;i muu &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisega sarnase pakkumise sihtemitendi aktsion&auml;ridele k&auml;ttesaadavaks tegemise korral v&otilde;i &uuml;lev&otilde;tja ja temaga koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutseva isiku poolt muude k&auml;esoleva seadusega v&otilde;i selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega vastuolus olevate tegude tegemise korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority has the right to issue a mandatory precept to the registrar of the Estonian Central Register of Securities for immediate execution to prohibit, for a term of up to twenty days, the use and disposal of securities in a securities account held by an offerer or a person acting in concert therewith in the event that an illegal takeover bid is made or that another bid, similar to a takeover bid, is made available to the shareholders of the target issuer or that the offerer and a person acting in concert therewith performs other acts which are in violation of this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 183. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 183. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise reeglid </eesti>
<inglise>Rules of takeover bids </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rahandusminister kehtestab oma m&auml;&auml;rusega, l&auml;htudes k&auml;esolevas seaduses toodud p&otilde;him&otilde;tetest, t&auml;psemad n&otilde;uded &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisele ja sellega seotud asjaoludele (edaspidi &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisreeglid). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Based on the principles set out in this Act, the Minister of Finance shall, by a regulation, establish more specific requirements for a takeover bid and the circumstances related thereto (hereinafter the rules of a takeover bid). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisreeglites s&auml;testatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The rules of a takeover bid shall prescribe the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise esemeks oleva aktsia &otilde;iglase ostuhinna m&auml;&auml;ratlemise ja tasumise kriteeriumid ning menetlus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the criteria and procedure for determining a fair purchase price for the share which serves as the object of the takeover bid and the payment thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise maksimumt&auml;htaeg ja &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tingimuslikkuse kriteeriumid, </eesti>
<inglise>2) the maximum term of the takeover bid and the conditionality criteria of the takeover bid; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise muutmise tingimused ja menetlus; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the conditions and procedure for amending the takeover bid; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise inspektsiooniga koosk&otilde;lastamise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the procedure for co-ordination of the takeover bid with the Supervision Authority; </inglise>
<eesti>5) &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise kohta teabe avalikustamise ja edastamise kriteeriumid ja menetlus; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the criteria and procedure for disclosing and communicating information regarding the takeover bid; </inglise>
<eesti>6) n&otilde;uded &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise k&otilde;iki tingimusi kajastava &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisprospekti sisule ja vormile; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the requirements as to the contents and form of the prospectus containing all the terms and conditions of the takeover bid; </inglise>
<eesti>7) &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tulemuste avalikustamise kriteeriumid ja menetlus; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the criteria and procedure for publication of the results of the takeover bid; </inglise>
<eesti>8) &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise esemeks olnud aktsiate jaotamise kriteeriumid ja menetlus &uuml;lev&otilde;tjale; </eesti>
<inglise>8) the criteria and procedure for distribution of the shares serving as the object of the takeover bid to the offerer; </inglise>
<eesti>9) &uuml;lev&otilde;tja kohustused tema poolt &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise esemeks olnud aktsia omandamisel sihtisikute suhtes soodsamatel tingimustel, v&otilde;rreldes &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumises tooduga; </eesti>
<inglise>9) the obligations of the offerer when acquiring the shares serving as the object of the takeover bid on more favourable conditions with respect to the target persons than those set out in the takeover bid; </inglise>
<eesti>10) n&otilde;uded sihtemitendi n&otilde;ukogu arvamuse sisule ning vormile &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise ja sellega seonduvate asjaolude kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>10) the requirements as to the contents and form of the opinion of the supervisory board of the target issuer regarding the takeover bid and related circumstances; </inglise>
<eesti>11) &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tegemata j&auml;tmisele v&otilde;i nurjumisele suunatud sihtemitendi v&otilde;i sihtisiku &otilde;igustamatute kaitsev&otilde;tete tunnused; </eesti>
<inglise>11) the nature of inappropriate protection measures taken by the target issuer or target person with the aim of not making the takeover bid or of defeating the takeover bid; </inglise>
<eesti>12) v&otilde;istlevale &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisele rakendatavad p&otilde;him&otilde;tted ja kehtivad s&auml;tted ning v&otilde;istleva &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise m&otilde;ju esialgsele pakkumisele; </eesti>
<inglise>12) the principles and valid provisions applicable to a competitive takeover bid and the impact of a competitive takeover bid on the original bid; </inglise>
<eesti>13) inspektsiooni &otilde;iguste ja kohustuste ulatus &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise avalikustamisele eelneva ja muu &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisega seotud j&auml;relevalve teostamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>13) the scope of the rights and obligations of the Supervision Authority in exercising supervision prior to the takeover bid being made public and supervision related to the takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisreeglites v&otilde;ib vajadusel ette n&auml;ha: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If necessary, the rules of a takeover bid may also prescribe: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kohustusliku &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise t&auml;psemad tunnused ja erakorralise asjaolu t&auml;psemad tunnused, mille puhul isikul on inspektsiooni n&otilde;usolekul &otilde;igus loobuda kohustusliku &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tegemisest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) more specific features of a mandatory takeover bid and more specific features of the extraordinary circumstances in the case of which a person has the right, with the approval of the Supervision Authority, to withdraw from making a mandatory takeover bid; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise raames tehtud ettepanekute tagasiv&otilde;tmise ning s&otilde;lmitud lepingutest taganemise menetlus. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the procedure to withdraw a proposal made within the framework of the takeover bid and to withdraw from an agreement entered into. </inglise>
<eesti>20. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 20 </inglise>
<eesti>Olulise osaluse omandamine turul </eesti>
<inglise>Acquisition of Qualifying Holding on Market </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 184. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 184. </inglise>
<eesti>Peat&uuml;ki kohaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of Chapter </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas peat&uuml;kis s&auml;testatut kohaldatakse Eesti turule kauplemisele v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i Eesti b&ouml;rsil noteeritud aktsiaid emiteerinud Eestis registreeritud aktsiaseltsides (edaspidi k&auml;esolevas peat&uuml;kis aktsiaselts) osaluse omandamisele ja v&otilde;&otilde;randamisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The provisions of this Chapter shall apply to the acquisition and transfer of holdings in public limited companies registered in Estonia (hereinafter in this Chapter public limited companies) which have issued shares that have been admitted for trading on an Estonian market or listed on an Estonian exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Aktsiatega esindatud h&auml;&auml;lte saamiseks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 185 l&otilde;ike 1 t&auml;henduses loetakse ka vahetusv&otilde;lakirja vahetamist h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;igust andvaks aktsiaks, m&auml;rkimist&otilde;endis dokumenteeritud &otilde;igust omandada aktsiatest tulenev h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;igus aktsiate saamisel, eelisaktsia omaniku poolt h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;iguse omandamist ja h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;igust andva aktsia alusel v&auml;ljaantud selle aktsia saamise &otilde;iguse omandamist, mille teostamine s&otilde;ltub &uuml;ksnes omandajast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of subsection 185 (1) of this Act, the acquisition of votes represented by shares also includes the exchange of a convertible bond for a share granting voting rights, the right to acquire voting rights arising from shares stated in the certificate of subscription upon the acquisition of such shares, the acquisition of voting rights by an owner of preferred shares and the acquisition of the right to acquire a share granting voting rights, issued on the basis of the share, if the exercise of such right depends solely on the acquirer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 185. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 185. </inglise>
<eesti>Teatamiskohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Notification obligation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Iga&uuml;ks, kes otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt isiklikult v&otilde;i koos koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutsevate isikutega omandab aktsiaseltsis olulise osaluse v&otilde;i suurendab seda &uuml;le 1/5, 1/3, 1/2 v&otilde;i 2/3 k&otilde;igist nimetatud aktsiaseltsi emiteeritud aktsiatega esindatud h&auml;&auml;ltest, peab tema poolt omatavate ja kontrollitavate h&auml;&auml;lte arvust viivitamata teatama sellele aktsiaseltsile ning selle aktsiaseltsi aktsiaraamatu pidajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Everyone who either directly or indirectly, whether individually or together with persons acting in concert, acquires a qualifying holding in a public limited company or increases such holding to more than 1/5, 1/3, 1/2 or 2/3 of all the votes represented by shares of the public limited company shall immediately notify the public limited company and the person maintaining the share register thereof, stating the number of votes owned and controlled thereby. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Iga&uuml;ks, kelle otsene v&otilde;i kaudne osalus isiklikult v&otilde;i koos koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutsevate isikutega langeb alla k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetud m&auml;&auml;ra, peab iga kord sellest ja tema poolt omatava ja kontrollitava osaluse suurusest aktsiaseltsis viivitamata teatama sellele aktsiaseltsile ning selle aktsiaseltsi aktsiaraamatu pidajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Everyone whose direct or indirect holding, whether held individually or together with persons acting in concert, falls below one of the rates specified in subsection (1) of this section shall, on each such occasion, immediately notify the public limited company and the person maintaining the share register thereof, stating the size of the holding in the public limited company owned and controlled thereby. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 186. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 186. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalikustamiskohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Disclosure obligation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Aktsiaseltsi aktsiaraamatu pidaja edastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 185 kohaselt saadud teabe viivitamata vastavale korraldajale v&otilde;i b&ouml;rsikorraldajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The person maintaining the share register of the public limited company shall immediately communicate information received pursuant to &sect; 185 of this Act to the relevant operator or operator of an exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korraldaja ja b&ouml;rsikorraldaja avalikustavad aktsiaraamatu pidajalt saadud teabe viivitamata oma veebilehel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The operator or operator of an exchange shall immediately make public information received from the person maintaining the share register on their website. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 187. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 187. </inglise>
<eesti>Erisus </eesti>
<inglise>Special rule </inglise>
<eesti>Aktsiaseltsile, kelle aktsiad on b&ouml;rsil noteeritud, kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 185 ja 186 s&auml;testatut ka 1/20 suurusega osaluse omandamisel v&otilde;i selle v&auml;henemisel. </eesti>
<inglise>The provisions of &sect;&sect; 185 and 186 of this Act shall also apply to a public limited company whose shares are listed on the exchange upon the acquisition or reduction of a holding in the size of 1/20. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 188. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 188. </inglise>
<eesti>Erand </eesti>
<inglise>Exception </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioonil on isiku kirjaliku p&otilde;hjendatud taotluse alusel &otilde;igus teha erand k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 185 ja 187 rakendamisest taotleja suhtes, kui rakendamine tooks kaasa ohu Eesti riiklikule julgeolekule, avalikule korrale, turu korrap&auml;rasele toimimisele v&otilde;i kui rakendamisega kaasneks investorite huvide oluline kahjustamine v&otilde;i muu erakorraline asjaolu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) On the basis of a justified written application from a person, the Supervision Authority has the right to grant an exception from the provisions of &sect;&sect; 185 and 187 of this Act with respect to an applicant if the application of &sect;&sect; 185 and 187 would entail a danger to Estonian national security, law and order or the regular operation of the market, considerable damage to the interests of investors or other extraordinary circumstances. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui inspektsioon ei ole erandi tegemist otsustanud seitsme p&auml;eva jooksul k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud taotluse saamisest arvates, loetakse, et inspektsioon erandit ei tee. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the Supervision Authority fails to decide on the grant of an exception within seven days as of receipt of an application specified in subsection (1) of this section, the Supervision Authority is deemed to have refused to grant the exception. </inglise>
<eesti>Erandi tegemata j&auml;tmist ei ole inspektsioon kohustatud p&otilde;hjendama. </eesti>
<inglise>The Supervision Authority need not justify its refusal to grant exception. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Rahandusminister v&otilde;ib kehtestada oma m&auml;&auml;rusega erandi andmise otsustamiseks vajaliku teabe loetelu ja taotluse l&auml;bivaatamise korra. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Minister of Finance may, by a regulation, establish a list of information necessary to make a decision on the grant of exception and the procedure for reviewing applications. </inglise>
<eesti>21. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 21 </inglise>
<eesti>Siseteabe alusel tehingute tegemise ja turuga manipuleerimise keelamine </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition on Conduct of Transactions and Manipulation of Market on Basis of Inside Information </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 189. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 189. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva peat&uuml;ki kohaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of this Chapter </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas peat&uuml;kis s&auml;testatut ei kohaldata tehingutele, mida Eesti Vabariik, Eesti Pank v&otilde;i nende nimel tegutsev isik v&otilde;i asutus on teinud seoses raha-, valuutakursi- v&otilde;i riigi v&otilde;lahalduspoliitikaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The provisions of this Chapter shall not apply to transactions conducted by the Republic of Estonia, the Bank of Estonia or a person or agency acting in their name in connection with monetary policy, exchange rate policy or state debt management policy. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolevas peat&uuml;kis v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite kohta s&auml;testatut kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 2 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-3 nimetatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite ning nende hoidmistunnistuste suhtes, samuti tuletisv&auml;&auml;rtpaberite suhtes, mille alusvaraks on eelnimetatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The provisions of this Chapter regarding securities shall apply to securities specified in clauses 2 (1) 1) -3) of this Act and their depositary receipts, as well as derivative instruments the underlying assets of which are the securities mentioned above. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esolevas peat&uuml;kis s&auml;testatut kohaldatakse tehingutele, mis on tehtud Eestis v&otilde;i kus tehingu &uuml;heks pooleks v&otilde;i tehingu poole esindajaks on Eesti isik ja mis on tehtud Eesti turul kaubeldava v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiga v&otilde;i tuletisv&auml;&auml;rtpaberiga, millega Eesti turul ei kaubelda, kuid mille alusvaraks on Eesti turul kaubeldav v&auml;&auml;rtpaber. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The provisions of this Chapter shall apply to transactions which are conducted in Estonia or in which one party to the transaction or a representative thereof is the Republic of Estonia and which are conducted with a security traded on an Estonian market or with a derivative instrument which is not traded on an Estonian market, but whose underlying asset is a security traded on an Estonian market. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva peat&uuml;ki t&auml;henduses loetakse v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiga kauplemiseks Eesti turul ka olukord, kus avalikustatud on isiku poolt Eesti turu korraldajale esitatud taotlus alustada selle v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiga kauplemist turul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) For the purposes of this Chapter, a situation where an application filed by a person with an operator of an Estonian market for the commencement of trading with a security on the market has been disclosed is also deemed to be trading with securities on an Estonian market. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 190. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 190. </inglise>
<eesti>Siseteave </eesti>
<inglise>Inside information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Siseteave k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on avalikustamata teave, mis puudutab otseselt v&auml;&auml;rtpaberit, millega turul kaubeldakse, v&otilde;i sellise v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitenti ja mis avalikustatuna t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt v&otilde;ib oluliselt m&otilde;jutada v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi hinda v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, inside information is undisclosed information pertaining directly to a security traded on the market or to the issuer of such a security and which, if disclosed, would probably have a significant effect on the price or value of the security. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Siseteabeks ei loeta eranditult avalikustatud teabe alusel teostatud anal&uuml;&uuml;si, kokkuv&otilde;tteid ja muid materjale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Analyses, summaries and other materials produced exclusively on the basis of disclosed information are not deemed to be inside information. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 191. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 191. </inglise>
<eesti>Siseteabe alusel tehingu tegemise keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition on conduct of transaction on basis of inside information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Insaider k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on isik, kes v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitendi t&auml;isosanikuna, juhtimis- v&otilde;i j&auml;relevalveorgani liikmena, osaluse t&otilde;ttu v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitendis v&otilde;i oma t&ouml;&ouml;, elukutse v&otilde;i kohustuste t&otilde;ttu omab ligip&auml;&auml;su siseteabele ja valdab seda. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, an insider is a person who, by reason of being a full partner or a member of the management or supervisory body of the issuer of a security due to his or her holding in the issuer of a security or his or her work, profession or duties, has access to inside information and is in possession thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud isik on &auml;ri&uuml;hing v&otilde;i muu juriidiline isik v&otilde;i asutus, siis on insaideriks f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik, kes v&otilde;tab osa tehingu tegemise otsuse langetamisest nimetatud juriidilise isiku arvel ja valdab seda siseteavet. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a person specified in subsection (1) of this section is a company or other legal person or agency, the natural person who participates in making the decision to conduct the transaction for the account of the above-mentioned legal person and who is in possession of such inside information is deemed to be an insider. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Insaideriks loetakse ka kolmandaid isikuid, kes omavad siseteavet, mille k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud isik on talle otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt avaldanud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A third party which is in possession of inside information which has been disclosed directly or indirectly to the person by a person specified in subsection (1) of this section is also deemed to be an insider. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Insaider ei v&otilde;i otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt omandada ega v&otilde;&otilde;randada oma arvel, kolmanda isiku arvel v&otilde;i nimel v&auml;&auml;rtpaberit, mida talle teada olev siseteave puudutab. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An insider may not directly or indirectly acquire or transfer, either for his or her own account or for the account or in the name of a third party, any security to which inside information known to him or her pertains. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 192. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 192. </inglise>
<eesti>Siseteabe avaldamise keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition on disclosure of inside information </inglise>
<eesti>Siseteavet on keelatud avaldada kolmandatele isikutele, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui see on vajalik t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i ametikohustuste tavap&auml;raseks t&auml;itmiseks v&otilde;i selle avaldamise kohustus on ette n&auml;htud &otilde;igusaktiga v&otilde;i teave avaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 142 ja 159 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>It is prohibited to disclose inside information to any third parties, unless disclosure is necessary to perform ordinary duties of employment or official duties or an obligation to disclose the information is prescribed by legislation or the information is disclosed on the basis of &sect;&sect; 142 or 159 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 193. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 193. </inglise>
<eesti>Keeld anda soovitusi </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition on giving of recommendations </inglise>
<eesti>Insaideril on keelatud anda kolmandatele isikutele soovitusi k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 189 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite, mille kohta ta omab siseteavet, omandamiseks v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randamiseks v&otilde;i m&otilde;jutada neid v&auml;&auml;rtpabereid omandama v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randama. </eesti>
<inglise>It is prohibited for an insider to give recommendations to third parties to acquire or transfer securities specified in subsection 189 (3) of this Act concerning which he or she has inside information or to influence third parties to acquire or transfer such securities. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 194. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 194. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku esindaja vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of representative of legal person </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 191, 192 v&otilde;i 193 s&auml;testatu rikkumise korral loetakse vastavat keeldu rikkunuks ka siseteavet omav juriidilise isiku f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust esindaja, kes andis n&otilde;usoleku &sect;-des 191, 192 v&otilde;i 193 s&auml;testatud teo tegemiseks v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i k&auml;sunduslepingu alusel v&otilde;i muul alusel esindas juriidilist isikut teo tegemisel, millega rikuti &sect;-des 191, 192 v&otilde;i 193 s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>In the event of a violation of the provisions of &sect;&sect; 191, 192 or 193 of this Act, the relevant prohibition is also deemed to have been violated by the legal person's representative who is a natural person, who is in possession of inside information and who granted his or her consent to the acts prescribed in &sect;&sect; 191, 192 or 193 of this Act being performed or who represented the legal person in performing acts violating the provisions of &sect;&sect; 191, 192 or 193 of this Act on the basis of an employment contract, authorisation agreement or on any other grounds. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 195. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 195. </inglise>
<eesti>Sisereeglite kehtestamise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Obligation to establish internal rules </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Emitent, kelle v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiga turul kaubeldakse, peab kehtestama sisereeglid, mis reguleerivad siseteabe hoidmist ja selle avaldamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An issuer whose securities are traded on a market shall establish internal rules to regulate the maintenance of the confidentiality of and disclosure of inside information. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Emitent, kelle v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiga turul kaubeldakse, samuti tema emaettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja on kohustatud kehtestama sisereeglid oma t&auml;isosanikele, n&otilde;ukogu ja juhatuse liikmetele ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele tehingute tegemiseks oma arvel v&otilde;i kolmandate isikute arvel v&otilde;i nimel nimetatud emitendi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An issuer whose securities are traded on a market, and the parent company or subsidiary thereof, are required to establish internal rules to regulate transactions conducted with securities of the issuer by their full partners, members of their supervisory and management boards and their employees for their own account or for the account or in the name of third parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 nimetatud sisereeglid on kohustatud kehtestama ka muu isik v&otilde;i asutus, sealhulgas inspektsioon, v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutseline osaline ja audiitor&uuml;hing, kes oma t&ouml;&ouml;- ja kutse&uuml;lesannete v&otilde;i kohustuste t&otilde;ttu omab regulaarselt juurdep&auml;&auml;su siseteabele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Other persons or agencies, including the Supervision Authority, professional securities market participants and auditors companies, which have regular access to inside information due to their duties of employment or their official duties or obligations are also required to establish internal rules specified in subsections (1) and (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Inspektsioonile esitatakse tema n&otilde;udmisel viivitamata k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1-3 nimetatud sisereeglid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) On the request of the Supervision Authority, the internal rules specified in subsections (1) -(3) of this section shall be submitted thereto immediately. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 196. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 196. </inglise>
<eesti>Insaideri poolt andmete esitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Provision of information by insider </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Insaider esitab inspektsioonile viimase n&otilde;udmisel andmed k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 189 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite omandamise v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randamise ja sellega seotud asjaolude kohta enda, oma abikaasa v&otilde;i faktilise elukaaslase ja alaealiste laste arvel v&otilde;i kolmanda isiku arvel v&otilde;i nimel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) On the request of the Supervision Authority, an insider shall submit information thereto concerning the acquisition and transfer of securities specified in subsection 189 (3) of this Act for his or her own account, for the account of his or her spouse or cohabitee and minor children or on account or in the name of a third party, and concerning circumstances connected with such acquisition or transfer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud kohustus esitada inspektsioonile andmed emitendi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite omandamise v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randamise kohta enda arvel laieneb ka juriidilisele isikule, kelle f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust esindaja omab juurdep&auml;&auml;su siseteabele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The obligation provided for in subsection (1) of this section to submit information to the Supervision Authority concerning the acquisition and transfer of securities of an issuer for own account also applies with respect to a legal person's representative who is a natural person and who has access to inside information. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 197. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 197. </inglise>
<eesti>Emitendi poolt andmete esitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Provision of information by issuer </inglise>
<eesti>Emitent, kelle v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiga turul kaubeldakse, ning tema emaettev&otilde;tja ja t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja esitavad inspektsioonile viimase n&otilde;udmisel andmed selle v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi insaiderite ja nendega seotud asjaolude kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>On the request of the Supervision Authority, an issuer whose securities are traded on the market, and the parent undertaking and subsidiary thereof, shall submit information concerning insiders with respect to such securities and any circumstances related thereto to the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 198. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 198. </inglise>
<eesti>Andmete esitamise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for submission of information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 196 ja 197 nimetatud andmed esitatakse inspektsioonile kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates j&auml;relep&auml;rimise k&auml;ttesaamise p&auml;evast, kui inspektsioon ei ole isiku p&otilde;hjendatud taotlusel lubanud andmete hilisemat esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The information specified in &sect;&sect; 196 and 197 of this Act shall be submitted to the Supervision Authority within three working days as of the date of receipt of the relevant request unless the Supervision Authority, on the basis of a justified application by the person, permits the information to be submitted later. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud andmete osas n&otilde;uda t&auml;psustavate andmete ja dokumentide esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority may demand the submission of more specific information and documents regarding the information specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 199. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 199. </inglise>
<eesti>Andmete kasutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Use of information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 196-198 alusel edastatud andmeid ja dokumente koguda, s&auml;ilitada ja kasutada &uuml;ksnes k&auml;esolevas peat&uuml;kis s&auml;testatud keeldude rikkumise ja kohustuste t&auml;itmise kontrollimiseks v&otilde;i teiste riikide v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituruj&auml;relevalve asutustega tehtava koost&ouml;&ouml; eesm&auml;rgil. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Supervision Authority may collect, preserve and use information and documents forwarded in accordance with &sect;&sect; 196-198 of this Act only to verify the violation of prohibitions and the performance of obligations prescribed in this Chapter or for the purposes of co-operation with securities supervisory agencies of other states. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 196 alusel inspektsioonile edastatud teave, mis ei ole enam vajalik k&auml;esolevas peat&uuml;kis s&auml;testatud keeldude rikkumise ja kohustuste t&auml;itmise kontrollimiseks v&otilde;i rahvusvahelise koost&ouml;&ouml; eesm&auml;rgil, h&auml;vitatakse viivitamata. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Information forwarded to the Supervision Authority on the basis of &sect; 196 of this Act which ceases to be necessary to verify the violation of prohibitions and the performance of obligations prescribed in this Chapter or for the purposes of international co-operation shall be immediately destroyed. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 200. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 200. </inglise>
<eesti>Turuga manipuleerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Manipulation of market </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turuga manipuleerimine on isiku tegevus v&otilde;i tegevusetus, mille eesm&auml;rgiks on turul kaubeldavate v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite v&auml;&auml;rtusest, hinnast, k&auml;ibest v&otilde;i kauplemise aktiivsusest eba&otilde;ige v&otilde;i eksitava mulje kujundamine, sekkudes seel&auml;bi turu n&otilde;udluse ja pakkumise kujunemise protsessi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Manipulation of the market is an act or omission of a person with the aim of forming an inaccurate or misleading impression of the value, price or turnover of securities traded on the market or of trading activity with such securities by interfering in the process of forming supply and demand on the market. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turuga manipuleerimiseks loetakse ka eba&otilde;ige v&otilde;i eksitava teabe avalikustamist v&otilde;i levitamist turul kaubeldava v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitendi v&otilde;i temaga &uuml;hte kontserni kuuluva &auml;ri&uuml;hingu kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The disclosure or distribution of inaccurate or misleading information with regard to the issuer of securities traded on the market or a company belonging to the same group thereas is also deemed to be manipulation of the market. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Turuga manipuleerimiseks loetakse muu hulgas allj&auml;rgnev turul avalduv v&otilde;i seda m&otilde;jutav tegu: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Amongst others, the following acts which occur on or influence the market are also deemed to be manipulation of the market: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tehingud v&otilde;i tehingute seeriad v&otilde;i mis tahes muu tegu, mille eesm&auml;rgiks on v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi hinna langetamine, t&otilde;stmine v&otilde;i &uuml;hel tasemel hoidmine turul; </eesti>
<inglise>1) transactions or series of transactions or any other act the aim of which is to reduce, increase or maintain the price of a security on the market; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tehingud v&otilde;i tehingute seeriad v&otilde;i mis tahes muu tegu, mille eesm&auml;rgiks on suurendada v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite k&auml;ivet v&otilde;i kauplemise aktiivsust turul; </eesti>
<inglise>2) transactions or series of transactions or any other act the aim of which is to increase the turnover of securities on the market or trading activity with such securities; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tehingud v&otilde;i tehingute seeriad v&otilde;i mis tahes muu tegu, mille eesm&auml;rgiks on ajendada teist isikut otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt turul v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi omandamise v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randamise tehingut tegema v&otilde;i sellest hoiduma; </eesti>
<inglise>3) transactions or series of transactions or any other act the aim of which is to induce another person directly or indirectly to conduct or to refrain from conducting a transaction to purchase or to transfer a security on the market; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tehingud v&otilde;i tehingute seeriad v&otilde;i mis tahes muu tegu, mille eesm&auml;rgiks on m&otilde;jutada v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi kauplemisp&auml;eva sulgemishinda turul; </eesti>
<inglise>4) transactions or series of transactions or any other act the aim of which is to influence the closing price of a security on the market; </inglise>
<eesti>5) tehingud v&otilde;i tehingute seeriad, mille hind v&otilde;i tehingutega kaasnevate v&otilde;imalike kahjude katmine lepitakse eelnevalt kokku turuv&auml;liselt; </eesti>
<inglise>5) transactions or series of transactions with respect to which the price or the covering of possible losses accompanying the transactions has been agreed in advance outside the market; </inglise>
<eesti>6) v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi omandamine v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randamine samaaegselt v&otilde;i l&uuml;hikese ajavahemiku jooksul, mille eesm&auml;rgiks on n&auml;iliselt suurendada turu aktiivsust v&otilde;i k&auml;ivet; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the purchase or sale of securities simultaneously or over a short period with the aim of seemingly increasing market activity or turnover; </inglise>
<eesti>7) tehingukorralduse sisestamine v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi osas, mille kohta on eelnevalt teada, et teine osapool sisestab samal ajal suuruselt ja hinnalt sarnase tehingukorralduse; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the entry of a transaction order with respect to a security with regard to which it is known in advance that a transaction order of a similar size and price is being entered at the same time by another party; </inglise>
<eesti>8) turul tehtavad n&auml;ilised v&otilde;i teeseldud tehingud; </eesti>
<inglise>8) ostensible or sham transactions conducted on the market; </inglise>
<eesti>9) emitendi poolt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 146 ja 159 kohaselt avalikustamisele kuuluva teabe avalikustamata j&auml;tmine v&otilde;i avalikustamisega p&otilde;hjendamatu viivitamine v&otilde;i ebat&auml;pse teabe avalikustamine; </eesti>
<inglise>9) failure on the part of the issuer to disclose information subject to disclosure in accordance with &sect;&sect; 146 and 159 of this Act, or unjustified delay in the disclosure of such information or disclosure of incomplete information; </inglise>
<eesti>10) muu tegevus, mille eesm&auml;rgiks on k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud eesm&auml;rgi saavutamine. </eesti>
<inglise>10) other activities aimed at achieving the objective set out in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Korraldajal on &otilde;igus lisaks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatule kehtestada oma reglemendiga t&auml;iendav loetelu tegudest, mida k&auml;sitatakse turuga manipuleerimisena. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In addition to the acts specified in subsection (3) of this section, an operator has the right to establish an additional list of acts that are deemed to be manipulation of the market in its rules and regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 201. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 201. </inglise>
<eesti>Turuga manipuleerimise keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition on manipulation of market </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turuga manipuleerimine on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Manipulation of the market is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingul, kes on teadlik v&otilde;i kellel on kahtlus turuga manipuleerimisest v&otilde;i selle katsest, on keelatud vastavat tehingut vahendada ja kohustus sellest viivitamata teavitada inspektsiooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An investment firm which knows of or has suspicions regarding manipulation of the market or an attempt to manipulate the market is prohibited from being an intermediary for the relevant transaction and shall inform the Supervision Authority thereof immediately. </inglise>
<eesti>22. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 22 </inglise>
<eesti>Vahekohus </eesti>
<inglise>Arbitral Tribunal </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 202. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 202. </inglise>
<eesti>Turu vahekohus </eesti>
<inglise>Arbitral tribunal of market </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turu vahekohus (edaspidi vahekohus) on Eesti turu korraldaja poolt moodustatav alaliselt tegutsev vahekohus, mis lahendab turu ja selle korraldajaga seotud lepingu- ja teistest tsiviil&otilde;iguslikest suhetest tulenevaid vaidlusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An arbitral tribunal of a market (hereinafter arbitral tribunal) is a permanent arbitral tribunal formed by an operator of an Estonian market which resolves disputes arising from contractual and other civil law relations with respect to the market and the operator thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Korraldaja teatab inspektsioonile, kas tema juures tegutseb alaliselt vahekohus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An operator shall inform the Supervision Authority of whether it has a permanently operating arbitral tribunal. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahekohtu tegutsemisel esitab korraldaja inspektsioonile vahekohtu koosseisu ja tegutsemise seadusele vastavust kinnitava kirjaliku teabe. </eesti>
<inglise>If an arbitral tribunal is operating, the operator shall submit written information confirming the members of the arbitral tribunal and the compliance of its operations with law to the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Inspektsioon teatab seaduslikult alaliselt tegutsevast vahekohtust kohtutele v&otilde;i muudele kohtuotsuste t&auml;itmist korraldavatele riigiasutustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Supervision Authority shall inform courts and other state agencies engaged in arranging the execution of court judgments of the lawful and permanent operation of an arbitral tribunal. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 203. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 203. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahekohtu p&auml;devus </eesti>
<inglise>Competence of arbitral tribunal </inglise>
<eesti>Vahekohus lahendab vaidlusi hagiavalduste alusel, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>An arbitral tribunal shall resolve disputes on the basis of an action filed if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) poolte vahel on kirjalik kokkulepe juba tekkinud v&otilde;i tekkida v&otilde;iva vaidluse &uuml;leandmise kohta vahekohtu lahendada; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the parties have entered into a written agreement to have the arbitral tribunal resolve a dispute which has already arisen or any dispute which may arise in the future; </inglise>
<eesti>2) n&otilde;usolek vaidluse lahendamiseks vahekohtus on v&auml;ljendatud hageja poolt hagi esitamisega, kostja poolt aga tegevusega, mis annab tunnistust tema vabatahtlikust allumisest vahekohtu jurisdiktsioonile. </eesti>
<inglise>2) consent to the arbitral tribunal resolving the dispute has been expressed by the plaintiff by filing the action and by the defendant by activities which reflect its readiness to subject itself voluntarily to the jurisdiction of the arbitral tribunal. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 204. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 204. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahekohtu n&otilde;ukogu ja vahekohtunik </eesti>
<inglise>Council of arbitral tribunal and arbitrators </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vahekohtu n&otilde;ukogus on kuni kuus liiget. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The council of an arbitral tribunal shall consist of up to six members. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahekohtu n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ratakse kuni kaheks aastaks vastavalt vahekohtu reglemendile. </eesti>
<inglise>The council of an arbitral tribunal shall be appointed for up to two years in accordance with the rules and regulations of the arbitral tribunal. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vahekohtu n&otilde;ukogu p&otilde;hiliseks &uuml;lesandeks on arvata isikuid vahekohtu nimekirja ning sellest v&auml;lja, samuti pidada vahekohtunike nimekirja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The principal duty of the council of an arbitral tribunal is to appoint and remove persons from the arbitral tribunal list and to maintain the list of arbitrators. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahekohtu n&otilde;ukogu muud &otilde;igused ja kohustused s&auml;testatakse vahekohtu reglemendis. </eesti>
<inglise>The other rights and obligations of the council of an arbitral tribunal shall be prescribed in the rules and regulations of the arbitral tribunal. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vahekohtu n&otilde;ukogu liikmel peab olema juriidiline akadeemiline k&otilde;rgharidus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Members of the council of an arbitral tribunal shall have an academic degree in law. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahekohtunikul peab olema akadeemiline k&otilde;rgharidus v&otilde;i sellega v&otilde;rdsustatud haridus. </eesti>
<inglise>Arbitrators shall have an academic degree or education equivalent thereto. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Vahekohtunikud on oma kohustuste t&auml;itmisel s&otilde;ltumatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Arbitrators shall be independent in the performance of their duties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 205. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 205. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahekohtu reglement </eesti>
<inglise>Rules and regulations of arbitral tribunal </inglise>
<eesti>Vahekohtu n&otilde;ukogu t&ouml;&ouml;korda, samuti vahekohtu moodustamise ja vaidluste lahendamise korda reguleeritakse vahekohtu reglemendiga, mille kinnitab vastav korraldaja. </eesti>
<inglise>The rules of procedure of the council of an arbitral tribunal and the procedure for forming an arbitral tribunal and for resolving disputes shall be regulated in the rules and regulations of the arbitral tribunal, which shall be approved by the relevant operator. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 206. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 206. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidlus vahekohtus </eesti>
<inglise>Dispute in arbitral tribunal </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vaidlusi vaatab vahekohtus l&auml;bi vastavalt vahekohtu reglemendile poolte valitud v&otilde;i vahekohtu n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ratud &uuml;ks v&otilde;i mitu vahekohtunikku. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Disputes shall be reviewed in an arbitral tribunal in accordance with its rules and regulations by one or several arbitrators chosen by the parties or appointed by the council of the arbitral tribunal. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vaidluste l&auml;bivaatamine vahekohtus on tasuta v&otilde;i tasuline vastavalt vahekohtu reglemendile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The review of disputes in an arbitral tribunal is free or subject to payment in accordance with the rules and regulations of the arbitral tribunal. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahekohtu tasu m&auml;&auml;r ning tasumise kord s&auml;testatakse vahekohtu reglemendis. </eesti>
<inglise>The rate for payment and the procedure for payment shall be prescribed in the rules and regulations of the arbitral tribunal. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vahekohus arvestab vaidluse lahendamisel &otilde;igusaktides ja turu reglemendis s&auml;testatut, samuti turul ausa ja &otilde;iglase kauplemise suhtes kehtivaid ja muid h&auml;id &auml;ritavasid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In resolving a dispute, an arbitral tribunal shall proceed from the provisions of legislation and the rules and regulations of the market, as well as generally accepted business practices applicable to fair and equitable trading on the market and other generally accepted business practices. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 207. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 207. </inglise>
<eesti>Hagi tagamine </eesti>
<inglise>Securing action </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vahekohus v&otilde;ib poole avalduse alusel rakendada j&auml;rgmisi hagi tagamise abin&otilde;usid: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) On the basis of an application from a party, an arbitral tribunal may apply the following measures to secure the action: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kostjale kuuluva kinnisvara v&otilde;&otilde;randamise keelum&auml;rge v&otilde;i kohtuliku h&uuml;poteegi seadmine kinnistusraamatus ja tema v&otilde;i teiste isikute juures oleva vallasvara v&otilde;i rahasummade arestimine hagihinda arvestades; </eesti>
<inglise>1) entry of a prohibition on the transfer of real property belonging to the defendant or entry of the establishment of a judicial mortgage in the land register, and seizure of movable property or money of the defendant which is at the location of the defendant or third parties by taking into account the value of the action; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kostjal teatud tehingute ja toimingute keelamine. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a prohibition on the defendant from entering into certain transactions or performing certain acts. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vahekohtu otsust, millega on m&auml;&auml;ratud hagi tagamise abin&otilde;u, t&auml;idetakse samal viisil nagu vahekohtu l&otilde;ppotsust vaidluse lahendamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A judgment of an arbitral tribunal establishing the measure with which the action is to be secured shall be executed in the same manner as the final judgment of the arbitral tribunal on the resolution of the dispute. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Hagi tagamisega p&otilde;hjustatava v&otilde;imaliku kahju h&uuml;vitamiseks v&otilde;ib vahekohus n&otilde;uda avaldajalt raha ettemaksmist vahekohtu deposiiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An arbitral tribunal may demand that an applicant make an advance deposit with the arbitral tribunal in order to compensate potential damage caused by securing the action. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui vahekohus j&auml;tab hagi rahuldamata ja kui hageja taotlusel hagi tagamisega on kostjale tekitatud kahju, on kostjal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda kahju h&uuml;vitamist hagejalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If an arbitral tribunal does not satisfy an action and if the defendant has sustained damage on the basis of the application by the plaintiff to secure the action, the defendant has the right to demand compensation from the plaintiff. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 208. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 208. </inglise>
<eesti>Koost&ouml;&ouml; maa- ja linnakohtuga </eesti>
<inglise>Co-operation with county and city courts </inglise>
<eesti>Vahekohus v&otilde;ib taotleda maa- v&otilde;i linnakohtult abi t&otilde;endamismenetluseks v&otilde;i muudeks kohtutoiminguteks, mis ei ole vahekohtu p&auml;devuses. </eesti>
<inglise>An arbitral tribunal may request the assistance of a county or city court in attestation procedures or in other court activities which do not fall within the competence of the arbitral tribunal. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohus lahendab taotluse vastavalt t&otilde;endamismenetluse v&otilde;i muude kohtutoimingute kohta kehtivatele menetluss&auml;tetele. </eesti>
<inglise>The court shall process the application pursuant to the procedural provisions regulating attestation procedures or other court activities. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 209. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 209. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidlustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Right of appeal </inglise>
<eesti>Eesti Vabariigi seaduse "Eesti Kaubandus-T&ouml;&ouml;stuskoja Arbitraa&zcaron;ikohtu kohta" (RT 1991, 25, 308; RT I 1999, 18, 302) &sect;-des 7 ja 7 (1) s&auml;testatut kohaldatakse seoses menetlusega vahekohtus. </eesti>
<inglise>Proceedings in an arbitral tribunal shall be subject to the provisions prescribed in &sect;&sect; 7 and 7 (1) of the Republic of Estonia Act on the Arbitral Tribunal of the Estonian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (RT 1991, 25, 308; RT I 1999, 18, 302). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 210. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 210. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahekohtu otsuse t&auml;itmine </eesti>
<inglise>Execution of judgment of arbitral tribunal </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vahekohtu otsus t&auml;idetakse Eestis asuva isiku suhtes t&auml;itemenetluse seadustikus (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 2001, 29, 156; 43, 238) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A judgment of an arbitral tribunal regarding a person located in Estonia shall be executed pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Code of Enforcement Procedure (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 2001, 29, 156; 43, 238). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vahekohtu otsus t&auml;idetakse v&auml;lisriigis asuva isiku suhtes t&auml;itemenetluse seadustikus v&otilde;i v&auml;lislepingus s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A judgment of an arbitral tribunal regarding a person located abroad shall be executed pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Code of Enforcement Procedure or an international agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>Selline otsus loetakse v&auml;lisriigi vahekohtu otsuseks t&auml;itemenetluse seadustiku &sect; 74 t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise>Such judgment is deemed to be a judgment of a foreign arbitral tribunal in the meaning of &sect; 74 of the Code of Enforcement Procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 211. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 211. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahekohtu l&otilde;petamine </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of arbitral tribunal </inglise>
<eesti>Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus teha korraldajale ettekirjutus vahekohtu tegevuse l&otilde;petamiseks, kui vahekohtu tegutsemine seab ohtu turu korrap&auml;rase toimimise v&otilde;i kohtuotsuste t&auml;itmist korraldavate riigiasutuste t&otilde;rgeteta toimimise. </eesti>
<inglise>The Supervision Authority has the right to issue a precept to an operator to terminate the activities of an arbitral tribunal if the activities of the arbitral tribunal endanger the regular operation of the market or the smooth operations of state agencies engaged in arranging the execution of court judgments. </inglise>
<eesti>V osa </eesti>
<inglise>Part V </inglise>
<eesti>Arveldus </eesti>
<inglise>Settlement </inglise>
<eesti>23. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 23 </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;&auml;rtpaberitehingutest tulenevate kohustuste arveldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Settlement of Obligations Arising from Securities Transactions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 212. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 212. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva osa kohaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of this Part </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevat osa kohaldatakse v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitehingutest tekkinud kohustuste t&auml;itmisele l&auml;bi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steemi, samuti tehingutele, millega tagatakse v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steemis osalemisega seotud kohustuste t&auml;itmine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Part shall apply to the performance of obligations arising from securities transactions through the securities settlement system and to transactions used to guarantee the performance of obligations related to participation in the securities settlement system. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva osa s&auml;tted ei laiene Eesti v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite keskregistri pidaja poolt Eesti v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite keskregistri seaduse (RT I 2000, 57, 373; 2001, 48, 268; 79, 480) alusel tehtavatele registritoimingutele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The provisions of this Part shall not apply to register acts carried out on the basis of the Estonian Central Register of Securities Act (RT I 2000, 57, 373; 2001, 48, 268; 79, 480) by the registrar of the Estonian Central Register of Securities. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 213. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 213. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steem </eesti>
<inglise>Securities settlement system </inglise>
<eesti>(1) V&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steem (edaspidi k&auml;esolevas osas s&uuml;steem) on kolme v&otilde;i enama s&uuml;steemi liikme ning s&uuml;steemi korraldaja vahel s&otilde;lmitud lepingu alusel v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitehingutest tekkinud kohustuste t&auml;itmiseks ja s&uuml;steemis osalemisest tekkinud kohustuste t&auml;itmise tagamiseks moodustatud organisatsiooniliste, tehniliste ja &otilde;iguslike lahenduste kogum. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A securities settlement system (hereinafter in this Part system) is a pool of administrative, technical and legal solutions formed for the purpose of performing obligations arising from securities transactions and guaranteeing performance of obligations related to participation in the system on the basis of an agreement entered into between three or more members of the system and the system operator. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses m&otilde;istetakse &uuml;lekandekorraldusena v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitehingutest tekkinud kohustuste t&auml;itmiseks antud maksek&auml;sundeid v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite &uuml;leandmiseks antud korraldusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Act, payment orders for the performance of obligations arising from securities transactions or instructions given for the transfer of securities are treated as transfer orders. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 214. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 214. </inglise>
<eesti>S&uuml;steemi korraldaja </eesti>
<inglise>System operator </inglise>
<eesti>(1) S&uuml;steemi korraldaja on isik, kes koosk&otilde;las s&uuml;steemi reeglites s&auml;testatuga ja nende alusel tema poolt s&otilde;lmitud lepingutega korraldab &uuml;lekandekorralduste t&auml;itmist ning s&otilde;ltuvalt s&uuml;steemi korraldamisest ka s&uuml;steemi liikmete vaheliste n&otilde;uete tasaarvestamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A system operator is a person who, in accordance with the provisions of the system rules and contracts entered into on the basis thereof, arranges for the execution of transfer orders and, depending on the arrangement of the system, also organises the settlement of claims between members of the system. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) S&uuml;steemi korraldajana v&otilde;ib tegutseda: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following may act as a system operator: </inglise>
<eesti>1) Eesti Pank; </eesti>
<inglise>1) The Bank of Estonia; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isik, kellele inspektsioon on sellekohaseks tegutsemiseks andnud vastava tegevusloa. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a person to whom the Supervision Authority has issued a relevant activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Igal s&uuml;steemil v&otilde;ib olla &uuml;ksnes &uuml;ks s&uuml;steemi korraldaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Each system shall have only one system operator. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 215. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 215. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;uded s&uuml;steemi korraldajale </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for system operator </inglise>
<eesti>(1) S&uuml;steemi korraldaja aktsiakapital peab olema v&auml;hemalt 125 000 eurot. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The share capital of a system operator shall be at least 125 000 euro. </inglise>
<eesti>Rahandusministril on &otilde;igus kehtestada s&uuml;steemi korraldaja usaldusv&auml;&auml;rsuse tagamiseks t&auml;iendavaid usaldatavusn&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Finance has the right to establish additional prudential requirements to ensure the reliability of the system operator. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud n&otilde;uete kehtestamisel v&otilde;etakse arvesse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 226 s&auml;testatud tagatisi ning muid olulist t&auml;htsust omavaid asjaolusid. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon establishment of such requirements, the collateral prescribed in &sect; 226 of this Act and other significant circumstances shall be taken into account. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) S&uuml;steemi korraldaja peab korraldama s&uuml;steemi toimimise selliselt, et &uuml;lekandekorralduste t&auml;itmisele suunatud andmet&ouml;&ouml;tlus ja muud toimingud tagaksid &uuml;lekandekorralduste t&auml;itmise vastavalt &uuml;lekandekorralduste tingimustele ja s&uuml;steemi reeglitele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The system operator shall arrange the operation of the system such that the data processing and other proceedings aimed at executing transfer orders ensure the performance of transfer orders in accordance with the conditions of the transfer orders and the system rules. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) S&uuml;steemi korraldaja peab juhtimis- ja tegevusriskide maandamiseks rakendama piisavaid sisekontrolli meetmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In order to manage operating and management risks, a system operator shall apply sufficient internal control measures. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) S&uuml;steemi korraldaja n&otilde;ukogu ja juhatuse liikmetele kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 79 l&otilde;ikes 5 ja &sect;-s 80 investeerimis&uuml;hingu juhtide suhtes s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The provisions of subsection 79 (5) and &sect; 80 of this Act pertaining to managers of an investment firm apply with respect to the members of the supervisory board and management board of a system operator. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 216. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 216. </inglise>
<eesti>S&uuml;steemi korraldaja tegevus </eesti>
<inglise>Activities of system operator </inglise>
<eesti>(1) S&uuml;steemi korraldajale antud tegevusluba annab &otilde;iguse &uuml;ksnes: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An activity licence issued to a system operator grants only the following rights: </inglise>
<eesti>1) pidada arvestust &uuml;lekandekorralduste alusel s&uuml;steemi kaudu t&auml;itmisele kuuluvate n&otilde;uete ja kohustuste &uuml;le (clearing); </eesti>
<inglise>1) to keep account of claims to be settled and obligations to be performed through the system on the basis of transfer orders (clearing); </inglise>
<eesti>2) korraldada ja tagada regulaarselt &uuml;lekandekorralduste alusel tekkinud n&otilde;uete ja kohustuste t&auml;itmist, sealhulgas nende tasaarvestamist (settlement); </eesti>
<inglise>2) to arrange and ensure on a regular basis the settlement of claims and the performance of obligations arising on the basis of transfer orders, including the settlement thereof (settlement); </inglise>
<eesti>3) s&otilde;lmida &uuml;lekandekorralduste t&auml;itmisega seotud rahaliste kohustuste arvelduste korraldamiseks lepinguid krediidiasutuste seaduses s&auml;testatud makses&uuml;steemi haldajaga v&otilde;i, kui s&uuml;steemi korraldajal on sellekohane tegevusluba, pidada rahaliste kohustuste arvelduste korraldamiseks s&uuml;steemi liikmete arvelduskontosid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) to enter into contracts to arrange for payment of monetary obligations related to the execution of transfer orders with the administrator of the payment system prescribed in the Credit Institutions Act or, if the system operator holds a relevant activity licence, to maintain the settlement accounts of the members of the system to arrange for payment of monetary obligations; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teha v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitehingute t&auml;itmiseks vajalikke p&auml;ringuid ja anda korraldusi Eesti v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite keskregistri pidajale (edaspidi k&auml;esolevas osas registripidaja) kannete tegemiseks koosk&otilde;las &otilde;igusaktide, s&uuml;steemi reeglite ja s&uuml;steemi korraldaja poolt s&otilde;lmitud lepingutega; </eesti>
<inglise>4) to make enquiries necessary to conduct securities transactions, and to give orders to the registrar of the Estonian Central Register of Securities (hereinafter in this Part registrar) to make entries in accordance with legislation, the system rules and the contracts entered into by the system operator; </inglise>
<eesti>5) teha v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitehingute t&auml;itmiseks vajalikke p&auml;ringuid ja anda korraldusi makses&uuml;steemile toimingute tegemiseks koosk&otilde;las &otilde;igusaktide, s&uuml;steemi reeglite ja s&uuml;steemi korraldaja poolt s&otilde;lmitud lepingutega; </eesti>
<inglise>5) to make enquiries necessary to conduct securities transactions, and to give orders to the payment system to perform acts in accordance with legislation, the system rules and the contracts entered into by the system operator; </inglise>
<eesti>6) moodustada ja k&auml;sutada s&uuml;steemi toimimiseks, s&uuml;steemi liikmete kohustuste t&auml;itmise tagamiseks ja s&uuml;steemi toimimisega seotud riskide maandamiseks vajalikke tagatisvahendite fonde; </eesti>
<inglise>6) to establish and manage guarantee funds necessary for the operation of the system, for ensuring performance of the obligations of the members of the system and for managing the risks arising from the operation of the system; </inglise>
<eesti>7) s&uuml;steemi reeglitega etten&auml;htud juhtudel ja korras v&otilde;tta &uuml;le v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitehingutest tekkinud n&otilde;udeid ja kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>7) to take over claims and obligations arising from securities transactions in the cases and pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the system rules. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) S&uuml;steemi korraldajal on lisaks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatule &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In addition to the provisions of subsection (1) of this section, a system operator has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) osutada makseagendi teenuseid v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega seotud v&auml;ljamaksete tegemisel. </eesti>
<inglise>1) provide the services of a paying agent in making payments related to securities. </inglise>
<eesti>Makseagendiks k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on emitendi esindaja, kes vahendab v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitelt tehtavaid makseid; </eesti>
<inglise>For the purposes of this Act, a paying agent is a representative of an issuer who acts as an intermediary for payments made with respect to securities; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teha nii v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite kui ka raha laenu- ning tagatistehinguid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) engage in lending and guarantee transactions of both securities and money; </inglise>
<eesti>3) osutada v&auml;lisvaluuta vahetusega seotud teenuseid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) provide services related to foreign currency exchange; </inglise>
<eesti>4) osutada muid teenuseid ning teha tehinguid ja toiminguid, mis on vajalikud seoses &uuml;lekandekorralduste t&auml;itmise korraldamise v&otilde;i tagamisega. </eesti>
<inglise>4) provide other services and conduct other transactions or acts which are necessary to arrange for performance of or to guarantee transfer orders. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 217. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 217. </inglise>
<eesti>S&uuml;steemi korraldaja tegevusluba </eesti>
<inglise>Activity licence of system operator </inglise>
<eesti>(1) S&uuml;steemi korraldaja tegevusloa (edaspidi k&auml;esolevas osas tegevusluba) suhtes kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 48 l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3, &sect; 51 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 3, &sect;-s 52, &sect; 53 l&otilde;ikes 3, &sect; 55 l&otilde;igetes 1-5 ja &sect;-s 57 s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The provisions of subsections 48 (2) and (3), subsections 51 (1) and (3), &sect; 52, subsection 53 (3), subsections 55 (1) -(5) and &sect; 57 of this Act apply with respect to the activity licence of a system operator (hereinafter in this Part activity licence). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusluba tuleb taotleda iga s&uuml;steemi korraldamiseks eraldi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An individual activity licence shall be applied for to operate each individual system. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 218. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 218. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa taotlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Application for activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa taotlemisel esitab taotleja inspektsioonile vastava kirjaliku avalduse ning k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 54 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-11 ja 15 nimetatud andmed ja dokumendid ning k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 222 nimetatud s&uuml;steemi reeglite projekti ja taotleja &auml;riplaani j&auml;rgneva kolme aasta kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon application for an activity licence, the applicant shall submit relevant written application to the Supervision Authority, as well as the information and documents specified in clauses 54 (1) 1) -11) and 15) of this Act, the draft system rules specified in &sect; 222 of this Act and the applicant's business plan for the next three years. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotluse vormi kehtestab rahandusminister oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The format of applications shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud &auml;riplaan peab sisaldama arveldus-, teabe- ja muude s&uuml;steemide toimimise t&auml;pset kirjeldust, samuti taotleja organisatsioonilise &uuml;lesehituse, tegevuskohtade, rakendatavate infotehnoloogiliste ja muude tehniliste vahendite ning majandusn&auml;itajate kirjeldust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The business plan specified in subsection (1) of this section shall contain a precise description of the operation of the settlement, information and other systems as well as a description of the applicant's organisational structure, places of business and the information technology and other technical measures to be implemented, and its economic indicators. </inglise>
<eesti>Rahandusminister v&otilde;ib oma m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestada &auml;riplaanile t&auml;psemad n&otilde;uded. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Finance may, by a regulation, establish more specific requirements for the business plan. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 219. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 219. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa andmisest keeldumine </eesti>
<inglise>Refusal to grant activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioon keeldub tegevusloa andmisest, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Supervision Authority shall refuse to issue an activity licence if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tegevusloa taotlemisel esitatud andmed v&otilde;i dokumendid ei vasta k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i need on eba&otilde;iged, eksitavad v&otilde;i mittet&auml;ielikud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the information or documents submitted upon application for the activity licence do not meet the requirements provided for in this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof or are inaccurate, misleading or incomplete; </inglise>
<eesti>2) taotleja ei esitanud t&auml;htaegselt v&otilde;i on keeldunud esitamast inspektsioonile taotlemisel esitamisele kuuluvaid v&otilde;i muid inspektsiooni poolt n&otilde;utud andmeid, dokumente v&otilde;i teavet; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the applicant fails, within the prescribed term, or refuses to submit the information or documents subject to submission upon application or requested by the Supervision Authority to the Supervision Authority; </inglise>
<eesti>3) taotleja ei suuda tulenevalt oma organisatsioonilisest &uuml;lesehitusest, &otilde;iguslikest ja tehnilistest lahenditest ning vara ja omakapitali ebapiisavusest t&auml;ita k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktidega s&uuml;steemi korraldajale ja s&uuml;steemile kehtestatud n&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the applicant, due to its organisational structure, legal and technical solutions or insufficiency of assets and owners' equity, is not able to meet the requirements established by this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof for system operators and the system; </inglise>
<eesti>4) taotleja muud tegevusalad seavad ohtu s&uuml;steemi korra- v&otilde;i &otilde;igusp&auml;rase toimimise v&otilde;i s&uuml;steemi korraldajana tegutsemise; </eesti>
<inglise>4) other areas of activity of the applicant endanger the regular and lawful operation of the system or its activities as a system operator; </inglise>
<eesti>5) inspektsiooni hinnangul taotleja n&otilde;ukogu ja juhatuse liikmed ei oma piisavalt s&uuml;steemi korraldamiseks vajalikke teadmisi v&otilde;i ei ole v&otilde;imelised korraldama s&uuml;steemi korra- ja &otilde;igusp&auml;rast toimimist, samuti kui taotleja juhil ei ole oma kohustuste t&auml;itmiseks vajalikku haridust, teadmisi, kogemusi v&otilde;i laitmatut reputatsiooni; </eesti>
<inglise>5) in the opinion of the Supervision Authority, the members of the supervisory board and management board of the applicant do not have sufficient knowledge for operating a system or they are unable to operate the system in a regular and lawful manner, or that a manager of the applicant is lacking the education, knowledge, experience or impeccable reputation necessary to perform his or her duties; </inglise>
<eesti>6) juht on olnud pankrotiv&otilde;lgnik v&otilde;i tema suhtes on pankrotimenetlus raugenud, juhi tegevus v&otilde;i tegevusetus on p&otilde;hjustanud isiku pankroti, sundl&otilde;petamise v&otilde;i tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamise v&otilde;i juhi tegevus v&otilde;i tegevusetus on n&auml;idanud tema suutmatust korraldada v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalise v&otilde;i kutselise investori tegevust selliselt, et v&otilde;lausaldajate huvid oleksid k&uuml;llaldaselt kaitstud; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a manager has been a bankrupt or if bankruptcy proceedings with respect to this person have been terminated by abatement, or if the activities or omissions of the manager have led to the bankruptcy, compulsory dissolution or revocation of the activity licence of a person or if the activities or omissions of the manager have shown his or her inability to organise the activities of a professional securities market participant or professional investor in a manner that would sufficiently protect the interests of its creditors; </inglise>
<eesti>7) taotleja ei ole t&auml;itnud k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the applicant fails to meet the requirements provided for in this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>8) taotleja on olulisel m&auml;&auml;ral v&otilde;i korduvalt rikkunud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud n&otilde;udeid v&otilde;i taotleja tegevus v&otilde;i tegevusetus ei vasta headele &auml;ritavadele. </eesti>
<inglise>8) the applicant has materially or repeatedly violated requirements provided for in legislation or the activities or omissions of the applicant are in contradiction with good business practices. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusluba omav s&uuml;steemi korraldaja on kohustatud tegevusloa kehtivuse ajal v&auml;ltima asjaolusid, mis on aluseks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud tegevusloa andmisest keeldumisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) During the period of validity of its activity licence, a system operator shall prevent any circumstances which would serve as a basis for refusal to issue the activity licence provided for in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 220. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 220. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamine on tegevusloa andmise otsusega omandatud &otilde;iguse t&auml;ielik v&otilde;i osaline &auml;rav&otilde;tmine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Revocation of an activity licence is the total or partial deprivation of a right acquired by a decision to issue an activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus tunnistada tegevusluba kehtetuks, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority has the right to revoke an activity licence if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) s&uuml;steemi korraldaja v&otilde;ib oma tegevuse v&otilde;i tegevusetusega p&otilde;hjustada ohu riigi majandusele tervikuna v&otilde;i riigi avalikule korrale v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru korra- v&otilde;i &otilde;igusp&auml;rasele toimimisele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the system operator may endanger the economy of the state as a whole or law and order in the state or the regular and lawful operation of the securities market through its activities or omissions; </inglise>
<eesti>2) s&uuml;steemi korraldaja suhtes esineb k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 219 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud tegevusloa andmisest keeldumise alus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) grounds for refusal to issue an activity licence provided for in subsection 219 (1) of this Act exist with respect to the system operator; </inglise>
<eesti>3) s&uuml;steemi korraldaja rikub oluliselt seaduses v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktis s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uet; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the system operator materially violates a requirement provided for in this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>4) s&uuml;steemi korraldaja ei ole t&auml;ies ulatuses v&otilde;i t&auml;htaegselt t&auml;itnud inspektsiooni poolt tehtud ettekirjutust; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the system operator fails to comply in full or within the prescribed term with a precept issued by the Supervision Authority; </inglise>
<eesti>5) s&uuml;steemi korraldaja on oma tegevuse v&otilde;i tegevusetuse t&otilde;ttu kaotanud usalduse; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the activities or omissions of the system operator have led to a loss of confidence therein; </inglise>
<eesti>6) s&uuml;steemi korraldaja ei ole alustanud s&uuml;steemi korraldajana tegutsemist kuue kuu jooksul tegevusloa andmisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the system operator fails to commence operations as a system operator within six months as of the issue of the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Enne tegevusloa k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 alusel kehtetuks tunnistamise otsustamist v&otilde;ib inspektsioon teha s&uuml;steemi korraldajale t&auml;htajalise ettekirjutuse kehtetuks tunnistamise aluseks olevate puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Prior to making a decision to revoke an activity licence on the basis of subsection (2) of this section, the Supervision Authority may issue a precept to the system operator establishing a deadline for elimination of the deficiencies which are the basis for revocation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 221. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 221. </inglise>
<eesti>S&uuml;steemi liige </eesti>
<inglise>Member of system </inglise>
<eesti>(1) S&uuml;steemi liige on isik, kes on &uuml;lekandekorralduste t&auml;itmiseks s&otilde;lminud s&uuml;steemi korraldajaga ja k&otilde;igi teiste s&uuml;steemi liikmetega lepingu s&uuml;steemi kasutamiseks vastavalt s&uuml;steemi reeglitele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A member of the system is a person who has entered into a contract with the system operator and all other members of the system to use the system pursuant to the system rules for the purpose of executing transfer orders. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud s&uuml;steemi liikmeks v&otilde;ib olla: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following persons may be members of a system specified in subsection (1) of this section: </inglise>
<eesti>1) krediidiasutus v&otilde;i v&auml;lisriigi krediidiasutuse filiaal krediidiasutuste seaduse t&auml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a credit institution or a branch of a foreign credit institution within the meaning of the Credit Institutions Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) investeerimis&uuml;hing v&otilde;i v&auml;lisriigi investeerimis&uuml;hingu filiaal, esindus ning piiri&uuml;leste investeerimisteenuse pakkuja k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise>2) an investment firm or a branch or representative office of a foreign investment firm, and a person providing cross-border investment services within the meaning of in this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) valitsusasutus, avalik-&otilde;iguslik juriidiline isik v&otilde;i riigi poolt asutatud sihtasutus; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a government agency, a legal person in public law or a foundation established by the state; </inglise>
<eesti>4) v&auml;lisriigi s&uuml;steemi korraldaja, v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite registri pidaja ja keskpank. </eesti>
<inglise>4) a foreign system operator, registrar of a securities register and central bank. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) S&uuml;steemi reeglitega etten&auml;htud juhtudel ja korras v&otilde;ib s&uuml;steemi liige vahendada s&uuml;steemi teenuseid kolmandatele isikutele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the cases and pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the system rules, a member of the system may act as an intermediary with respect to services of the system for third parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) S&uuml;steemi liige on kohustatud teavitama &otilde;igustatud isikuid enda s&uuml;steemi liikmeks olekust ning s&uuml;steemi reeglitest neis s&auml;testatud juhtudel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the cases and pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the system rules, a member of the system is required to inform entitled persons of its membership of the system and of the system rules. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 222. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 222. </inglise>
<eesti>S&uuml;steemi reeglid </eesti>
<inglise>System rules </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lekandekorralduste andmist ja t&auml;itmist ning s&uuml;steemi toimimist reguleeritakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel s&uuml;steemi korraldaja poolt kehtestatud reeglitega (edaspidi k&auml;esolevas osas s&uuml;steemi reeglid), milles peavad muu hulgas sisalduma: </eesti>
<inglise>The issue and execution of transfer orders and the operation of the system shall be regulated by rules established by the system operator on the basis of this Act (hereinafter in this Part system rules), which shall include: </inglise>
<eesti>1) s&uuml;steemi korraldaja nimi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name of the system operator; </inglise>
<eesti>2) s&uuml;steemile esitatavad n&otilde;uded; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the requirements for the system; </inglise>
<eesti>3) s&uuml;steemi liikmetele esitatavad n&otilde;uded; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the requirements for members of the system; </inglise>
<eesti>4) s&uuml;steemi liikme staatuse andmise, peatamise ning t&uuml;histamise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the procedure for granting, suspending and revoking the status of a member of the system; </inglise>
<eesti>5) &uuml;lekandekorralduste t&auml;itmiseks kasutatava arveldustehnika kirjeldus; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a description of the settlement facilities used to execute transfer orders; </inglise>
<eesti>6) &uuml;lekandekorralduste alusel tekkinud n&otilde;uete ja kohustuste arveldamise kord, see on &uuml;lekandekorralduste t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise ajakava ning &uuml;lekandekorralduste t&auml;itmine ja selle korraldamine juhul, kui s&uuml;steemi toimimine on h&auml;iritud tehnilisest rikkest v&otilde;i s&uuml;steemis osaleja kohustuste mittekohasest t&auml;itmisest tingituna; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the procedure for settling claims and obligations which arise from transfer orders, meaning the schedule for processing transfer orders and the execution and arrangement of transfer orders in the event that the operation of the system is upset due to a technical failure or by reason of inadequate performance of the obligations of a member of the system; </inglise>
<eesti>7) &uuml;lekandekorralduste t&auml;itmise tagamise viisid ning tagatisvahendite moodustamise ja kasutamise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>7) methods of ensuring the execution of transfer orders, and the procedure for establishing and using guarantee facilities; </inglise>
<eesti>8) s&uuml;steemis osalemisest tulenevate kohustuste t&auml;itmise tagamise tingimused ja kord; </eesti>
<inglise>8) the conditions of and procedure for ensuring performance of obligations arising from participation in the system; </inglise>
<eesti>9) arvelduste l&otilde;plikkust m&auml;&auml;ratlevad tingimused, sealhulgas &uuml;lekandekorralduse vastuv&otilde;tmise ja tagasiv&otilde;etamatuse hetk; </eesti>
<inglise>9) conditions determining the finality of settlements, including the moment of receipt of a transfer order and the moment the transfer order becomes irrevocable; </inglise>
<eesti>10) s&uuml;steemi korraldaja ja liikmete kohustused ja vastutus; </eesti>
<inglise>10) the obligations and liability of the system operator and members of the system; </inglise>
<eesti>11) s&uuml;steemi reeglite muutmise ja vaidlustamise kord. </eesti>
<inglise>11) the procedure for amending system rules and for appealing against them. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 223. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 223. </inglise>
<eesti>S&uuml;steemi reeglite koosk&otilde;lastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Approval of system rules </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rast s&uuml;steemi reeglite v&otilde;i nende muudatuste vastuv&otilde;tmist esitatakse need inspektsioonile koosk&otilde;lastamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) After adoption or amendment, the system rules shall be submitted for approval to the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>Koosk&otilde;lastamise taotlemisel esitatakse inspektsioonile vastav kirjalik avaldus, s&uuml;steemi reeglid v&otilde;i nende muudatused koos selgitustega ja hinnanguga nende m&otilde;ju kohta s&uuml;steemi liikmetele ja s&uuml;steemi toimimisele. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon application for approval, a relevant written application shall be submitted to the Supervision Authority together with the system rules or the amendments thereto, accompanied by explanations and an evaluation of their impact on the members of the system and on the operation of the system. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda s&uuml;steemi reeglite v&otilde;i nende muudatuste t&auml;psustamiseks ja m&otilde;ju hindamiseks s&uuml;steemi korraldajalt t&auml;iendavate andmete ja dokumentide esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to specify the system rules or the amendments thereto or to evaluate the impact thereof, the Supervision Authority may demand the submission of additional information and documents from the system operator. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Inspektsioon teeb otsuse s&uuml;steemi reeglite v&otilde;i nende muudatuste koosk&otilde;lastamise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise kohta 15 p&auml;eva jooksul vastava avalduse esitamisest arvates, kuid mitte hiljem kui 10 p&auml;eva p&auml;rast k&otilde;igi k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud andmete esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Supervision Authority shall make a decision regarding approval of or refusal to approve the system rules or amendments thereto within fifteen days as of submission of the relevant application but not later than within ten days after submission of all the information specified in subsection (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Inspektsioon keeldub s&uuml;steemi reeglite v&otilde;i nende muudatuste koosk&otilde;lastamisest, kui s&uuml;steemi reeglid v&otilde;i nende muudatused ei vasta &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i ei ole piisavad s&uuml;steemi t&otilde;husaks toimimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Supervision Authority shall refuse to approve the system rules or amendments thereto if they do not meet the requirements of legislation or are insufficient for the effective operation of the system. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) S&uuml;steemi reeglid ja nende muudatused j&otilde;ustuvad p&auml;rast nende avalikustamist s&uuml;steemi korraldaja veebilehel, kui s&uuml;steemi reeglites v&otilde;i nende muudatustes ei ole m&auml;&auml;ratud hilisemat t&auml;htaega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The system rules and amendments thereto shall enter into force after they are made public on the website of the system operator, unless the system rules or their amendments prescribe a later term. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalikustada v&otilde;ib &uuml;ksnes inspektsiooni poolt koosk&otilde;lastatud s&uuml;steemi reegleid v&otilde;i nende muudatusi. </eesti>
<inglise>Only system rules and amendments thereto which have been approved by the Supervision Authority may be made public. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) S&uuml;steemi reeglite v&otilde;i nende muudatuste koosk&otilde;lastamise n&otilde;uet ei kohaldata juhul, kui s&uuml;steemi korraldajana tegutseb Eesti Pank. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The requirement for approval of the system rules or amendments thereto does not apply in the case where the Bank of Estonia operates as the system operator. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 224. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 224. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lekandekorralduste l&otilde;plikkus </eesti>
<inglise>Finality of transfer order </inglise>
<eesti>(1) S&uuml;steemi korraldajale s&uuml;steemi reeglite kohaselt edastatud &uuml;lekandekorraldust ei v&otilde;i alates s&uuml;steemi reeglitega s&auml;testatud hetkest tagasi v&otilde;tta ega muuta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A transfer order forwarded to the system operator in accordance with the system rules may not be withdrawn or amended as of the moment prescribed by the system rules. </inglise>
<eesti>Toimingud, mis on tehtud p&auml;rast nimetatud hetke eesm&auml;rgiga muuta v&otilde;i t&uuml;histada antud &uuml;lekandekorraldus, on t&uuml;hised. </eesti>
<inglise>Acts performed after this moment with the aim of amending or cancelling a transfer order already made are void. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;lekandekorralduse tagasiv&otilde;itmine pankrotimenetluses ei too kaasa s&uuml;steemi korraldaja poolt tehtud tasaarvestuse kehtetust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The withdrawal of a transfer order in bankruptcy proceedings shall not result in the invalidity of settlements performed by the system operator. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 225. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 225. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasaarvestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Settlement </inglise>
<eesti>S&uuml;steemis v&otilde;idakse s&uuml;steemi liikmete vahelisi ning s&uuml;steemi liikmete ja s&uuml;steemi korraldaja vahelisi n&otilde;udeid ja kohustusi t&auml;ita n&otilde;uete tasaarvestamise teel. </eesti>
<inglise>Within the system, claims and obligations between the members of the system and between the members of the system and the system operator may be settled and performed by means of the settlement of accounts. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellisel juhul toimub arveldus samaliigiliste n&otilde;uete ja kohustuste tasaarvestamise tulemusena saadud summaarsete n&otilde;uete ehk kogun&otilde;uete (neton&otilde;ue) ja summaarsete kohustuste ehk kogukohustuste (netokohustus) t&auml;itmise teel. </eesti>
<inglise>In this event, settlement is carried out by executing the aggregate claims or total claims (net claim) and the aggregate obligations or total obligations (net obligation) resulting from setting off claims of the same type against obligations of the same type. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;uete tasaarvestamise korral loetakse s&uuml;steemi reeglite kohaselt arvestatud summaarne n&otilde;ue kehtivaks &uuml;he n&otilde;udena nii vastava isiku, tema kreeditoride kui ka kolmandate isikute suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon settlement of claims, the aggregate claim calculated on the basis of the system rules is deemed to be one claim valid with respect to the relevant person, its creditors and third parties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 226. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 226. </inglise>
<eesti>S&uuml;steemi tagatisvahendid </eesti>
<inglise>Collateral instruments of system </inglise>
<eesti>(1) S&uuml;steemi liikmete ning s&uuml;steemi korraldaja kohustuste t&auml;itmise tagamiseks on s&uuml;steemi korraldaja kohustatud moodustama tagatisvahendite fondi (edaspidi k&auml;esolevas osas tagatisfond), mille moodustamise alused s&auml;testatakse s&uuml;steemi reeglites. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to ensure performance of the obligations of the members of the system and of the system operator, the system operator is required to establish a fund of collateral instruments (hereinafter if this Part guarantee fund), and the bases for the formation of the fund shall be prescribed in the system rules. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tagatisfondi kuuluvat vara kasutatakse s&uuml;steemi reeglites s&auml;testatud korras &uuml;lekandekorralduste t&auml;itmiseks juhul, kui korralduse &otilde;igeaegne t&auml;itmine korralduse andja vahendite arvel ei ole v&otilde;imalik ning kui s&uuml;steemi reeglite kohaselt seatud muude tagatiste v&auml;&auml;rtus ei ole korralduste t&auml;itmiseks piisav. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the system rules, assets belonging to the guarantee fund shall be used for executing transfer orders if it is not possible to execute the order in time on account of the funds of the person who gave the order and if the value of other collateral provided in accordance with the system rules is insufficient for the execution of the orders. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 227. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 227. </inglise>
<eesti>Tagatisv&auml;&auml;rtpaber </eesti>
<inglise>Collateral security </inglise>
<eesti>(1) S&uuml;steemis osalemisest tekkinud kohustuste t&auml;itmise tagamiseks v&otilde;ivad s&uuml;steemis osalevad isikud kokku leppida Eesti v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite keskregistris registreeritud, nimetatud isikutele kuuluvate v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite koormamiseks s&uuml;steemi korraldaja v&otilde;i s&uuml;steemi teise liikme kasuks seatud pandiga s&uuml;steemi reeglites s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to ensure performance of obligations arising from participation in the system, the persons participating in the system may, pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the system rules, agree to encumber securities registered in the Estonian Central Register of Securities and belonging to the above-mentioned persons with a pledge established for the benefit of the system operator or another member of the system. </inglise>
<eesti>Selliselt panditud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberit nimetatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses tagatisv&auml;&auml;rtpaberiks. </eesti>
<inglise>A security so pledged is referred to as a collateral security in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud korras ei v&otilde;i pantida v&auml;&auml;rtpabereid, mille v&otilde;&otilde;randamine on piiratud kolmandate isikute suhtes kehtiva ostuees&otilde;igusega v&otilde;i mille kasutus- v&otilde;i k&auml;sutusre&zcaron;iimile on seatud muud p&otilde;hikirjast tulenevad piirangud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Securities the transfer of which is restricted with a pre-emptive right valid with respect to a third party or the use or disposal of which is restricted by other restrictions arising from the articles of association may not be pledged pursuant to the procedure prescribed in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberid loetakse kolmandate isikute suhtes pandituks alates sellekohase m&auml;rke tegemisest Eesti v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite keskregistris avatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberikontol. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Securities specified in subsection (1) of this section are deemed to have been pledged for the benefit of third parties after a relevant entry has been made in the securities account in the Estonian Central Register of Securities. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tagatisv&auml;&auml;rtpaberiga tagatud kohustuse mittekohase t&auml;itmise korral v&otilde;ib s&uuml;steemi korraldaja v&otilde;i s&uuml;steemi liige, kelle kasuks on pant seatud, v&auml;&auml;rtpaberid viivitamata v&otilde;&otilde;randada, kui pandi kasutamist reguleerivate s&uuml;steemi reeglite v&otilde;i pandi seadmise aluseks oleva kokkuleppega ei ole ette n&auml;htud teistsugust tagatisv&auml;&auml;rtpaberite v&otilde;&otilde;randamise re&zcaron;iimi. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the event of inadequate performance of an obligation guaranteed by a collateral security, the system operator or member of the system for whose benefit the pledge is established may transfer the securities immediately, unless the system rules regulating the use of the pledge or the agreement serving as the basis for establishing the pledge prescribe a different regime for transferring collateral securities. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud v&otilde;&otilde;randamise &otilde;igus on isikul, kelle kasuks on pant seatud, ka pankrotimenetluse k&auml;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>The person for whose benefit the pledge is established also has this right in the course of bankruptcy proceedings. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) V&auml;&auml;rtpaberite omanik ei v&otilde;i tagatisv&auml;&auml;rtpabereid v&otilde;&otilde;randada ega koormata. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The owner of securities may not transfer or encumber collateral securities. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Tagatisv&auml;&auml;rtpaberid ei kuulu v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite omaniku pankrotivara hulka, samuti ei laiene selliselt koormatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitele nende omaniku suhtes kohaldatavad hagi tagamise abin&otilde;ud ega muud k&auml;sutuspiirangud. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Collateral securities shall not be included in the bankruptcy estate of the owner of the securities, nor shall the measures applicable to the owner of such securities to secure action or other restrictions on disposal apply to securities so encumbered. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 228. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 228. </inglise>
<eesti>S&uuml;steemi liikme pankroti erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Special rules upon bankruptcy of member of system </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamise korral s&uuml;steemi liikme suhtes, samuti moratooriumi kehtestamise korral krediidiasutusest s&uuml;steemi liikme puhul peatab s&uuml;steemi korraldaja viivitamata vastava s&uuml;steemi liikme poolt antavate &uuml;lekandekorralduste vastuv&otilde;tmise. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a member of the system is declared bankrupt or a moratorium is established with respect to a member of the system which is a credit institution, the system operator shall immediately stop accepting transfer orders given by the member of the system. </inglise>
<eesti>Pankrotimenetluse algatamise korral s&uuml;steemi liikme suhtes on s&uuml;steemi korraldajal &otilde;igus peatada vastava s&uuml;steemi liikme poolt antavate &uuml;lekandekorralduste vastuv&otilde;tmine s&uuml;steemi reeglites s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>In the event bankruptcy proceedings are initiated with respect to a member of the system, the system operator has the right to suspend the acceptance of transfer orders given by such member of the system pursuant to the procedure prescribed in system rules. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pankrotimenetluse algatamine v&otilde;i pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamine s&uuml;steemi liikme suhtes, samuti moratooriumi kehtestamine krediidiasutusest s&uuml;steemi liikme puhul ei peata vastava s&uuml;steemi liikme poolt s&uuml;steemi korraldajale enne pankrotimenetluse algatamist, pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamist v&otilde;i moratooriumi kehtestamist s&uuml;steemi reeglite kohaselt edastatud &uuml;lekandekorralduste t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The initiation of bankruptcy proceedings against a member of the system or the declaration of a member as bankrupt, and the establishment of a moratorium with respect to a member of the system which is a credit institution does not suspend the execution of transfer orders forwarded by the relevant member of the system in accordance with the system rules prior to the initiation of bankruptcy proceedings, declaration of bankruptcy or establishment of a moratorium. </inglise>
<eesti>Enne pankrotimenetluse algatamist, pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamist v&otilde;i moratooriumi kehtestamist s&uuml;steemis osalemisega v&otilde;etud kohustused t&auml;idetakse s&uuml;steemi liikme poolt seatud tagatiste ning s&uuml;steemi tagatisfondi arvel. </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations undertaken by participating in the system prior to the initiation of bankruptcy proceedings, declaration of bankruptcy or establishment of a moratorium shall be performed on account of the collateral established by the member of the system and the system guarantee fund. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) S&uuml;steemi liikme suhtes pankrotimenetluse algatamise, pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamise v&otilde;i krediidiasutusest s&uuml;steemi liikme puhul moratooriumi kehtestamise p&auml;eval s&uuml;steemi korraldajale s&uuml;steemi reeglite kohaselt edastatud ja t&auml;idetud &uuml;lekandekorraldused kehtivad vaid juhul, kui s&uuml;steemi korraldaja ei olnud teadlik ega pidanudki teadma pankrotimenetluse algatamisest, pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamisest v&otilde;i moratooriumi kehtestamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Transfer orders forwarded to the system operator and executed in accordance with the system rules on the day of the initiation of bankruptcy proceedings against a member of the system, declaration of a member of the system as bankrupt or establishment of a moratorium with respect to a member of the system which is a credit institution shall be valid only in the event the system operator was not and did not have to be aware of the initiation of the bankruptcy proceedings, the declaration of bankruptcy or the establishment of the moratorium. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) S&uuml;steemi liikme pankroti korral ei kuulu k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud &uuml;lekandekorralduse t&auml;itmise tulemusel s&uuml;steemi liikme omandist v&auml;ljal&auml;inud vara tema pankrotivara hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the event of the bankruptcy of a member of the system, assets excluded from the ownership of the member as a result of executing a transfer order prescribed in subsection (2) of this section shall not be included in the bankruptcy estate thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) S&uuml;steemi liikme pankroti korral ei kuulu tema poolt s&uuml;steemi reeglite kohaselt s&uuml;steemi tagatisfondi tasutu tema pankrotivara hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In the event of the bankruptcy of a member of the system, payments made into the guarantee fund in accordance with the system rules shall not be included in the bankruptcy estate thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) S&uuml;steemi liige teavitab viivitamata s&uuml;steemi korraldajat ja inspektsiooni iseenda suhtes pankrotimenetluse algatamisest ja selle l&otilde;ppemisest v&otilde;i pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamisest v&otilde;i moratooriumi kehtestamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A member of the system shall immediately notify the system operator and the Supervision Authority of the initiation and termination of bankruptcy proceedings against it or if it is declared bankrupt or a moratorium is established with respect to it. </inglise>
<eesti>Sama kohustus on ka vastaval ajutisel pankrotihalduril, pankrotihalduril v&otilde;i moratooriumihalduril vastava s&uuml;steemi liikme suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>The same obligation also rests with the relevant temporary trustee in bankruptcy, the trustee in bankruptcy or the moratorium administrator with respect to the relevant member of the system. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 229. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 229. </inglise>
<eesti>S&uuml;steemi korraldaja pankroti erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Special rules upon bankruptcy of system operator </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui s&uuml;steemi korraldaja suhtes on algatatud pankrotimenetlus v&otilde;i v&auml;lja kuulutatud pankrot, l&otilde;petab s&uuml;steemi korraldaja viivitamata &uuml;lekandekorralduste vastuv&otilde;tmise s&uuml;steemi liikmetelt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the initiation of bankruptcy proceedings against a system operator or the declaration of a system operator as bankrupt, the system operator shall immediately stop accepting transfer orders from the members of the system. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pankrotimenetluse algatamise v&otilde;i pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamise korral s&uuml;steemi korraldaja suhtes kuuluvad k&otilde;ik s&uuml;steemi korraldajale eelnevalt t&auml;itmiseks antud &uuml;lekandekorraldused t&auml;itmisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon the initiation of bankruptcy proceedings or a declaration of bankruptcy with respect to a system operator, all prior transfer orders given to the system operator shall be executed. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) S&uuml;steemi korraldaja pankroti korral ei kuulu s&uuml;steemi liikmete poolt s&uuml;steemi korraldajale &uuml;lekandekorralduste t&auml;itmiseks v&otilde;i selle tagamiseks &uuml;leantud vara, v&auml;lja arvatud s&uuml;steemi tagatisfondi vahendid, s&uuml;steemi korraldaja pankrotivara hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon the bankruptcy of a system operator, the assets given by the members of the system to the system operator to execute transfer orders or to ensure the execution thereof, with the exception of the assets of the system guarantee fund, shall not be included in the bankruptcy estate of the system operator. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) S&uuml;steemi korraldaja teavitab viivitamata inspektsiooni iseenda suhtes pankrotimenetluse algatamisest ja selle l&otilde;ppemisest v&otilde;i pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A system operator shall immediately notify the Supervision Authority of the initiation and termination of bankruptcy proceedings against it or if it is declared bankrupt. </inglise>
<eesti>Sama kohustus on ka vastaval ajutisel pankrotihalduril v&otilde;i pankrotihalduril vastava s&uuml;steemi korraldaja suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>The same obligation also rests with the relevant temporary trustee in bankruptcy or the trustee in bankruptcy with respect to the relevant system operator. </inglise>
<eesti>VI osa </eesti>
<inglise>Part VI </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relevalve ja vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Supervision and Liability </inglise>
<eesti>24. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 24 </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>Supervision </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 230. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 230. </inglise>
<eesti>Inspektsiooni &otilde;igused j&auml;relevalve teostamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of Supervision Authority in exercising supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioonil on k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatu kohase t&auml;itmise &uuml;le j&auml;relevalve teostamisel k&otilde;ik k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja Finantsinspektsiooni seaduses s&auml;testatud &otilde;igused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Supervision Authority has all the rights established in this Act and in the Financial Supervision Authority Act in exercising supervision over compliance with this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus teostada j&auml;relevalvet v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalisega samasse kontserni kuuluvate &auml;ri&uuml;hingute tegevuse &uuml;le niiv&otilde;rd, kuiv&otilde;rd see on vajalik v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalise kontrollimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority has the right to exercise supervision over companies belonging to the same group as a professional securities market participant to the extent necessary for inspection of the professional securities market participant. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 231. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 231. </inglise>
<eesti>Teabe saamine ja kontode kasutamise peatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Obtaining information and suspension of use of accounts </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioonil on j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks &otilde;igus saada tasuta teavet, dokumente ja selgitusi f&uuml;&uuml;siliselt ja juriidiliselt isikult, samuti valitsusasutustest ja j&auml;relevalveorganitest ning riigi ja kohaliku omavalitsuse andmekogudest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to exercise supervision, the Supervision Authority has the right to obtain information, documents and explanations from any natural or legal person and from government agencies, supervisory bodies and state and local government databases free of charge. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioonil on j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks &otilde;igus saada krediidiasutustelt teavet v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutseliste osaliste, emitentide, investorite ja insaiderite pangakontode ja v&auml;&auml;rtpaberikontode k&auml;ivete ja saldode kohta ning p&otilde;hjendatud kahtluse olemasolul &otilde;iguserikkumise suhtes esitada kohtule motiveeritud avaldus kontode kasutamise peatamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to exercise supervision, the Supervision Authority has the right to obtain information from credit institutions regarding the turnover and balances of the bank accounts and securities accounts of professional securities market participants, issuers, investors and insiders and, upon the existence of justified doubt, to file a motivated petition with a court for suspension of the use of such accounts. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud avalduse saamist vaatab kohus asja &uuml;he t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul l&auml;bi ja otsustab kontode arestimise. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The court shall review the petition within one working day after its receipt and rule on the seizure of the accounts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 232. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 232. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalise ja emitendi kohapealne kontroll </eesti>
<inglise>On-site inspection of professional securities market participants and issuers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioonil on j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks &otilde;igus l&auml;bi viia v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalise ja emitendi, kelle poolt emiteeritud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega kaubeldakse reguleeritud turul v&otilde;i kelle v&auml;&auml;rtpabereid pakutakse avalikult v&otilde;i neid on avalikult pakutud viimase viie aasta jooksul, kohapealne kontroll. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to exercise supervision, the Supervision Authority has the right to carry out on-site inspection of a professional securities market participant and an issuer whose securities are traded on a regulated market or whose securities are subject to a public offer or have been subject to a public offer during the past five years. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohapealne kontroll viiakse l&auml;bi, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An on-site inspection shall be carried out if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) on osutunud vajalikuks kontrollida esitatud andmete vastavust tegelikkusele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) it has become necessary to check whether the information submitted corresponds to reality; </inglise>
<eesti>2) inspektsioonil on kahtlus, et on rikutud k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja selle alusel s&auml;testatut; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the Supervision Authority has reason to believe that the provisions of this Act or provisions established on the basis thereof have been violated; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kontroll on vajalik j&auml;relevalve&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the inspection is necessary to execute supervisory duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kohapealse kontrollimise viib l&auml;bi inspektsiooni selleks volitatud t&ouml;&ouml;taja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) On-site inspection shall be carried out by an authorised employee of the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>Kontrolli l&auml;biviimisest teatatakse kontrollitavale hiljemalt kolm t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva enne kontrolli algust, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui kontrollist etteteatamine on vastuolus kontrolli eesm&auml;rkidega. </eesti>
<inglise>The person to be inspected shall be given at least three working days' notice, unless such notice is in contradiction with the goals of the inspection. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kohapealsel kontrollimisel on kontrollijal &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) During on-site inspection, the person carrying out the inspection has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) siseneda k&otilde;ikidesse ruumidesse, j&auml;rgides k&otilde;iki kontrollitava suhtes kehtivaid turvaeeskirju; </eesti>
<inglise>1) enter all premises, in compliance with all security requirements in force with regard to the person undergoing checks; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kasutada t&ouml;&ouml;ks vajalikku eraldi ruumi; </eesti>
<inglise>2) use a separate room necessary for his or her work; </inglise>
<eesti>3) piiranguteta uurida j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks vajalikke dokumente ja andmekandjaid ning teha nendest v&auml;ljav&otilde;tteid ja &auml;rakirju ning j&auml;lgida t&ouml;&ouml;protsesse. </eesti>
<inglise>3) study documents and media necessary for exercising supervision, make excerpts and copies thereof and monitor the work processes without restrictions. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kontrollitava juhatus on kohustatud m&auml;&auml;rama kompetentse esindaja, kelle juuresolekul kontrollimine toimub ning kes esitab kontrollijale tema &uuml;lesande t&auml;itmiseks vajalikke dokumente ja muud teavet, kaasa arvatud audiitori poolt kontrollitava aruannete kohta tehtud j&auml;reldusotsused koos juhatusele esitatavate m&auml;rkustega, ning annab nende kohta vajalikke selgitusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The management of a person being inspected is required to appoint a competent representative in whose presence the inspection is carried out and who shall provide the person carrying out the inspection with documents and other information necessary for the performance of his or her duties, including the auditor's report concerning the reports of the person being inspected together with findings to be submitted to the management, and provide necessary explanations with regard to such documents and information. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kontrollija on kohustatud koostama kontrollimise tulemuste kohta akti v&otilde;i &otilde;iendi, mis esitatakse kontrollitava juhatuse liikmele v&otilde;i tema poolt volitatud isikule, kes annab selle k&auml;ttesaamise kohta allkirja. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A person carrying out an inspection is required to prepare a report or statement concerning the results of the inspection and submit the report or statement to a member of the management board of the person being inspected or to a person authorised thereby, who shall sign for the receipt thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Isikul on &otilde;igus motiveeritult vaidlustada kontrollimise akti v&otilde;i &otilde;iendit. </eesti>
<inglise>The person has the right to file a motivated appeal against the report or statement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 233. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 233. </inglise>
<eesti>Erakorralise audiitorkontrolli v&otilde;i ekspertiisi m&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Ordering of special audits or assessments </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalise suhtes erakorralise audiitorkontrolli v&otilde;i ekspertiisi l&auml;biviimist, kui v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalise aruanded on eksitavad, tegelikkusele mittevastavad v&otilde;i kui esineb kahtlus, et on tehtud tehinguid, mille tulemusena v&otilde;idakse tekitada v&otilde;i on tekitatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselisele osalisele, investorile v&otilde;i m&otilde;nele teisele isikule olulist kahju v&otilde;i kui muud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalise j&auml;relevalveks olulised k&uuml;simused vajavad t&auml;iendavat selgitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Supervision Authority has the right to demand special audits or assessments be conducted with regard to a professional securities market participant if the reports submitted by the professional securities market participant are misleading or inaccurate or if a suspicion exists that transactions have been conducted as a result of which significant damage may be caused or may have been caused to a professional securities market participant, investor or any other person or if other matters relevant for the purpose of exercising supervision over a professional securities market participant require additional clarification. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus m&auml;&auml;rata erakorralise audiitorkontrolli v&otilde;i ekspertiisi l&auml;biviimiseks audiitor, kellel on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutseliselt osaliselt k&otilde;iki kontrolli v&otilde;i ekspertiisi l&auml;biviimiseks vajalikke andmeid ja dokumente. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order for a special audit or assessment to be conducted, the Supervision Authority has the right to appoint an auditor who has the right to demand all information and documents necessary to conduct the audit or expert review from the professional securities market participant. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutseline osaline on kohustatud need piiranguteta esitama ja osutama audiitorile igak&uuml;lgset abi vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 232 s&auml;testatud korrale. </eesti>
<inglise>Professional securities market participants are required to submit such information and documents without restrictions and to provide all possible assistance to auditors pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 232 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Erakorralise audiitorkontrolli v&otilde;i ekspertiisi l&auml;biviimisega seotud kulud kannab inspektsioon. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Costs related to the conduct of a special audit or assessment shall be borne by the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 234. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 234. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettekirjutus </eesti>
<inglise>Precepts </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus teha ettekirjutusi: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Supervision Authority has the right to issue a precept: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kui j&auml;relevalve tulemusel on avastatud seaduste ja nende alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide, reguleeritud turu reglemendi v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru osalise p&otilde;hikirja n&otilde;uete rikkumisi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) if, as a result of supervision, violations of Acts and legislation issued on the basis thereof or of the requirements of the rules and regulations of a regulated market or of the articles of association of a securities market participant have been discovered; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;iguserikkumiste &auml;rahoidmiseks v&otilde;i kui v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalise poolt v&otilde;etud riskid on oluliselt suurenenud v&otilde;i kui esineb muid tema tegevust, investorite v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kui terviku huve v&otilde;i usaldusv&auml;&auml;rsust ohustavaid v&otilde;i ohustada v&otilde;ivaid asjaolusid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to prevent violations of law or if the risks assumed by a professional securities market participant have increased significantly or if other circumstances emerge which endanger or may endanger the interests or reliability of investors or the securities market as a whole; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kui see on vajalik investorite kaitseks v&otilde;i turu l&auml;bipaistvuse tagamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>3) if this is necessary to protect the interests of investors or to ensure the transparency of the market. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ettekirjutuses peavad olema toodud: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A precept shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ettekirjutuse koostaja nimi ja ametikoht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name and position of the person preparing the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ettekirjutuse tegemise kuup&auml;ev; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the date of preparation of the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ettekirjutuse saaja nimi ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the name and address of the recipient of the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ettekirjutuse tegemise alused koos viidetega vastavate &otilde;igusaktide s&auml;tetele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the bases for issuing the precept together with a reference to the relevant provisions of legislation; </inglise>
<eesti>5) ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmise t&auml;htaeg; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the term for compliance with the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>6) ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmisel rakendatavad sanktsioonid; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the sanctions to be imposed upon failure to comply with the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>7) ettekirjutuse vaidlustamise kord. </eesti>
<inglise>7) the procedure for appealing against the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ettekirjutus v&auml;ljastatakse viivitamata saajale allkirja vastu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A precept shall be issued promptly to the recipient against a signature. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ettekirjutuse saaja peab p&auml;rast selle saamist viivitamata asuma selle t&auml;itmisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The recipient of a precept shall, immediately after receipt of the precept, commence compliance therewith. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Ettekirjutuse peale v&otilde;ib esitada kaebuse halduskohtule 10 p&auml;eva jooksul ettekirjutuse saamisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An appeal against a precept may be filed with an administrative court within ten days as of the receipt of the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kaebuse esitamine ja menetlemine ei peata ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmist, kui inspektsiooni poolt ei ole ette n&auml;htud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The filing of an appeal against a precept and proceedings regarding the appeal do not suspend the requirement to comply with the precept, unless otherwise provided by the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 235. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 235. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igused ettekirjutuse tegemisel </eesti>
<inglise>Rights upon issue of precept </inglise>
<eesti>Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus ettekirjutusega: </eesti>
<inglise>The Supervision Authority has the right to issue a precept to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) keelata teatud tehingute v&otilde;i toimingute tegemine v&otilde;i piirata nende mahtu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) prohibit certain transactions or activities from being conducted or to establish restrictions on their volume; </inglise>
<eesti>2) keelata osaliselt v&otilde;i t&auml;ielikult kasumist tehtavad v&auml;ljamaksed; </eesti>
<inglise>2) prohibit, partially or wholly, any distributions from profits; </inglise>
<eesti>3) n&otilde;uda emitendilt, kelle v&auml;&auml;rtpabereid pakutakse avalikult, teabe viivitamatut avalikustamist, kui sellise teabe avalikustamise kohustus tuleneb k&auml;esolevast seadusest; </eesti>
<inglise>3) demand that the issuer whose securities are offered publicly promptly disclose information, if the obligation to disclose such information arises from this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) n&otilde;uda v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalise tegevuskulude piiramist; </eesti>
<inglise>4) demand a restriction of the operating expenses of a professional securities market participant; </inglise>
<eesti>5) n&otilde;uda v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalise sise-eeskirjade ja protseduurireeglite muutmist; </eesti>
<inglise>5) demand amendment of internal rules and rules of procedure of a professional securities market participant; </inglise>
<eesti>6) teha v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalise n&otilde;ukogule ettepanek juhatuse liikme tagasikutsumiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>6) make a proposal to the supervisory board of a professional securities market participant to remove a member of the management board; </inglise>
<eesti>7) teha ettepanek v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalise aktsion&auml;ride &uuml;ldkoosolekule n&otilde;ukogu liikme tagasikutsumiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>7) make a proposal to the general meeting of the shareholders of a professional securities market participant to remove a member of the supervisory board; </inglise>
<eesti>8) esitada muid n&otilde;udmisi k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>8) set other demands to ensure compliance with this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 236. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 236. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalise juhtimisorganite kokkukutsumine ja nendes osalemine </eesti>
<inglise>Calling of and participation in meeting of directing bodies of professional securities market participant </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioonil on &otilde;igus teha ettekirjutus: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Supervision Authority has the right to issue a precept in order to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselise osalise juhatuse, n&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;i &uuml;ldkoosoleku kokkukutsumiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) call a meeting of the management board or supervisory board of a professional securities market participant or to call the general meeting of a professional securities market participant; </inglise>
<eesti>2) inspektsiooni arvamuse kohaselt vajaliku k&uuml;simuse juhatuse, n&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;i &uuml;ldkoosoleku p&auml;evakorda v&otilde;tmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) include an issue on the agenda of a meeting of the management board or supervisory board or the general meeting if this is necessary in the opinion of the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Inspektsioon v&otilde;ib saata koosolekule oma esindaja, kellel on &otilde;igus esitada oma seisukohti ja teha ettepanekuid ning n&otilde;uda nende protokolli kandmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supervision Authority may send a representative to a meeting who has the right to present positions and make proposals and demand the recording thereof in the minutes of the meeting. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 237. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 237. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimekiri </eesti>
<inglise>List </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsioon peab nimekirja: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Supervision Authority shall maintain a list of: </inglise>
<eesti>1) inspektsiooni poolt registreeritud avaliku pakkumise prospektide kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) prospectuses of public offers registered by the Supervision Authority; </inglise>
<eesti>2) inspektsiooni poolt koosk&otilde;lastatud &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumiste kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>2) takeover bids approved by the Supervision Authority; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kehtivat tegevusluba omavate Eestis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hingute kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) investment firms registered in Estonia which hold a valid activity licence; </inglise>
<eesti>4) Eestis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hingutes olulist osalust omavate isikute kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>4) persons having a qualifying holding in investment firms registered in Estonia; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kehtivat tegevusluba omavate Eestis registreeritud reguleeritud turu korraldajate kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>5) operators of regulated markets who are registered in Estonia and who hold a valid activity licence; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kehtivat tegevusluba omavate Eestis registreeritud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steemi korraldajate kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>6) operators of securities settlement systems who are registered in Estonia and who hold a valid activity licence; </inglise>
<eesti>7) k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktides 3-6 nimetatud juriidiliste isikute n&otilde;ukogu ja juhatuse liikmete kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>7) information on members of the management board and supervisory board of legal persons specified in clauses 3) -6) of this subsection; </inglise>
<eesti>8) Eestis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hingute v&auml;lisriigis asutatud filiaalide kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>8) branches established abroad by investment firms registered in Estonia; </inglise>
<eesti>9) Eestis registreeritud investeerimis&uuml;hingute v&auml;lisriigis avatud esinduste kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>9) representative offices established abroad by investment firms registered in Estonia; </inglise>
<eesti>10) v&auml;lisriigi investeerimis&uuml;hingu Eestis asutatud filiaalide kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>10) branches established in Estonia by foreign investment firms; </inglise>
<eesti>11) piiri&uuml;leste teenuste osutamise luba omavate v&auml;lisriigis tegutseva v&auml;&auml;rtpaberib&ouml;rsi liikmete kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>11) members of a stock exchange operating in a foreign state who have permission to provide cross-border services; </inglise>
<eesti>12) v&auml;lisriigi investeerimis&uuml;hingute Eestis avatud esinduste kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>12) representative offices established in Estonia by foreign investment firms. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud nimekirja kantud andmed peavad olema avalikustatud inspektsiooni veebilehel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The information included in the list provided for in subsection (1) of this section shall be published on the website of the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Rahandusminister kehtestab oma m&auml;&auml;rusega avalikustatavate andmete t&auml;psema loetelu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Minister of Finance shall, by a regulation, establish a more precise list of information to be disclosed. </inglise>
<eesti>25. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 25 </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku haldusvastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Administrative Liability of Legal Persons </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 238. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 238. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;&auml;rtpaberite pakkumise n&otilde;uete rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements for offers of securities </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Pakkuja poolt v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite pakkumisel prospekti inspektsioonis eelnevalt registreerimata j&auml;tmise eest, v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite ilma prospektita pakkumise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on an offerer for failure to register a prospectus of an offer of securities with the Supervision Authority prior to the offer, or for offering securities without a prospectus. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pakkuja poolt prospekti avalikustamise kohustuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest, prospekti avalikustamise t&auml;htaja rikkumise eest, prospekti avalikkusele k&auml;ttesaadavaks tegemata j&auml;tmise eest pakkumise v&auml;ljakuulutamisel v&otilde;i prospekti eest tasu v&otilde;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on an offerer for failure to perform the obligation to disclose the prospectus, for violation of the term for disclosing the prospectus, for failure to make the prospectus available to the general public when declaring a public offer, or for charging a fee for the prospectus. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Pakkuja poolt v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite pakkumise v&auml;ljakuulutamise ja peatamise korra rikkumise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 20 000-200 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A fine in the amount of 20 000 to 200 000 kroons shall be imposed on an offerer for violation of the procedure for the declaration and suspension of an offer of securities. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Pakkuja poolt v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite pakkumise k&auml;igus k&otilde;igi v&otilde;imalike investorite v&otilde;rdsetel alustel teavitamise kohustuse rikkumise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on an offerer for violating the requirement to inform all potential investors on equal terms during an offer of securities on an equal basis. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Pakkuja poolt v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite pakkumise kohta enne pakkumise v&auml;ljakuulutamist reklaami avalikustamise v&otilde;i pakkumise kohta eksitava reklaami avalikustamise v&otilde;i prospektis kajastamata teabe esitamise eest reklaamis v&otilde;i pakkumise kohta k&auml;iva reklaami materjali enne avalikustamist inspektsioonile edastamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 5000-50 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A fine in the amount of 5000 to 50 000 kroons shall be imposed on an offerer for advertising an offer of securities before declaring the offer, for disclosing misleading advertisements about an offer, for presenting information in an advertisement which has not been presented in the prospectus, or for failure to forward advertising material concerning an offer to the Supervision Authority prior to disclosure. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Pakkuja poolt pakkumise perioodil pakkumise tingimuste olulise muutmise korral v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite tagasiostmise kohustuse rikkumise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 100 000-1 000 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A fine in the amount of 100 000 to 1 000 000 kroons shall be imposed on an offerer for violating the obligation to repurchase the securities if the conditions of the offer are significantly changed during the period of the offer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 239. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 239. </inglise>
<eesti>Prospekti n&otilde;uete rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements for prospectuses </inglise>
<eesti>Pakkuja poolt pakkumise perioodil prospektis esitatud teabes toimuvate oluliste muudatuste registreerimata j&auml;tmise eest inspektsioonis v&otilde;i nendest teavitamata j&auml;tmise eest v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite hinda m&otilde;jutada v&otilde;ivate asjaolude, mis ilmnevad p&auml;rast prospekti registreerimist v&otilde;i selle tr&uuml;kkimise ja pakkumise l&otilde;ppemise vahelisel ajal, prospekti lisana inspektsioonile esitamata j&auml;tmise v&otilde;i avalikkusele k&auml;ttesaadavaks tegemata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-400 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 400 000 kroons shall be imposed on an offerer for failure to register significant changes to the information presented in a prospectus with the Supervision Authority during the period of the offer, for failure to disclose such information, and for failure to present information about circumstances which may affect the price of securities and which become evident after registration of the prospectus or during the period between the printing of the prospectus and the termination of the offer to the Supervision Authority as an annex to the prospectus or for failure to make the annex available to the general public. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 240. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 240. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalikkuse teavitamise n&otilde;ude rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements to inform public </inglise>
<eesti>Pakkuja poolt pakkumise peatamisest ja selle j&auml;tkamisest v&otilde;i m&auml;rkimise t&uuml;histamisest avalikkuse teavitamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on an offerer for failure to make information public regarding suspension of an offer, resumption thereof or cancellation of a subscription. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 241. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 241. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa omamise n&otilde;ude rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements to hold activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimisteenuse osutamise eest selleks vastavat tegevusluba omamata - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-1 000 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 1 000 000 kroons shall be imposed for providing investment services without the relevant activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt muu tegevusega tegelemise eest peale investeerimisteenuste ja investeerimisk&otilde;rvalteenuste osutamise, kui see ei ole seadusega lubatud v&otilde;i kui selline tegevus ei ole otseselt vajalik investeerimisteenuste v&otilde;i investeerimisk&otilde;rvalteenuste osutamiseks, - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 20 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A fine in the amount of 20 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on an investment firm for engaging in activities other than investment services and non-core services, unless these are permitted by law or are directly necessary for providing investment services or non-core services. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Reguleeritud turu korraldamise eest selleks vastavat tegevusluba omamata - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 75 000-1 500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A fine in the amount of 75 000 to 1 500 000 kroons shall be imposed for operating a regulated market without the relevant activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) V&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steemi korraldamise eest selleks vastavat tegevusluba omamata - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 75 000-1 500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A fine in the amount of 75 000 to 1 500 000 kroons shall be imposed for operating a securities settlement system without the relevant activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 242. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 242. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa omamise n&otilde;ude rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements to have permission </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt inspektsiooni loata v&auml;lisriigis t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i filiaali asutamise v&otilde;i v&auml;lisriigi investeerimis&uuml;hingus osaluse omandamise eest selliselt, et see muutub investeerimis&uuml;hingu t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjaks, - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-250 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 250 000 kroons shall be imposed on an investment firm for founding a subsidiary or branch abroad without the permission of the Supervision Authority or for acquiring a holding in a foreign investment firm such that the latter becomes a subsidiary of the investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt inspektsiooni loata lepinguriigis filiaali asutamise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-250 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 250 000 kroons shall be imposed on an investment firm for founding a branch in a Contracting State without the permission of the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&auml;lisriigi investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt inspektsiooni loata Eestis filiaali asutamise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-250 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 250 000 kroons shall be imposed on a foreign investment firm for founding a branch in Estonia without the permission of the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) V&auml;lisriigis tegutseva v&auml;&auml;rtpaberib&ouml;rsi liikme poolt ilma inspektsiooni loata Eestis elavatele v&otilde;i asuvatele isikutele Eestis asuva v&auml;&auml;rtpaberib&ouml;rsi vahendusel piiri&uuml;leste teenuste osutamise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-250 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 250 000 kroons shall be imposed on a member of a stock exchange operating abroad for providing cross-border services to persons residing or located in Estonia with the intermediation of a stock exchange in Estonia without the permission of the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 243. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 243. </inglise>
<eesti>Teavitamise kohustuse n&otilde;ude rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements regarding notification obligation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt v&auml;lisriigis esinduse avamisest inspektsiooni teavitamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 5000-20 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A fine in the amount of 5 000 to 20 000 kroons shall be imposed on an investment firm for failure to notify the Supervision Authority of the opening of a representative office abroad. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt piiri&uuml;leste teenuste osutamisest inspektsiooni teavitamata j&auml;tmise eest v&otilde;i piiri&uuml;leste teenuste osutamisel &auml;riplaani muudatustest teavitamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 5000-20 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A fine in the amount of 5 000 to 20 000 kroons shall be imposed on an investment firm for failure to notify the Supervision Authority of the provision of cross-border services or of amendments made to the business plan for providing cross-border services. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&auml;lisriigi investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt Eestis esinduse avamisest inspektsiooni teavitamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 20 000-250 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A fine in the amount of 20 000 to 250 000 kroons shall be imposed on a foreign investment firm for failure to notify the Supervision Authority of the opening of a representative office in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Investeerimis&uuml;hingute poolt &uuml;hinemisloa saamisest avalikkuse viivitamata teavitamata j&auml;tmise v&otilde;i &uuml;hinemisest ning uue investeerimis&uuml;hingu tegevuse alustamisest teavitamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 20 000-250 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A fine in the amount of 20 000 to 250 000 kroons shall be imposed on investment firms for failure to notify the public immediately of the grant of merger permission or failure to disclose information about their merger and the commencement of activities by the new investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 244. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 244. </inglise>
<eesti>Kliendi varade hoidmise ja kaitse n&otilde;ude ning tegevuskeelu n&otilde;ude rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements to maintain and protect assets of clients and prohibition on business </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt kliendi varade hoidmise ja kaitsega seotud kohustuste t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-1 000 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 1 000 000 kroons shall be imposed on an investment firm for failure to perform the obligations related to the maintenance and protection of the assets of clients. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud keelatud tegevusega tegelemise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-1 000 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 1 000 000 kroons shall be imposed on an investment firm for engaging in prohibited activities prescribed by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 245. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 245. </inglise>
<eesti>Andmete registreerimise ja s&auml;ilitamise ning tehingute registreerimise n&otilde;uete rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements to register and maintain information and to register transactions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt andmete registreerimata ja s&auml;ilitamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on an investment firm for failure to register and preserve information. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt seoses investeerimisteenuste osutamisega reguleeritud turule kauplemisele lubatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega tehingute registreerimata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-1 750 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 1 750 000 kroons shall be imposed on an investment firm for failure to register transactions with securities admitted to be traded on a regulated market in connection with the provision of investment services. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Reguleeritud turu korraldaja poolt reguleeritud turul tehtud ja reguleeritud turu korraldajale teatatud tehingute registreerimata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-1 750 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 1 750 000 kroons shall be imposed on an operator of a regulated market for to failure register transactions conducted on the regulated market and of which the operator of the regulated market is notified. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 246. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 246. </inglise>
<eesti>Usaldatavusn&otilde;uete rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of prudential requirements </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja selle alusel s&auml;testatud aktsiakapitali, omakapitali ja muude usaldatavusn&otilde;uete j&auml;rgimata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 20 000-750 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A fine in the amount of 20 000 to 750 000 kroons shall be imposed on an investment firm for violating the requirements for its share capital or own capital or other prudential requirements prescribed by and on the basis of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Reguleeritud turu korraldaja poolt finantsriski maandamise kohustuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-1 000 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 1 000 000 kroons shall be imposed on an operator of a regulated market for failure to perform the obligation to manage financial risk. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) B&ouml;rsikorraldaja poolt finantsriski maandamise kohustuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-1 000 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 1 000 000 kroons shall be imposed on an operator of an exchange for failure to perform the obligation to manage financial risk. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 247. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 247. </inglise>
<eesti>Olulise osaluse n&otilde;uete rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements regarding qualifying holdings </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingus olulise osaluse omandamise v&otilde;i suurendamise tehingu inspektsioonis eelnevalt koosk&otilde;lastamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 10 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A fine in the amount of 10 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed for failure to co-ordinate a transaction to acquire a qualifying holding in an investment firm or to increase a qualifying holding therein in advance with the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingus olulise osaluse v&otilde;&otilde;randamise tehingust inspektsiooni teavitamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 10 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A fine in the amount of 10 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed for failure to notify the Supervision Authority of a transaction to transfer a qualifying holding in an investment firm. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt investeerimis&uuml;hingus olulise osaluse ja k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud m&auml;&auml;ra ulatuses osaluse v&otilde;&otilde;randamise kavatsusest, eelnimetatud tehingute toimumisest v&otilde;i osaluse omandamise tehingu toimumisest inspektsiooni teavitamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 10 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A fine in the amount of 10 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed for failure to notify the Supervision Authority of an intention to transfer a qualifying holding in an investment firm or to transfer a qualifying holding within the rate prescribed by this Act, or of the occurrence of the above-mentioned transactions or of a transaction to acquire a holding. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt koos majandusaasta aruandega olulist osalust omavate aktsion&auml;ride nimekirja esitamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 10 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A fine in the amount of 10 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed for failure to submit a list of shareholders having a qualifying holding to the Supervision Authority together with the annual report. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Isiku poolt Eesti turule kauplemisele v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i Eesti b&ouml;rsil noteeritud aktsiaid emiteerinud Eestis registreeritud aktsiaseltsis olulise osaluse omandamisest ja v&otilde;&otilde;randamisest v&otilde;i k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud m&auml;&auml;ra ulatuses osaluse suurendamisest ja v&auml;hendamisest seda aktsiaseltsi ning selle aktsiaseltsi aktsiaraamatu pidajat teavitamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 10 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A fine in the amount of 10 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on a person for failure to notify a public limited company registered in Estonia whose shares are admitted for trading on the Estonian market or are listed on an Estonian exchange and for failure to notify the person maintaining the share register thereof of the acquisition or transfer of a qualifying holding in the public limited company or of an increase or reduction in the holding within the rate prescribed by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Aktsiaraamatu pidaja poolt Eesti turule kauplemisele v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i Eesti b&ouml;rsil noteeritud aktsiaid emiteerinud Eestis registreeritud aktsiaseltsis olulise osaluse omandamisest ja v&otilde;&otilde;randamisest v&otilde;i k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud m&auml;&auml;ra ulatuses osaluse suurendamisest ja v&auml;hendamisest reguleeritud turu korraldajat v&otilde;i b&ouml;rsikorraldajat teavitamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 10 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A fine in the amount of 10 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on a person maintaining the share register of a public limited company for failure to notify an operator of a regulated market or operator of an exchange of the acquisition or transfer of a qualifying holding in a public limited company registered in Estonia whose shares are admitted for trading on the Estonian market or are listed on an Estonian exchange or of an increase or reduction in the holding in the company within the rate prescribed by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 248. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 248. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtidest ja audiitorist teavitamise n&otilde;ude rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements to give notification regarding managers and auditors of investment firm </inglise>
<eesti>Investeerimis&uuml;hingu, reguleeritud turu korraldaja v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steemi korraldaja poolt juhtidest ja audiitorist inspektsiooni teavitamise kohustuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 10 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine in the amount of 10 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on an investment firm, operator of a regulated market or operator of a securities settlement system for failure to notify the Supervision Authority of its managers and auditor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 249. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 249. </inglise>
<eesti>Sise-eeskirjade n&otilde;uete rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements for internal rules </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt sise-eeskirjade kehtestamise kohustuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 10 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A fine in the amount of 10 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on an investment firm for failure to perform the obligation to establish internal rules. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu poolt siseaudiitorile piisavate &otilde;iguste ja t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste tagamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 10 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A fine in the amount of 10 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on an investment firm for failure to provide the internal auditor with sufficient rights and working conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 250. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 250. </inglise>
<eesti>Aruannete ja teabe n&otilde;uete rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements for reports and information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Investeerimis&uuml;hingu aruandlusele s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uete rikkumise ning usaldatavusn&otilde;uetega seotud teavitamise kohustuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 10 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A fine in the amount of 10 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on an investment firm for violating reporting requirements and for failure to perform the notification obligation connected with prudential requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Reguleeritud turu korraldaja poolt andmete, aruannete v&otilde;i teabe inspektsioonile esitamata j&auml;tmise eest, kui teabe esitamine on k&auml;esolevast seadusest tulenevalt kohustuslik, v&otilde;i eba&otilde;ige v&otilde;i ebat&auml;ieliku teabe esitamise eest, samuti avaldamisele kuuluva teabe avaldamata j&auml;tmise v&otilde;i eba&otilde;ige v&otilde;i ebat&auml;ieliku teabe avaldamise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on an operator of a regulated market for failure to submit information or reports to the Supervision Authority if the provision of information is mandatory on the basis of this Act, or for submission of inaccurate or incomplete information, and for failure to disclose information subject to disclosure or for disclosing inaccurate or incomplete information. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Reguleeritud turu korraldajale andmete v&otilde;i teabe esitamata j&auml;tmise eest, kui teabe esitamine on k&auml;esolevast seadusest tulenevalt kohustuslik, v&otilde;i eba&otilde;ige v&otilde;i ebat&auml;ieliku teabe esitamise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-250 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 250 000 kroons shall be imposed for failure to submit information to the operator of a regulated market if the provision of information is mandatory on the basis of this Act, or for submission of inaccurate or incomplete information. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 251. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 251. </inglise>
<eesti>Reglemendi n&otilde;uete rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements for rules and regulations </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Reguleeritud turu korraldaja poolt reglemendi muudatuste inspektsiooniga koosk&otilde;lastamata j&auml;tmise, alusetu teenuste osutamisest keeldumise v&otilde;i reglemendi n&otilde;uete rikkumise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-1 000 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 1 000 000 kroons shall be imposed on an operator of a regulated market for failure to co-ordinate amendments to the rules and regulations with the Supervision Authority, for unjustified refusal to provide services or for violating the requirements of the rules and regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Reguleeritud turu korraldaja poolt reglemendi avalikustamise kohustuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-1 000 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 1 000 000 kroons shall be imposed on an operator of a regulated market for failure to perform the obligation to disclose the rules and regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 252. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 252. </inglise>
<eesti>Turul osaleja ning turul kaubeldava v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitendi n&otilde;uete rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements for market participator and issuer of securities traded on market </inglise>
<eesti>Turul osaleja ning turul kaubeldava v&auml;&auml;rtpaberi emitendi poolt k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud kohustuste t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-1 750 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 1 750 000 kroons shall be imposed on a market participator and an issuer of securities traded on the market for failure to perform the obligations prescribed in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 253. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 253. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalikustamisele mittekuuluva teabe hoidmise n&otilde;uete rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of requirements to maintain confidentiality of information not subject to disclosure </inglise>
<eesti>Reguleeritud turu korraldaja poolt avalikustamisele mittekuuluva teabe hoidmise n&otilde;uete rikkumise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 20 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine in the amount of 20 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on an operator of a regulated market for violating the requirements to maintain the confidentiality of information not subject to disclosure. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 254. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 254. </inglise>
<eesti>Insaideri ja emitendi kohustuse rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of obligations of insider and issuer </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Insaideri poolt emitendi v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite omandamise v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;randamise ja sellega seotud asjaolude kohta inspektsiooni viimase n&otilde;udmisel teavitamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 20 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A fine in the amount of 20 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on an insider for failure to notify the Supervision Authority, if so required by the latter, of the acquisition or transfer by the insider of the securities of the issuer and of the circumstances related thereto. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Emitendi poolt, kelle v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega kaubeldakse reguleeritud turul, inspektsioonile insaideritest ja nendega seotud isikutest teatamata j&auml;tmise eest v&otilde;i siseteabe hoidmist v&otilde;i selle avaldamist reguleeriva sise-eeskirja koostamata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on an issuer whose securities are traded on a regulated market for failure to notify the Supervision Authority of insiders and persons connected with the latter, or for failure to establish internal rules for maintaining the confidentiality of or disclosing inside information. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 255. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 255. </inglise>
<eesti>Turuga manipuleerimise keelu rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of prohibition on manipulation of market </inglise>
<eesti>Reguleeritud turuga manipuleerimise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-1 750 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 1 750 000 kroons shall be imposed for violating the prohibition on manipulation of the market. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 256. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 256. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tegemise kohustuse rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of obligation to make takeover bid </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tegemise kohustuse rikkumise eest, kui isikule ei olnud antud n&otilde;usolekut loobuda kohustusliku &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tegemisest, - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 100 000-3 000 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine in the amount of 100 000 to 3 000 000 kroons shall be imposed for violating the obligation to make a takeover bid, unless the person is granted permission not to make a mandatory takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 257. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 257. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise n&otilde;uete rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of takeover bid requirements </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tja poolt &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise raames samaliigiliste aktsiate omanike ebav&otilde;rdse kohtlemise eest, &uuml;lev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i sihtemitendi poolt sihtisikutele &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise kaalumiseks olulise, &otilde;ige, t&auml;pse, t&auml;ieliku v&otilde;i &uuml;hesuguse teabe andmata j&auml;tmise eest v&otilde;i eksitava, eba&otilde;ige v&otilde;i ebat&auml;pse teabe andmise eest v&otilde;i erinevatele sihtisikutele erisuguse teabe andmise eest v&otilde;i sihtisikutel &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise kaalumise takistamise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-200 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 200 000 kroons shall be imposed on the offerer for unequal treatment of holders of shares of the same type within the framework of a takeover bid, on the offerer or target issuer for failure to provide the target persons with significant, correct, accurate, complete and identical information for informed consideration of the takeover bid or for the provision of misleading, incorrect or inaccurate information or for the provision of different information to different target persons or for hindering the target persons upon consideration of the takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 258. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 258. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise reeglite rikkumine </eesti>
<inglise>Violation of takeover bid rules </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tja, juriidilisest isikust &uuml;lev&otilde;tja n&otilde;ukogu liikme, juhatuse liikme v&otilde;i neid asendava organi liikme, sihtemitendi, selle sihtemitendi n&otilde;ukogu liikme v&otilde;i juhatuse liikme, eelnimetatutega koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutseva isiku v&otilde;i sihtemitendi aktsion&auml;ri poolt &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisreeglite v&otilde;i sihtemitendi aktsiaid noteeriva b&ouml;rsi reglemendi &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumist reguleerivate s&auml;tete rikkumise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 250 000-1 000 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine in the amount of 250 000 to 1 000 000 kroons shall be imposed on an offerer, on a member of the management board, supervisory board or body substituting therefor of an offerer which is a legal person, on a target issuer, on a member of the management board or supervisory board of the target issuer, on a person acting in concert with the above-mentioned persons or on a shareholder of the target issuer for violating the takeover bid rules or the provisions of the rules and regulations of the exchange where the shares of the target issuer are listed which regulate the takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 259. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 259. </inglise>
<eesti>Keelatud &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tegemine </eesti>
<inglise>Making a prohibited takeover bid </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i temaga koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutseva isiku poolt sellesama sihtemitendi suhtes kuue kuu jooksul, &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumisest arvates, uue &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise tegemise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 50 000-500 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine in the amount of 50 000 to 500 000 kroons shall be imposed on an offerer or a person acting in concert with the offerer for making a new takeover bid with regard to the same target issuer within six months as of the expiry of the term of a previous takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 260. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 260. </inglise>
<eesti>Karistustest teavitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Notification regarding penalties </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtul on &otilde;igus k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 238-259 kohaselt m&auml;&auml;ratud trahvidest teavitada &uuml;leriigilise p&auml;evalehe kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>Courts have the right to disclose information concerning fines imposed pursuant to &sect;&sect; 238-259 of this Act in a national daily newspaper. </inglise>
<eesti>Teates peab olema m&auml;rgitud isiku nimi, kellele trahv m&auml;&auml;rati, ning trahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise p&otilde;hjus ja kuup&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>The notice shall set out the name of the person on whom the fine is imposed and the reason for and date of imposition of the fine. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 261. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 261. </inglise>
<eesti>Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli koostamine </eesti>
<inglise>Preparation of administrative offence reports </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Inspektsiooni volitatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajal on &otilde;igus koostada protokoll k&auml;esoleva seaduse rikkumise kohta juriidilise isiku poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Authorised employees of the Supervision Authority have the right to prepare reports on violations of this Act by legal persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud protokollis peavad sisalduma j&auml;rgmised andmed: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A report specified in subsection (1) of this section shall set out the following information: </inglise>
<eesti>1) koostamise aeg ja koht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the time and place of preparation thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) inspektsiooni aadress ja m&auml;rge selle kohta, et protokoll on koostatud inspektsiooni nimel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the address of the Supervision Authority and a notation indicating that the report is prepared in the name of the Supervision Authority; </inglise>
<eesti>3) protokolli koostanud isiku ametinimetus ning ees- ja perekonnanimi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the official title, given name and surname of the person who prepares the report; </inglise>
<eesti>4) haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja nimi, registrikood ja asukoht; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the name, registration number and seat of the administrative offender; </inglise>
<eesti>5) haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja ees- ja perekonnanimi ning ametikoht; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the given name, surname and position of the representative of the administrative offender; </inglise>
<eesti>6) haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise koht, aeg ja kirjeldus; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the place, time and description of the administrative offence; </inglise>
<eesti>7) viide seaduss&auml;tetele, mille alusel haldusvastutust kohaldatakse; </eesti>
<inglise>7) a reference to the provisions of legislation which are the basis for imposition of administrative liability; </inglise>
<eesti>8) haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja seletus v&otilde;i m&auml;rge seletuse andmisest loobumise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>8) an explanation provided by the representative of the administrative offender or a notation concerning refusal to provide an explanation; </inglise>
<eesti>9) m&auml;rge selle kohta, et haldus&otilde;iguserikkujale on selgitatud tema &otilde;igust kasutada &otilde;igusabi. </eesti>
<inglise>9) a notation indicating that the administrative offender has been informed of his or her right to obtain legal assistance. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Protokollile kirjutavad alla selle koostanud t&ouml;&ouml;taja ja haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja volitatud esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The worker who prepares the report and the authorised representative of the administrative offender shall sign the report. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja keeldub protokollile alla kirjutamast, tehakse sellesse vastav kanne. </eesti>
<inglise>If the representative of the administrative offender refuses to sign the report, this shall be noted in the report. </inglise>
<eesti>Protokollile lisatakse haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja kirjalikud m&auml;rkused protokolli, samuti protokollile allakirjutamisest keeldumise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>The written comments of the representative of the administrative offender concerning the report or refusal to sign the report shall be annexed to the report. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokoll koostatakse kahes eksemplaris, millest &uuml;ks j&auml;&auml;b koostajale, teine haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An administrative offence report shall be prepared in two original copies, one of which shall be retained by the person who prepared the report and the other by the representative of the administrative offender. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 262. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 262. </inglise>
<eesti>Menetlus juriidilise isiku haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asjas </eesti>
<inglise>Proceedings in matters concerning administrative offences of legal persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse rikkumise asja arutamise ja karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramise &otilde;igus on maa- v&otilde;i linnakohtul ja inspektsiooni juhatuse esimehel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) County and city court judges and the chairman of the management board of the Supervision Authority have the right to hear matters regarding violations of this Act and to impose penalties. </inglise>
<eesti>Inspektsiooni juhatuse esimehel on &otilde;igus m&auml;&auml;rata rahatrahv kuni 50 000 krooni ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>The chairman of the management board of the Supervision Authority has the right to impose fines of up to 50 000 kroons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Menetlus k&auml;esoleva seaduse rikkumise asjas juriidilise isiku poolt toimub haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustiku (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453) menetluskorda j&auml;rgides. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Proceedings in matters regarding offences provided for in this Act and committed by legal persons shall be conducted pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Code of Administrative Offences (RT I 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel juriidilisele isikule m&auml;&auml;ratud rahatrahv n&otilde;utakse sisse haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustikus ja t&auml;itemenetluse seadustikus s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A fine imposed on a legal person on the basis of this Act shall be collected pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Code of Administrative Offences and the Code of Enforcement Procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>VII osa </eesti>
<inglise>Part VII </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Implementation of Act </inglise>
<eesti>26. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 26 </inglise>
<eesti>Rakenduss&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Implementing Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 263. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 263. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Repeal of Act </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast tunnistatakse seni kehtinud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru seadus (RT I 1993, 35, 543; 1995, 22, 328; 1996, 26, 528; 1997, 34, 535; 1998, 61, 979; 2000, 10, 55) kehtetuks. </eesti>
<inglise>The Securities Market Act (RT I 1993, 35, 543; 1995, 22, 328; 1996, 26, 528; 1997, 34, 535; 1998, 61, 979; 2000, 10, 55) currently in force is repealed as of the date on which this Act enters into force. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 264. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 264. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevuslubade kehtivus </eesti>
<inglise>Validity of activity licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise ajal kehtivat tegevusluba omavate v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutseliste osaliste tegevusload kehtivad kuni vastavate tegevuslubade kehtivuse t&auml;htaja l&otilde;puni v&otilde;i nende kehtetuks tunnistamiseni k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Activity licences of professional securities market participants which are valid at the time this Act enters into force shall remain valid until the expiry of their term of validity or until they are revoked pursuant to the procedure prescribed in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumiseni kehtinud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru seaduses s&auml;testatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberivahendaja suhtes kohaldatakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses investeerimis&uuml;hingu kohta s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The provisions of this Act regarding investment firms shall apply to securities brokers prescribed in the Securities Market Act which is valid until the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 265. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 265. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevuse koosk&otilde;lla viimine </eesti>
<inglise>Bringing activities into compliance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise ajal kehtivat tegevusluba omavad v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselised osalised peavad oma tegevuse ja dokumendid viima k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatuga vastavusse kuue kuu jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest, kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikest 2 ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Professional securities market participants which hold a valid activity licence at the time this Act enters into force shall bring their activities and documents into compliance with the provisions of this Act within six months as of the entry into force of this Act, unless otherwise prescribed in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise ajal kehtivat tegevusluba omavate v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutseliste osaliste aktsiakapital peab hiljemalt 2002. aasta 1. juuniks olema v&auml;hemalt 125 000 eurot ning peab hiljemalt 2003. aasta 1. juuniks vastama k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 93 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 2 ja &sect; 152 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The share capital of professional securities market participants which hold a valid activity licence at the time this Act enters into force shall be at least 125 000 euro by 1 June 2002 at the latest and shall meet the requirements prescribed in clause 93 (1) 2) and subsection 152 (1) of this Act by 1 June 2003 at the latest. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 266. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 266. </inglise>
<eesti>Olulise osaluse loa taotlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Application for permission for qualifying holding </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 73 s&auml;testatud olulise osaluse omandanud isik, kellel ei ole samas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud olulise osaluse luba, peab selle taotlema vastavalt k&auml;esolevale seadusele kuue kuu jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who has acquired a qualifying holding provided for in &sect; 73 of this Act and who does not have permission for the qualifying holding as provided for in the same section shall apply for permission in accordance with this Act within six months as of the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui isik ei t&auml;ida k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud kohustust, peab ta oma k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 73 nimetatud k&uuml;nnist &uuml;letava osaluse v&otilde;&otilde;randama 2002. aasta 31. maiks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a person does not perform the obligation prescribed in subsection (1) of this section, the person shall transfer the holding in excess of the threshold specified in &sect; 73 of this Act by 31 May 2002. </inglise>
<eesti>Alates 2002. aasta 1. juunist ei tohi ta kasutada sellest osalusest tulenevat h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;igust. </eesti>
<inglise>As of 1 June 2002, the person may not use the voting rights arising from such holding. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 267. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 267. </inglise>
<eesti>Eurode arvestus </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation of euro </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolevas seaduses eurodes toodud n&auml;itajad arvestatakse kroonidesse Eesti Panga ametliku vahetuskursi alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>The amounts stated in this Act in euro shall be calculated in kroons on the basis of the official Bank of Estonia exchange rate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 268. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 268. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjon </eesti>
<inglise>Takeover bid committee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kuni 2002. aasta 1. septembrini on &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumiste koosk&otilde;lastamise ja erandite tegemise otsustamise ainup&auml;devus inspektsiooni m&auml;&auml;ratud b&ouml;rsikorraldaja juures tegutseval &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisi koosk&otilde;lastaval komisjonil (edaspidi &uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjon). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Until 1 September 2002, the approval of takeover bid and grant of exceptions shall be within the exclusive competence of the committee approving takeover bids which operates at an exchange operator appointed by the Supervision Authority (hereinafter: takeover bid committee). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjonil on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda &uuml;lev&otilde;tjalt ja sihtemitendilt teavet seoses &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The takeover bid committee has the right to demand information from the offerer and target issuer regarding the takeover bid. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni poolt oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitatakse riigi poolt &otilde;igusaktis s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Damage caused by the takeover bid committee in the course of its activities shall be compensated by the state on the bases and pursuant to the procedure prescribed by legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigil on tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitamise korral tagasin&otilde;ude &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>The state has the right of recourse in the case of compensating damage. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni organisatsiooniline &uuml;lesehitus, &otilde;igused ja kohustused s&auml;testatakse b&ouml;rsikorraldaja reglemendis. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The organisational structure, rights and obligations of the takeover bid committee shall be set out in the rules and regulations of the operator of the exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 269. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 269. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni koosseis </eesti>
<inglise>Composition of takeover bid committee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni kuulub viis liiget, kellest kolm nimetab b&ouml;rsikorraldaja ja kaks inspektsiooni juhatuse esimees. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The takeover bid committee shall consist of five members, of which three are appointed by the operator of the exchange and two by the chairman of the management board of the Supervision Authority. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni liikmed valivad endi hulgast &uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni esimehe, kes koordineerib &uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni t&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise>The members of the takeover bid committee shall elect the chairman of the committee from among themselves who shall co-ordinate the activities of the committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni liige ei v&otilde;ta &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise koosk&otilde;lastamise ja erandi tegemise otsustamisest osa, kui ta on otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt huvitatud asja lahendist v&otilde;i esineb p&otilde;hjendatud kahtlus selle liikme erapooletuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A member of the takeover bid committee shall not participate in deciding on the approval of a takeover bid or the grant of an exception if he or she is directly or indirectly interested in the outcome or if there are justified doubts as to his or her impartiality. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui &uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni liige ei saa k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud asjaolude ilmnemisel v&otilde;i muu erakorralise asjaolu t&otilde;ttu isiklikult &uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni t&ouml;&ouml;s osaleda, m&auml;&auml;rab selle isiku &uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni liikmeks nimetanud b&ouml;rsikorraldaja v&otilde;i inspektsiooni juhatuse esimees temale asendaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a member of the takeover bid committee cannot participate in person in the work of the takeover bid committee because of the existence of circumstances set out in subsection (2) of this section or due to any other extraordinary circumstances, the operator of the exchange or the chairman of the management board of the Supervision Authority who appointed the member shall appoint a replacement for him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni liikmed on kohustatud seoses tegevusega &uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjonis hoidma saadud avalikustamisele mittekuuluvat teavet t&auml;htajatult saladuses, v&auml;lja arvatud juhtudel, kui avalikustamisele mittekuuluva teabe avalikustamise kohustus tuleneb seadusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Members of the takeover bid committee are required to maintain indefinitely the confidentiality of any confidential information obtained by reason of their activities in the takeover bid committee, unless the disclosure of confidential information is prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 270. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 270. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni otsus </eesti>
<inglise>Resolution of takeover bid committee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Igal &uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni liikmel on &uuml;ks h&auml;&auml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Each member of the takeover bid committee has one vote. </inglise>
<eesti>Liikmel ei ole &otilde;igust h&auml;&auml;letamisest keelduda ega erapooletuks j&auml;&auml;da, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui ta huvide konflikti t&otilde;ttu ei v&otilde;i osaleda h&auml;&auml;letamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>Members do not have the right to refuse to vote or abstain, except in cases where they may not participate in the voting because of a conflict of interests. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni otsus on vastu v&otilde;etud, kui selle poolt h&auml;&auml;letas v&auml;hemalt kolm &uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni liiget. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A resolution of the takeover bid committee is adopted if at least three members of the takeover bid committee vote in favour. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 271. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 271. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relevalve &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumiste &uuml;le </eesti>
<inglise>Supervision of takeover bids </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kuni 2002. aasta 1. septembrini kontrollib &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumiste vastavust &otilde;igusaktidele koost&ouml;&ouml;s inspektsiooniga ning n&otilde;ustab ja teenindab &uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni inspektsiooni poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud b&ouml;rsikorraldaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Until 1 September 2002, an operator of an exchange appointed by the Supervision Authority shall monitor the compliance of takeover bids with legislation in co-operation with the Supervision Authority and shall advise and provide services to the takeover bid committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud b&ouml;rsikorraldajal on koosk&otilde;lastatult inspektsiooniga &otilde;igus kehtestada &uuml;lev&otilde;tjale teenustasu &uuml;lev&otilde;tmispakkumise koosk&otilde;lastamise menetluse l&auml;biviimiseks ja oma &uuml;lev&otilde;tmiskomisjoni tegevuse kulude katteks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Subject to approval by the Supervision Authority, an operator of an exchange specified in subsection (1) of this section has the right to establish a service fee on an offerer for carrying out the procedure of approving a takeover bid and to cover the operating costs of its takeover bid committee. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 272. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 272. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steemi korraldajale rakendatavad erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Special rules applicable to securities settlement system operators </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Seni, kuni &uuml;helegi isikule ei ole k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 217 ja 218 alusel v&auml;lja antud tegevusluba tegutsemiseks v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steemi korraldajana, v&otilde;ib v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steemi korraldajana tegutseda Eesti v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite keskregistri pidaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Until such time as a person has been issued an activity licence to operate as an operator of a securities settlement system on the basis of &sect;&sect; 217 and 218 of this Act, the registrar of the Estonian Central Register of Securities may operate as an operator of a securities settlement system. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&auml;&auml;rtpaberiarvelduss&uuml;steemi korraldajana tegutseval Eesti v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite keskregistri pidajal ei ole &otilde;igust tagada &uuml;lekandekorralduste alusel tekkinud n&otilde;uete ja kohustuste t&auml;itmist ega v&otilde;tta muid t&auml;iendavaid finantsriske. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The registrar of the Estonian Central Register of Securities, while it is operating as an operator of a securities settlement system, does not have the right to guarantee the performance of claims and obligations arising on the basis of transfer orders or to assume other additional financial risks. </inglise>
